    <del:identifier>contribution_260</del:identifier>
    <del:text>El Parlamento dedicГғВі especial atenciГғВіnГӮВ a garantizar las salvaguardas y los derechos fundamentales en la negociaciГғВіn del paquete de asilo y de inmigraciГғВіn. Se podrГғВЎ discutir esta propuesta, pero ciertamente no se puede descalificar sobre la base de que no respete estos derechos y tampoco los de los menores no acompaГғВұados.
Nos importa mucho el papel de la ComisiГғВіn en la negociaciГғВіn con los terceros paГғВӯses, que va a ser clave para el ГғВ©xito, y el propio papel de la ComisiГғВіn a la hora de fomentar y hacer posible la aplicaciГғВіn del Reglamento. Esto no va a ser una rutina, esto no es business as usual, esto es un desafГғВӯo que nos afecta a todas las instituciones de la UniГғВіn.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:28:32</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_192"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_259"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_260"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/role_participant_85">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Role"/>
    <del:name>President</del:name>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_129">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_129</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Vicent MarzГғВ  IbГғВЎГғВұez</del:name>
    <del:name>Elisabeth Grossmann</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Verts_ALE"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_189">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_189</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Pe 6 decembrie anul trecut, a avut loc un fapt fГ„ВғrГ„Вғ precedent ГғВ®n Uniunea EuropeanГ„Вғ, ГҲВҷi anume anularea alegerilor prezidenГҲВӣiale din RomГғВўnia. Pe 9 martie anul acesta, candidatul care avea cele mai mari ГҲВҷanse sГ„Вғ cГғВўГҲВҷtige alegerile prezidenГҲВӣiale ГҲВҷi care a cГғВўГҲВҷtigat primul tur de scrutin de anul trecut, a fost interzis pentru o nouГ„Вғ candidaturГ„Вғ, i s-a interzis sГ„Вғ candideze din nou.
MГғВўine-poimГғВўine vor fi interzise probabil ГҲВҷi partidele care nu corespund noii politici a RomГғВўniei, care a luat-o pe un drum al dictaturii.
Ce face UE ГғВ®n aceastГ„Вғ situaГҲВӣie? Comisia EuropeanГ„Вғ nu are niciun fel de reacГҲВӣie. Sunt oficiali care acoperГ„Вғ acest abuz, iar reacГҲВӣiile Statelor Unite ale Americii sunt ignorate pur ГҲВҷi simplu de cГ„Вғtre autoritГ„ВғГҲВӣile din RomГғВўnia.
VГ„Вғ atrag atenГҲВӣia cГ„Вғ astГ„Вғzi se ГғВ®ntГғВўmplГ„Вғ ГғВ®n RomГғВўnia, iar mГғВўine se poate ГғВ®ntГғВўmpla ГғВ®n oricare ГҲВӣarГ„Вғ a Uniunii Europene.</del:text>
    <del:text>However, I do believe two things. First of all, without allowing men to actively, actively participate in gender equality, we will never achieve anything. So this feminist hatred against men will not bring us any further, but will polarise society instead.
Secondly, we women are part of the problem. As long as we victimise ourselves, we continue to keep the vicious circle of gender inequality intact. It's time to take responsibility for our actions and to refuse to be treated as victims. We are not victims. If we refuse to be, we are not victims.
It's time we take our rightful place in the society just because we can and not because a gender quota assigns us a spot.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:51:58</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:38:10</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_109"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_139"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_188"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_189"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_250">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_250</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Und trotz der weitreichenden Auswirkungen auf Grundrechte hat die Kommission es erneut verpasst, die mГғВ¶glichen Auswirkungen ihres Vorschlags zu analysierenГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ es gibt wieder keine FolgenabschГғВӨtzung. All das fГғВјgt sich nahtlos in das Narrativ der Kommission unter Frau von der Leyen, Migranten seien potenziell eine Bedrohung. Diese ErzГғВӨhlung lehne ich ab. Und Herr Brunner, wir werden einige Verbesserungen fГғВјr Ihren Vorschlag einarbeiten mГғВјssen, damit das Ganze funktioniert.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:15:08</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_185"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_249"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_250"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_169">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_169</del:identifier>
    <del:name>ГҺВңГҺВ№ГҸВҮГҺВ¬ГҺВ»ГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВ§ГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВ¶ГҺВ·ГҸВҖГҺВұГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВӯГҺВ»ГҺВұ</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_362">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_362</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The US has also been a long-term partner, but now it seems that President Trump is using the divide-and-rule model known since Roman times to get China off Russia's side to divide Europe and oppress others under its own power.
One should not side with those who dream of Tsarist power or world empire. MrГӮВ Toveri, how do we find European cooperation and understand that the situation is that only a united and strong Europe, which covers its powers in all areas of activity, will survive?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:58:32</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_262"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_361"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_362"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_116">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_116</del:identifier>
    <del:text>To deliver on our ambitious goals, we must continue this positive engagement and work together. We want to move forward swiftly, without delay and with the co-legislators' support.
Going forward, I would like to highlight that each Commissioner will present an annual progress report on implementation and enforcement to the respective Parliament committee. The reports will present progress towards key policy objectives, enforcement and simplification actions and take stock of stakeholder dialogues, stress tests and reality checks.
We also wish to work closely with you to deliver fast progress on simplification measures. To this end, I would like to emphasise that this legislation is urgent and requires prioritisation, in particular our 'stop the clock' proposal contained in the first Omnibus proposal on sustainability reporting. This is why we identify them as such in our work programme and are consulting actively with Parliament on them and would encourage you to handle them with priority.
We also hope to count on your support to minimise additional administrative burdens introduced during the legislative process. For this purpose, we will put forward a simple methodology that could help you assess the impacts of significant amendments. We also believe that it is important that each institution sets the resources to deliver on this commitment in our existing interinstitutional agreement.
To conclude, honourable Members, as you can see, this Commission is firmly committed to improving implementation and delivering simpler and more cost-efficient rules. We hope to count on your support so that we can deliver fast and sustained changes on the ground in the coming months and years.</del:text>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:56:47</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T12:55:56</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_31"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_115"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_116"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_226">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_226</del:identifier>
    <del:name>ГҺВ“ГҺВ№ГҺВ¬ГҺВҪГҺВҪГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВңГҺВұГҺВҪГҺВ№ГҺВ¬ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВӮ,</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_416">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_416</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:57:04</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_290"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_415"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_416"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_92">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_92</del:identifier>
    <del:text>In dieser Situation sollte man meinen, dass die EU bereit ist, endlich wirklich gegenzusteuern, dass die EU bereit ist zu einem echten Politikwechsel, dass die EU bereit ist, die Industrie zu rettenГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ sollte man meinen, passiert aber nicht; es geht einfach so weiter wie bisher. Es wird stur weitergemacht, und das ist die ganze Wahrheit hinter Ihrem Omnibus: weiter wie bisher. Und das Schlimmste ist, dass Sie das auch wissen. Sie wissen ganz genau, dass es der Green Deal ist, der unsere Wirtschaft zerstГғВ¶rt.
Sie wissen, dass Sie seit fГғВјnf Jahren einem Irrweg folgen, aber das zuzugeben, hieГғВҹe fГғВјr Sie Gesichtsverlust, und darum machen Sie weiter wie bisher. Darum opfern Sie aus Eitelkeit lieber unsere wirtschaftlichen Grundlagen und die Zukunft unserer Jugend. Dieser Omnibus, diese ГғВ„nderungen, ist viel zu wenig und kommt viel zu spГғВӨt.</del:text>
    <del:text>A la seГғВұora de la guerra no le importa que el gasto militar lo paguen los pueblos, no le importa que la factura de la guerra la pague la ciudadanГғВӯa, prefiere apoyar el belicismo antes que la polГғВӯtica social, prefiere apoyar mГғВЎs gasto militar y menos servicios pГғВәblicos como la vivienda, la salud o las pensiones.
Hay que volver a la defensa de la paz, a la resoluciГғВіn pacГғВӯfica de conflictos, a la diplomacia, a la defensa de los derechos humanos. Hay que volver a la democracia, no a estar supeditado ni a la OTAN ni a los Estados Unidos. No al rearme, ni a la escalada militar y belicista de la UniГғВіn Europea. (La oradora pronuncia una frase en gallego).</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:21:07</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:44:00</del:timestamp>
