  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_337">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_337</del:identifier>
    <del:text>ГҺВҡГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҸВҒГҺВҜГҺВұ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВҜГҸВҒГҺВ№ГҺВұ ГҺВөГҸВҒГҸВүГҸВ„ГҺВ®ГҺВјГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВұ:
ГҺВ ГҸВҺГҸВӮ ГҺВёГҺВұ ГҺВіГҺВҜГҺВҪГҺВөГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВ· ГҺВәГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВҪГҺВҝГҺВјГҺВ® ГҸВ„ГҸВүГҺВҪ ГҺВұГҺВјГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҸВҺГҺВҪ ГҺВҙГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВұГҺВҪГҸВҺГҺВҪ ГҺВіГҺВ№ГҺВұ ГҸВ„ГҺВ· ГҸВҮГҸВҒГҺВ·ГҺВјГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҺВҙГҸВҢГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВғГҺВ· ГҸВ„ГҸВүГҺВҪ ГҺВәГҸВҒГҺВұГҸВ„ГҸВҺГҺВҪ ГҺВјГҺВөГҺВ»ГҸВҺГҺВҪ; ГҺВ‘ГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВҒГҺВұГҺВ№ГҸВ„ГҺВ®ГҸВ„ГҸВүГҸВӮ, ГҸВғГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҺВұГҸВҒГҸВ„ГҺВ®ГҸВғГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҸВҖГҺВҝГҺВ»ГҺВ»ГҸВҺГҺВҪ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВғГҺВ·ГҺВјГҺВұГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҸВҺГҺВҪ ГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВҒГҺВұГҺВіГҸВҢГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҸВүГҺВҪ, ГҸВҶГҺВұГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВ¬ГҺВ¶ГҺВҝГҺВјГҺВұГҺВ№, ГҸВҢГҸВҖГҸВүГҸВӮ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҸВҖГҺВ»ГҺВ·ГҺВёГҸВ…ГҸВғГҺВјГҺВҝГҸВҚ ГҸВ„ГҸВүГҺВҪ ГҺВәГҸВҒГҺВұГҸВ„ГҸВҺГҺВҪ ГҺВјГҺВөГҺВ»ГҸВҺГҺВҪ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВ¬ГҺВ»ГҺВ»ГҸВүГҺВҪ ГҺВ№ГҺВҙГҺВ№ГҺВұГҺВ№ГҸВ„ГҺВөГҸВҒГҺВҝГҸВ„ГҺВ®ГҸВ„ГҸВүГҺВҪ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВӮ.
ГҺВҳГҺВұ ГҸВ…ГҸВҖГҺВ¬ГҸВҒГҸВҮГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВҪ ГҺВәГҸВҒГҺВ¬ГҸВ„ГҺВ· ГҺВјГҺВӯГҺВ»ГҺВ· ГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҺВёГҺВұ ГҺВ»ГҺВ¬ГҺВІГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВҪ ГҸВ„ГҺВ· ГҺВјГҺВөГҸВҒГҺВҜГҺВҙГҺВұ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҺВ»ГҺВӯГҺВҝГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВӮ; ГҺВ•ГҺВ»ГҺВ»ГҺВ¬ГҺВҙГҺВұ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВҡГҸВҚГҸВҖГҸВҒГҺВҝГҸВӮ ГҸВҖГҸВҒГҺВӯГҸВҖГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВөГҸВҖГҸВүГҸВҶГҺВөГҺВ»ГҺВ·ГҺВёГҺВҝГҸВҚГҺВҪ ГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҺВјГҺВӯГҺВіГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВұ, ГҺВҙГҺВөГҺВҙГҺВҝГҺВјГҺВӯГҺВҪГҸВүГҺВҪ ГҸВ„ГҸВүГҺВҪ ГҺВұГҸВ…ГҺВҫГҺВ·ГҺВјГҺВӯГҺВҪГҸВүГҺВҪ ГҺВұГҺВҪГҺВұГҺВіГҺВәГҸВҺГҺВҪ ГҺВ»ГҸВҢГҺВіГҸВү ГҺВіГҺВөГҸВүГҺВіГҸВҒГҺВұГҸВҶГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ®ГҸВӮ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВӮ ГҺВёГҺВӯГҸВғГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВіГҺВөГҺВ№ГҸВ„ГҺВҪГҺВҜГҺВұГҸВғГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВјГҺВө ГҸВҮГҸВҺГҸВҒГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҸВҢГҸВҖГҸВүГҸВӮ ГҺВ· ГҺВӨГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҺВәГҺВҜГҺВұ.
ГҺВӨГҺВөГҺВ»ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ¬, ГҺВөГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҸВүГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВҠГҺВәГҺВ® ГҺВ¬ГҺВјГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВ® ГҺВөГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҸВүГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҺВәГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ®; ГҺВЈГҺВұГҸВҶГҸВҺГҸВӮ ГҺВөГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҸВүГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВҠГҺВәГҺВ®, ГҸВғГҺВө ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВҪГҺВӯГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВјГҺВӯГҸВҒГҺВҝГҸВӮ ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВөГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҸВүГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВҠГҺВәГҺВ®ГҸВӮ ГҺВ¬ГҺВјГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВғГҺВө ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВјГҺВҜГҺВұ ГҺВұГҺВјГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ® ГҺВҙГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВ¬ГҺВҪГҺВ· ГҺВҙГҺВөГҺВҪ ГҺВёГҺВұ ГҸВғГҸВ…ГҺВјГҺВјГҺВөГҸВ„ГҺВӯГҸВҮГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВ· ГҺВӨГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҺВәГҺВҜГҺВұ. ГҺВ”ГҺВөГҺВҪ ГҺВёГҺВұ ГҺВІГҺВ¬ГҺВ»ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВјГҺВө ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҺВҪ ГҺВ»ГҸВҚГҺВәГҺВҝ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҸВҶГҸВ…ГҺВ»ГҺВ¬ГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҸВҖГҸВҒГҸВҢГҺВІГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВұ.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:26:32</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_243"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_336"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_337"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_21">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_21</del:identifier>
    <del:text>(Parliament rejected the request)
So the agenda is unchanged.
We move now to a request by the ESN Group ГўВҖВ“ for Wednesday as well ГўВҖВ“ which has requested that a Commission statement on 'Presidential elections in Romania, particularly the Constitutional Court's ruling of 8ГӮВ March' be added as the second point in the afternoon.
I give the floor toГӮВ Christine Anderson to move the request.</del:text>
    <del:text>However, you will not escape from the fundamental questions. You are talking about the security of Europe. Great. I would like to ask you how the security of Europe is served by cancelling elections in Romania and not allowing the candidate with 50ГӮВ % of support to run? How does allowing Tusk to destroy the opposition, take away all public money from the opposition party, and imprison MEPs serve Europe's security? How do your immigration policy and the Migration Pact serve European security? And the key question is: do you want Europe to defend itself from external threats, or for Europeans to kill each other? Instead of integrating Europe in the face of threats, as usual you choose your particular interests.
If the strength of Ukraine grew from the number of your empty words, the Ukrainian army now would be preparing to parade in Moscow. Do you want to help? You have EURГӮВ 300ГӮВ billion of frozen Russian assets. Give them to Ukraine. That will be enough for five years of war. But you won't do it. You keep it because you want them to use to negotiate further resets with Russia. That is why you keep attacking America, provoking it to leave Europe. And you yourselves do not have those military capabilities. Your behaviour will cause the EU countries that border Russia to be in great danger.ГӮВ President Zelenskyy found about this after the summit in London. He will not provide the army weapons with your slogans, and that's why we need to change it.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:20:07</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:07:05</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_18"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_20"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_21"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_88">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_88</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Marta Kos,</del:name>
    <del:name>Leniie Umerova,</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_161">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_161</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:text>MeГ„В‘utim, Г…Вҫelim vas podsjetiti da za svaki euro koji zaradi muГ…ВЎkarac, Г…Вҫena zaradi 0,87 eura. Trenutno stanje u Europskom parlamentu, Г…Вҫena ima oko 40 posto, ali meГ„В‘u liderima politiГ„ВҚkih grupacija i pojedinaca, predsjednicima vlada ta brojka puno je manja.
Naravno da prepreke poput rodnog jaza u plaГ„ВҮama, staklenog stropa i naplaГ„ВҮenog kuГ„ВҮanskog rada i dalje ograniГ„ВҚavaju Г…Вҫene. KljuГ„ВҚne su nam politike koje podrГ…Вҫavaju pristup kvalitetnom obrazovanju, poduzetniГ…ВЎtvu i financijskim resursima i naravno bolja ravnoteГ…Вҫa izmeГ„В‘u privatnog i poslovnog Г…Вҫivota, pa i u ruralnim podruГ„ВҚjima, nemojmo na to zaboraviti.
MeГ„В‘utim, viГ…ВЎe od polovice svjetske populacije Г„ВҚinimo mi, Г…Вҫene. U Europskoj uniji ima nas 52 posto. Imamo potencijala preoblikovati sustave moГ„ВҮi, ekonomiju i druГ…ВЎtvene vrijednosti. Ali ne kao raГ…ВЎtimani orkestar, ne kao ideologija, veГ„ВҮ kao one koje doista Г…Вҫele politiku iskoristiti u svrhu poboljГ…ВЎanja uvjeta Г…Вҫena i da svim Г…Вҫenama u Europskoj uniji bude bolje.
NeГ„ВҮemo to postiГ„ВҮi ako Г„ВҮemo se samo nadmetati u tome tko je u pravu, a tko nije.
ZakljuГ„ВҚit Г„ВҮu, ekonomska neovisnost omoguГ„ВҮuje jedino slobodu izbora i na tome trebamo raditi.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:12:16</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:59:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_120"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_115"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_160"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_161"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_16">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_16</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Isabelle Le Callennec,</del:name>
    <del:name>ГҺВ“ГҺВ№ГҺВ¬ГҺВҪГҺВҪГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВңГҺВұГҺВҪГҺВ№ГҺВ¬ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВӮ</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_395">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_395</del:identifier>
    <del:text>A UniГғВЈo Europeia reconheceu o ГғВіbvio: a Europa nГғВЈo estГғВЎ pronta para se defender. A paz depende da forГғВ§a, e a Europa nГғВЈo tem a suficiente.ГӮВ Durante dГғВ©cadas, acreditГғВЎmos num mundo sem guerra, numa ordem baseada em regras e num continente seguro, sem investimento em defesa.
A NATO continua a ser o pilar da nossa seguranГғВ§a, imaginar uma defesa europeia isolada da AlianГғВ§a ГғВ© uma fantasia perigosa.
NГғВЈo precisamos de um exГғВ©rcito europeu, mas de 27 forГғВ§as armadas eficazes, interoperГғВЎveis, com padrГғВөes comuns e capacidade de resposta coordenada. Isso significa mais harmonizaГғВ§ГғВЈo, defesa aГғВ©rea avanГғВ§ada e uma indГғВәstria de defesa robusta; assegurar o domГғВӯnio estratГғВ©gico no espaГғВ§o e no ciberespaГғВ§o, tudo isto sГғВЈo escolhas que definirГғВЈo o futuro da Europa.
Os desafios que enfrentamos nГғВЈo sГғВЈo teГғВіricos, sГғВЈo reais, e a HistГғВіria nГғВЈo espera por quem hesita. Precisamos de uma polГғВӯtica de defesa ГғВ  altura do nosso tempo.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:39:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_210"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_394"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_395"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_231">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_231</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Now, the worldwide backlash against abortion, in combination with increasingly restrictive US policies, could lead to stockpiling again and shortages. And that is why I urge this Commissioner to aim to include mifepristone and misoprostol on the list of essential medications.
As the Commissioner himself said, it's about providing critical medication there and where needed. And if we don't do this, we really risk a lot of women conducting unsafe, not legal or illegal abortions at home, especially in those Member States where this right is severely restricted.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:35:55</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_101"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_230"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_231"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_202">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_202</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Therefore, we welcome the ambition to maintain a list of critical medicines for which European research and production capacities would be granted. But it is not an easy task. As critical, we consider a wide range of medicines, including those old simple molecules whose production was, due to cost optimisation, transferred outside the EU in the past decades. And now we want them back.
Also, we shall consider what should be the role of the EU here. In my opinion, mainly coordination of fair distribution of supportive projects among Member States to avoid duplication and at the end, after implementation, coordination of logistics of critical medicines.
However, we believe that tools like CMA and Pharma Package can contribute positively to increase medicine supplies resilience on our continent, and in this regard, Mr Commissioner, you have our full support.
However, I would like to extend that attracting private investments of pharma industry in the EU would require at the same time, in parallel, energy cost reductions, decreasing of obligations linked to the medicines lifecycle and also less bureaucracy, which is exactly the opposite of which some of your colleagues, Mr Commissioner, are doing.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:55:45</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_147"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_201"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_202"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_160">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_160</del:identifier>
    <del:name>NicolГғВЎs GonzГғВЎlez Casares</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_363">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_363</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Paolo Inselvini</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_65">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_65</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Komission esittГғВӨmГғВӨt muutokset vesittГғВӨvГғВӨt esimerkiksi yritysvastuudirektiivin rajaamalla soveltamisalasta ulos pienemmГғВӨt alihankkijat sekГғВӨ heikentГғВӨmГғВӨllГғВӨ ihmisoikeusloukkausten uhrien asemaa. Jos huolellisuutta vaaditaan vain ensimmГғВӨisessГғВӨ tuotantoportaassa, kuten komissio nyt esittГғВӨГғВӨ, valvotaan esimerkiksi ananasmehun tuotannon ihmisoikeusvaikutuksia jatkossa vain Suomen Kuopiossa, ei Thaimaassa, mistГғВӨ alihankintaa tehdГғВӨГғВӨn.
TГғВӨllaisessa sГғВӨГғВӨntelyssГғВӨ ei ole mitГғВӨГғВӨn jГғВӨrkeГғВӨ, ja se myГғВ¶s tuhoaa tГғВӨmГғВӨn koko direktiivin alkuperГғВӨisen ajatuksen.</del:text>
    <del:text>Ich sage: Das ist der falsche Weg. Europa braucht dieses Geld fГғВјr neue und gute Jobs. Europa braucht dieses Geld fГғВјr soziale AktivitГғВӨten, fГғВјr SpitГғВӨler, fГғВјr den Bildungsbereich, fГғВјr Schulen, aber nicht, um aufzurГғВјsten. Und ins selbe Horn stГғВ¶ГғВҹt auch der Vorschlag, der jetzt aus Frankreich kommt, nГғВӨmlich den ganzen Kontinent mit Atomwaffen quasi zu ГғВјbersГғВӨen. Das ist der falsche Weg.
Wir haben zurzeit Verhandlungen in Saudi-Arabien mit der Trump-AdministrationГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ und jetzt kann man von Trump halten, was immer man mГғВ¶chte, aber es ist zumindest der Versuch, hier am Tisch Frieden herbeizufГғВјhren. Ich hГғВӨtte mir gewГғВјnscht, dass die EuropГғВӨische Union dort anknГғВјpft, wo sie 2012, glaube ich, schon einmal war, nГғВӨmlich eine Art Friedensnobelpreis erhalten zu haben, und sich jetzt hier in Kooperation und in einem Zusammenspiel mit dem Westen gemeinsam dafГғВјr ausspricht, das Sterben endlich zu beenden, endlich dafГғВјr Sorge zu tragen, dass es zu qualitativen Friedensverhandlungen kommt und dass wir in Zukunft wieder daran arbeiten kГғВ¶nnen, den Wohlstand auf diesem Kontinent voranzutreiben, und nicht zuzusehen, wie hier mehr und mehr Tote und Verletzte generiert werden.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:43:06</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:10:31</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_40"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_57"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_64"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_65"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_20">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_20</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Marie Toussaint,</del:name>
    <del:name>Petras GraГ…Вҫulis</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ESN"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_69">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_69</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Kiedy my tutaj debatujemy, w moim okrГ„Вҷgu, w Janikowie, w powiecie inowrocГ…ВӮawskim, koszt Zielonego Г…ВҒadu pГ…ВӮacГ„В… mieszkaГ…В„cy, samorzГ„В…d i pracownicy zakГ…ВӮadГғВіw chemicznych, ktГғВіre za chwilГ„Вҷ zostanГ„В… zamkniГ„Вҷte, a co za tym idzie caГ…ВӮy Г…ВӮaГ…В„cuszek przedsiГ„Вҷbiorstw zostanie zamkniГ„Вҷtych. Ludzie tracГ„В… pracГ„Вҷ, a caГ…ВӮy powiat wkrГғВіtce bГ„Вҷdzie powiatem widmem. Tak dziaГ…ВӮa Zielony Г…ВҒad.</del:text>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:51:12</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:16:23</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_44"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_59"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_68"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_69"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_146">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_146</del:identifier>
    <del:text>We must bolster Moldova's resilience now. This is about more than financial aid. It is about resilience, reforms and Moldova's EU path. Strengthening institutions, independent media and electoral integrity must be immediate, not gradual.
The first payout is set at 20ГӮВ %, but in this critical moment, that's not enough. We should amend the plan and increase it by an additional 5ГӮВ %. Moving faster and further sends a clear message: Moldova belongs in Europe, free from malign influence.</del:text>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T20:51:05</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:41:01</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_113"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_106"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_145"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_146"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_135">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_135</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Polska wspiera MoГ…ВӮdawiГ„Вҷ od momentu uzyskania przez niГ„В… niepodlegГ…ВӮoГ…Вӣci. Mam osobistГ„В… satysfakcjГ„Вҷ, Г…Вјe jako minister spraw wewnГ„Вҷtrznych mogГ…ВӮem uczestniczyГ„ВҮ w tej pomocy. W 2023 r. w obliczu prorosyjskich prГғВіb destabilizacji, prorosyjskich bojГғВіwek na ulicach Kiszyniowa przekazaliГ…Вӣmy moГ…ВӮdawskiemu MSW bardzo duГ…ВјГ„В… iloГ…ВӣГ„ВҮ sprzГ„Вҷtu policyjnego, w tym broГ…В„ i amunicjГ„Вҷ, aby MoГ…ВӮdawia byГ…ВӮa samowystarczalna w zakresie zapewnienia porzГ„В…dku publicznego. Dajmy szansГ„Вҷ MoГ…ВӮdawii uciec przed dyktaturГ„В… Putina. Jestem przekonany, Г…Вјe wsparcie finansowe, nad ktГғВіrym jutro bГ„Вҷdziemy gГ…ВӮosowaГ„ВҮ, dobrze siГ„Вҷ do tego przyczyni.</del:text>
    <del:text>Die ach so toleranten Mitstreiter im FEMM-Ausschuss beantragten ihre Ausladung, die dann auch prompt erfolgte. So ernst meinen es also unsere selbsternannten weiblichen VorkГғВӨmpfer mit der politischen Teilnahme und der gleichen ReprГғВӨsentation von Frauen. Nicht einmal in den eigenen weiblichen Reihen werden andere Meinungen toleriert. Reem AlsalemГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ merkt euch den Namen der echten KГғВӨmpferin fГғВјr Frauenrechte!</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T20:36:03</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:29:29</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_102"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_99"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_134"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_135"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_168">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_168</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Abuzul electoral, interzicerea unor cetГ„ВғГҲВӣeni de a candida ГҲВҷi ГғВ®mpiedicarea unei pГ„Вғturi importante a societГ„ВғГҲВӣii de a-ГҲВҷi exercita dreptul legitim de vot, par sГ„Вғ fi devenit noua regulГ„Вғ din RomГғВўnia.
Prin cenzura electoralГ„Вғ, autoritГ„ВғГҲВӣile romГғВўne au reuГҲВҷit performanГҲВӣa de a inflama populaГҲВӣia, creГғВўnd tensiune maximГ„Вғ ГғВ®ntr-o societate ГғВ®n care milioane de oameni se simt astГ„Вғzi neГғВ®ndreptГ„ВғГҲВӣiГҲВӣi ГҲВҷi neascultaГҲВӣi. Cum pot sГ„Вғ mai aibГ„Вғ romГғВўnii ГғВ®ncredere ГғВ®n democraГҲВӣie sau ГғВ®n justiГҲВӣie? Acest coГҲВҷmar trebuie sГ„Вғ ГғВ®nceteze. Trebuie sГ„Вғ revenim imediat la valorile democratice ГҲВҷi la libertate.</del:text>
    <del:text>Questo atto non puГғВІ essere giustificato: ГғВЁ un episodio di violenza gravissimo, che trascende la satira e diventa un pericolosissimo strumento di incitamento all'odio verso le donne.
Si cerca di attaccare una donna che, invece di essere un bersaglio di violenza, dovrebbe essere vista come un esempio di come la forza, il merito e l'ambizione possano permettere a chiunque di raggiungere i propri sogni.
Giorgia Meloni rappresenta milioni di donne italiane che credono nel proprio potenziale, nella propria indipendenza, nel diritto di aspirare a grandi traguardi senza essere fermate dalla discriminazione e dai pregiudizi.
E tutto questo avviene nel silenzio piГғВ№ assordante della sinistra e delle istituzioni. Sarebbe con questa violenza e intolleranza verso Giorgia Meloni che la sinistra intende difendere i diritti delle donne?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:23:28</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:08:03</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_114"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_120"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_167"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_168"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_176">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_176</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Par ailleurs, un projet dГўВҖВҷimplantation de parc industriel ГғВ©olien au large de Dunkerque est ГғВ  lГўВҖВҷГғВ©tude. Cette implantation, prГғВ©vue sur une surface de plus de 50ГӮВ kilomГғВЁtres carrГғВ©s, ne peut que se heurter ГғВ  cette question, qui devient dГғВЁs lors trГғВЁs urgente et particuliГғВЁrement dГғВ©licate. Il faut ГғВ©galement noter quГўВҖВҷune partie de la mer du Nord est classГғВ©e en zone NaturaГӮВ 2000. Il est donc primordial que ce problГғВЁme ne soit pas ignorГғВ©, ni par les ГғВүtats membres ni par notre institution. Il en va de la pГғВ©rennitГғВ© de notre ГғВ©cosystГғВЁme et de la bonne santГғВ© ГғВ©conomique de la moitiГғВ© nord de lГўВҖВҷEurope.</del:text>
    <del:text>Nonostante gli importanti passi avanti, permangono forti divari di genere, soprattutto nelle aree piГғВ№ svantaggiate, come la Sicilia, la Sardegna, il Sud Italia, dove purtroppo l'occupazione femminile ГғВЁ ancora troppo bassa anche a causa dell'insufficienza di servizi alla famiglia.
ГғВҲ necessario investire, investire in asili nido, in scuole per l'infanzia, in particolare dove la carenza di servizi ГғВЁ tuttora causa di forti diseguaglianze.
Dobbiamo sostenere le politiche di conciliazione tra vita privata e lavoro, incentivando i congedi parentali, le politiche di flessibilitГғВ  oraria, favorendo il lavoro delle donne, elemento essenziale per la crescita dell'intero sistema economico per una societГғВ  piГғВ№ giusta.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:34:13</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:20:16</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_127"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_128"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_175"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_176"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_37">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_37</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Je veux saluer la dГғВ©cision de la prГғВ©sidente du conseil rГғВ©gional de La RГғВ©union, HuguetteГӮВ Bello, dГўВҖВҷactiver le fonds Restore, que jГўВҖВҷai eu lГўВҖВҷhonneur de dГғВ©fendre ici, devant ce Parlement, en tant que rapporteur, et qui va permettre de mobiliser immГғВ©diatement 100ГӮВ millionsГӮВ dГўВҖВҷeuros: 100ГӮВ millionsГӮВ dГўВҖВҷeuros pour venir en aide aux familles qui ont perdu leur maison, rГғВ©parer les routes dГғВ©truites et pouvoir rГғВ©parer les infrastructures endommagГғВ©es. Je veux aussi saluer les modifications que nous avons apportГғВ©es au Feader, qui va permettre de venir immГғВ©diatement en aide aux agriculteurs en leur attribuant 40ГӮВ 000ГӮВ euros par exploitation agricole sinistrГғВ©e.
Pour conclure, Monsieur le PrГғВ©sident, je veux dire que ces catastrophes naturelles nous rappellent le devoir que nous avons de continuer ГғВ  agir contre le rГғВ©chauffement planГғВ©taire, et que nous devons placer les ГғВ®les particuliГғВЁrement fragiles au cГ…В“ur de la politique dГўВҖВҷadaptation au rГғВ©chauffement climatique. Je veux terminer en disant aux RГғВ©unionnaises et aux RГғВ©unionnais que je salue leur courage et leur rГғВ©silience. Ils se tiennent debout, et cГўВҖВҷest ainsi quГўВҖВҷils pourront se relever.</del:text>
    <del:text>SeГғВұoras y seГғВұores, el problema no es cuГғВЎnto se gasta, sino cГғВіmo se gasta. El dilema es que tenemos veintisiete sistemas defensivos diferentes sin una coordinaciГғВіn efectiva. Somos ineficientes y esto no lo resolveremos con una lluvia de millones en los presupuestos nacionales; aunque esta lluvia de millones tal vez sГғВӯ calme a Donald Trump y a la industria armamentГғВӯstica estadounidense.
Representantes de la ComisiГғВіn, analicen cГғВіmo podemos ser mГғВЎs eficientes, coordinen desde la UniГғВіn Europea la estrategia y la inversiГғВіn y hablemos sin tabГғВәs de cГғВіmo financiar este esfuerzo, por ejemplo con impuestos europeos propios, impuestos a los mГғВЎs ricos y a los que mГғВЎs contaminan, porque, de lo contrario, sabemos que serГғВЎ la ciudadanГғВӯa quien pagarГғВЎ esta factura. Y esta es una lГғВӯnea roja.
No podemos permitir que los presupuestos estatales o de la UniГғВіn Europea vean reducidas las partidas sociales y climГғВЎticas, porque hace quince aГғВұos en la UniГғВіn Europea se recortaron derechos sociales en nombre de la austeridad. Hoy no lo harГғВЎn en nombre de la guerra.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:46:18</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:30:36</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_21"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_31"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_36"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_37"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_318">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_318</del:identifier>
    <del:text>I will ask my colleagues to remember that you have the blue-card option very soon, so you have a chance to ask questions for your colleagues. And when you don't have the blue card, please let people speak quietly. Please, colleagues. Thank you.
So now we are here where I open up for the blue-card option. We always do that after the first round of speakers on behalf of the political groups. And we ended that.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:58:00</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_317"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_318"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_499">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_499</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Les violences de ces derniers jours, quГўВҖВҷexploitent sans honte les valets de BacharГӮВ el-Assad, y compris dans ce Parlement, alors quГўВҖВҷils ont couvert sans ciller un demi-million de morts, disent tout de lГўВҖВҷГғВ©tat dans lequel cinquanteГӮВ ans de dictature ont laissГғВ© la Syrie: dГғВ©chirГғВ©e par des tiraillements communautaires et en proie aux interventions ГғВ©trangГғВЁres les plus toxiques.
Que doit faire lГўВҖВҷEurope? Aider la population ГғВ©puisГғВ©e, qui sort dГўВҖВҷannГғВ©es de tГғВ©nГғВЁbres, sГўВҖВҷassurer que le pouvoir en place met ses actes en conformitГғВ© avec ses paroles, continuer de combattre Daech, qui reste une menace, et aider ГғВ  la stabilisation de la Syrie. Nous devrons ГғВӘtre dГўВҖВҷautant plus engagГғВ©s que les ГғВүtats-Unis risquent de se dГғВ©tourner de lГғВ  comme dГўВҖВҷailleurs. La stabilitГғВ© de la nouvelle Syrie est dans notre intГғВ©rГғВӘt et celui de la rГғВ©gion.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:59:05</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_229"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_498"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_499"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_476">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_476</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ci saremmo perГғВІ aspettati piГғВ№ ambizione, in particolare su ciГғВІ che puГғВІ essere fatto nel breve periodo: parlo in primo luogo del prezzo dell'energia. Per fare sГғВ¬ che i contratti di lungo termine diventino una prassi diffusa anche per le piccole imprese, servono strumenti di de-risking e di garanzia pubblica.
Non basta suggerire agli Stati membri di abbassare le tasse. Il punto ГғВЁ come si forma il prezzo dell'energia e come si trasferiscono agli utenti i benefici che derivano dalla diffusione delle rinnovabili.
Per questo occorre anticipare la valutazione di impatto sui mercati dell'energia a breve termine, anche perchГғВ© i competitor delle industrie europee, oltre che pagare meno l'energia, possono contare su enormi sussidi.
Sulla concorrenza sleale, su come fronteggiare l'overcapacity, le risposte del Clean Industrial Deal non ci sembrano ad oggi sufficienti.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:22:04</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_342"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_475"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_476"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_210">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_210</del:identifier>
    <del:text>I agree that in some Member States, medicine is more accessible than in others, and this is something we shouldn't accept. We should work together to have a European Union, a true European health Union, where every European citizen has equal access to medicines.
I'm really sure that we as a Parliament together can work on this commonly shared aim.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:07:03</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_153"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_209"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_210"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_282">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_282</del:identifier>
    <del:text>ГҺВӣГҸВҚГҸВғГҺВөГҺВ№ГҸВӮ ГҸВ…ГҸВҖГҺВ¬ГҸВҒГҸВҮГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВҪ. ГҺВ•ГҺВҪГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВҮГҸВҚГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҺВјГҺВө ГҺВәГҺВ¬ГҺВёГҺВө ГҺВјГҺВӯГҸВғГҺВҝ ГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҸВӮ ГҸВҮГҸВҺГҸВҒГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВ„ГҺВөГҺВ»ГҺВҝГҸВҚГҺВҪ ГҸВҖГҸВҒГҸВҺГҸВ„ГҺВ· ГҸВҖГҸВҚГҺВ»ГҺВ· ГҺВөГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВҢГҺВҙГҺВҝГҸВ…, ГҸВҢГҸВҖГҸВүГҸВӮ ГҺВ· ГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВ„ГҸВҒГҺВҜГҺВҙГҺВұ ГҺВјГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҺВ· ГҺВ•ГҺВ»ГҺВ»ГҺВ¬ГҺВҙГҺВұ, ГҺВұГҺВ»ГҺВ»ГҺВ¬ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВ· ГҺВҷГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВ»ГҺВҜГҺВұ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВ· ГҺВҷГҸВғГҸВҖГҺВұГҺВҪГҺВҜГҺВұ. ГҺВҢГҸВҖГҺВҝГҺВ№ГҺВҝГҺВ№ ГҺВөГҺВ№ГҸВғГҺВІГҺВ¬ГҺВ»ГҺВ»ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВҪ ГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВҒГҺВ¬ГҺВҪГҺВҝГҺВјГҺВұ ГҸВғГҺВө ГҺВөГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҸВүГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВҠГҺВәГҸВҢ ГҺВӯГҺВҙГҺВұГҸВҶГҺВҝГҸВӮ ГҺВҙГҺВөГҺВҪ ГҸВҖГҸВҒГҺВӯГҸВҖГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВҙГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ГҺВҝГҸВҚГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВҝГҸВҚГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҺВөГҸВҖГҺВҜГҺВҙГҺВҝГҺВјГҺВұ ГҺВҝГҸВҚГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҺВ¬ГҸВғГҸВ…ГҺВ»ГҺВҝ. ГҺВ ГҸВҒГҺВӯГҸВҖГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҸВғГҸВ…ГҺВ»ГҺВ»ГҺВұГҺВјГҺВІГҺВ¬ГҺВҪГҺВҝГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВ№, ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВ¬ГҸВғГҸВҮГҺВҝГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҺВәГҺВ№ГҺВҪГҺВ·ГҸВ„ГҺВ¬, ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВјГҺВөГҸВ„ГҺВұГҸВҶГҺВӯГҸВҒГҺВҝГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВғГҺВө ГҺВәГҺВ»ГҺВөГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВ¬ ГҺВәГҺВӯГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҸВҒГҺВұ, ГҸВғГҺВө ГҺВұГҺВәГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҺВҜГҺВәГҺВ·ГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҺВҪГҺВ·ГҸВғГҺВ№ГҺВ¬ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҸВҢ ГҺВөГҺВәГҺВөГҺВҜ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВөГҺВ»ГҺВұГҸВҚГҺВҪГҺВҝГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВ· ГҸВҮГҸВҺГҸВҒГҺВұ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВӮ ГҺВ® ГҺВјГҺВө ГҺВҙГҺВ№ГҺВұГҺВәГҸВҒГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВӯГҸВӮ ГҸВғГҸВ…ГҺВјГҸВҶГҸВүГҺВҪГҺВҜГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҸВғГҺВө ГҸВҮГҸВҺГҸВҒГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҺВөГҺВәГҸВ„ГҸВҢГҸВӮ ГҺВ•ГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҸВүГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВҠГҺВәГҺВ®ГҸВӮ ГҺВҲГҺВҪГҸВүГҸВғГҺВ·ГҸВӮ. ГҺВЈГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВјГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВ®ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҺВөГҸВҖГҺВ№ГҸВ„ГҺВӯГҺВ»ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВӮ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВөГҸВҖГҺВ№ГҸВҮГҺВҝГҸВҒГҺВ·ГҺВіГҺВөГҺВҜГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҸВ„ГҺВ· ГҺВҙГҺВ№ГҺВұГҺВјГҺВҝГҺВҪГҺВ® ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВөГҸВҖГҺВ№ГҸВҮГҺВҝГҸВҒГҺВ·ГҺВіГҺВ®ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВӯГҺВ»ГҺВұГҸВғГҺВ® ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВӮ. ГҺВҰГҺВ¬ГҸВҒГҺВҝГҸВӮ ГҺВјГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҸВҖГҸВҒГҺВӯГҸВҖГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВөГҺВҜГҺВҪГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВҝГҺВ№ ГҸВҖГҺВҝГҺВ»ГҺВ№ГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВӯГҸВӮ ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВҹГҸВ…ГҺВіГҺВіГҺВұГҸВҒГҺВҜГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВ ГҺВҝГҺВ»ГҸВүГҺВҪГҺВҜГҺВұГҸВӮ, ГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҸВӮ ГҺВҝГҸВҖГҺВҝГҺВҜГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҺВұГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВҜ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҸВ…ГҺВ№ГҺВҝГҺВёГҺВөГҸВ„ГҺВ®ГҸВғГҺВөГҸВ„ГҺВө, ГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҸВӮ ГҸВҖГҺВҝГҺВ»ГҺВөГҺВјГҺВ¬ГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҺВіГҺВ№ГҺВұ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВјГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВөГҺВҪГҺВұГҸВҮГҸВүГҸВҒГҺВ·ГҺВёГҺВөГҺВҜ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝ ГҺВҷГҸВғГҺВ»ГҺВ¬ГҺВј. ГҺВҢГҸВҖГҺВҝГҺВ№ГҺВҝГҸВӮ ГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВҒГҺВұГҺВІГҺВ№ГҺВ¬ГҺВ¶ГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҸВғГҸВҚГҺВҪГҺВҝГҸВҒГҺВұ ГҺВјГҺВ№ГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҸВҮГҸВҺГҸВҒГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҺВөГҺВҜГҺВҪГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВғГҺВұГҺВҪ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВҒГҺВұГҺВІГҺВ№ГҺВ¬ГҺВ¶ГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҸВҖГҸВҢГҸВҒГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҸВғГҸВҖГҺВ№ГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВҝГҸВҚ ГҺВјГҺВұГҸВӮ. ГҺВ— ГҺВ»ГҺВұГҺВёГҸВҒГҺВҝГҺВјГҺВөГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВҪГҺВ¬ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВөГҸВ…ГҸВғГҺВ· ГҺВөГҺВҜГҺВҪГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВҝ ГҺВәГҺВұГҸВҒГҺВәГҺВҜГҺВҪГҺВҝГҸВӮ ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВ•ГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҸВҺГҸВҖГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВөГҸВғГҺВөГҺВҜГҸВӮ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҺВҪ ГҺВұГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВјГҺВөГҸВ„ГҸВүГҸВҖГҺВҜГҺВ¶ГҺВөГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҺВјГҺВө ГҺВұГҸВғГҸВҖГҺВ№ГҸВҒГҺВҜГҺВҪГҺВөГҸВӮ. ГҺВһГҺВөГҺВәГҺВ№ГҺВҪГҺВ®ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВө, ГҺВ»ГҺВҝГҺВ№ГҸВҖГҸВҢГҺВҪ, ГҺВјГҺВұГҺВ¶ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВӯГҸВӮ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВөГҺВ»ГҺВ¬ГҸВғГҺВөГҺВ№ГҸВӮ ГҸВҮГҺВёГҺВөГҸВӮ. ГҺВ§ГҸВҒГҺВ®ГҺВјГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҸВ…ГҸВҖГҺВ¬ГҸВҒГҸВҮГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВҪ, ГҺВұГҺВөГҸВҒГҺВҝГҺВҙГҸВҒГҸВҢГҺВјГҺВ№ГҺВұ ГҸВ…ГҸВҖГҺВ¬ГҸВҒГҸВҮГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВҪ, ГҺВәГҺВӯГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҸВҒГҺВұ ГҺВәГҸВҒГҺВ¬ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВғГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҸВ…ГҸВҖГҺВ¬ГҸВҒГҸВҮГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВҪ. ГҺВЈГҸВ…ГҺВіГҺВәГҺВөГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҸВҒГҸВҺГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВӮ ГҸВғГҺВө ГҺВәГҺВӯГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҸВҒГҺВұ ГҺВәГҸВҒГҺВ¬ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВғГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВҙГҺВ№ГҸВҺГҺВҫГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВӮ ГҸВҖГҸВҒГҺВ№ГҺВҪ ГҸВҖГҺВөГҺВёГҺВ¬ГҺВҪГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВ· ГҺВ•ГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҸВҺГҸВҖГҺВ·. ГҺВҳГҺВӯГҺВ»ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВјГҺВө ГҸВҖГҺВҜГҸВғГҸВү ГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҸВӮ ГҸВҮГҸВҺГҸВҒГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҺВјГҺВұГҸВӮ, ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҸВ„ГҺВұГҸВ…ГҸВ„ГҸВҢГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВ„ГҺВ¬ ГҺВјГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҸВӮ ГҺВұГҺВҫГҺВҜГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҺВјГҺВұГҸВӮ. ГҺВҡГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВұГҺВҪ ГҺВөГҸВғГҺВөГҺВҜГҸВӮ ГҺВҝГҺВ№ ГҺВҙГҺВ®ГҺВёГҺВөГҺВҪ ГҺВөГҸВ…ГҺВұГҺВҜГҸВғГҺВёГҺВ·ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҺВ№ ГҸВғГҺВҝГҸВғГҺВ№ГҺВұГҺВ»ГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВӯГҸВӮ ГҸВҲГҺВ¬ГҸВҮГҺВҪГҺВөГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҺВіГҺВ№ГҺВұ ГҸВҒГҺВұГҸВ„ГҸВғГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВӯГҸВӮ, ГҺВәГҺВҝГҺВ№ГҸВ„ГҺВ¬ГҺВҫГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВёГҸВҒГҺВӯГҸВҶГҸВ„ГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҸВғГҺВұГҸВӮ. ГҺВ•ГҺВҜГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҺВҝГҺВ№ ГҺВјГҺВөГҺВіГҺВұГҺВ»ГҸВҚГҸВ„ГҺВөГҸВҒГҺВҝГҺВ№ ГҸВҒГҺВұГҸВ„ГҸВғГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВӯГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВ¬ ГҸВ„ГҸВүГҺВҪ ГҺВ•ГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҸВүГҸВҖГҺВұГҺВҜГҸВүГҺВҪ.
(ГҺВ— ГҺВұГҺВіГҺВҝГҸВҒГҺВ®ГҸВ„ГҸВҒГҺВ№ГҺВұ ГҺВҙГҺВӯГҸВҮГҺВөГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВұГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВ®ГҸВғГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҸВғГҺВө ГҺВөГҸВҒГҸВҺГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВғГҺВ· ГҺВјГҺВө ГҺВіГҺВұГҺВ»ГҺВ¬ГҺВ¶ГҺВ№ГҺВұ ГҺВәГҺВ¬ГҸВҒГҸВ„ГҺВұ)</del:text>
