  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_215">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_215</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Za druhГғВ©, vyzГғВҪvГғВЎm k odstranГ„ВӣnГғВӯ tГ„Вӣch regulacГғВӯ, kterГғВ© brГғВЎnГғВӯ obnovГ„Вӣ vГғВҪroby zГғВЎkladnГғВӯch lГғВ©Г„ВҚiv v EvropГ„Вӣ, jako tomu bГғВҪvalo, abychom se zГғВЎvislosti na dovozu postupnГ„Вӣ zbavili. Za tГ…ВҷetГғВӯ, lГғВ©Г„ВҚiva vnГғВӯmejme jako strategickou komoditu dГ…ВҜleГ…ВҫitГ„ВӣjГ…ВЎГғВӯ neГ…Вҫ zbranГ„Вӣ. Nedostatek antibiotik jsme mГ„Вӣli v roce 2023 a vГ…ВҜbec to nebylo pГ„ВӣknГғВ©. MГғВӯsto bilionГ…ВҜ na ReArm proto dejme radГ„Вӣji prostor rozvoji vlastnГғВӯ farmaceutickГғВ© vГғВҪroby.
A za Г„ВҚtvrtГғВ©, mnohГғВ© vГғВҪpadky jsou ve skuteГ„ВҚnosti dГ…ВҜsledek poruГ…ВЎenГғВӯ hospodГғВЎГ…ВҷskГғВ© soutГ„ВӣГ…Вҫe. Ty lГғВ©ky jsou, ale kvГ…ВҜli distribuГ„ВҚnГғВӯm monopolГ…ВҜm se nedostanou do menГ…ВЎГғВӯch lГғВ©kГғВЎren a k pacientГ…ВҜm. K potlaГ„ВҚenГғВӯ tohoto neГ…ВЎvaru uГ…Вҫ Komise dГғВЎvno pravomoci mГғВЎ, jenom je musГғВӯ zaГ„ВҚГғВӯt pouГ…ВҫГғВӯvat. Tak to dГ„Вӣlejme!</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:13:12</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_70"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_214"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_215"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_236">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_236</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Hannah Neumann</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Verts_ALE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_426">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_426</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Wir brauchen Energie. Wenn jemand Leistungen erbringen soll und die Transformation ist eine riesige Leistung, dann braucht er keine eng geschnallten GГғВјrtel, sondern Energie. Deswegen ist es so gut, dass die Kommission im Clean Industrial Deal gesagt hat: Wir brauchen mehr Strom, und wir brauchen gГғВјnstigeren Strom. Strom ist die Energie der Transformation, und Strom ist auch die Energie, die uns unabhГғВӨngig von Russland und anderen problematischen Lieferanten macht. Deswegen bitte mit massiver Kraft all diese Elemente umsetzen.
Wir brauchen Verfahrensbeschleunigung. Der Chef eines groГғВҹen Stahlwerks hat mir gesagt, er will dekarbonisieren, aber er braucht 50ГӮВ Genehmigungen von ganz vielen verschiedenen BehГғВ¶rden. Deswegen muss auch das, was Christian Ehler angefangen hat in der letzten Periode ГўВҖВ“ Net Zero Industrial Deal ГўВҖВ“, jetzt vollbracht werden, nicht nur fГғВјr Batterien, sondern auch fГғВјr Stahlwerke.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:16:02</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_304"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_425"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_426"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_24">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_24</del:identifier>
    <del:text>I was just wondering about that colleague that said the people elected this candidate. They didn't elect this candidate in a fair election; it was an election that was scammed by Russian propaganda and Russian bots and Russian influence. I know that you are fond of stuff like this, because it tends to help you as well in our elections.
But democracy also includes the free will of the people without manipulation, without foreign interference. That is the problem here. It is not that a fair election was taken away; it is that a scammed election was taken away. If the institutions ГўВҖВ“ the Constitutional Court, the board of elections ГўВҖВ“ decide like this, you have to respect it. You cannot just cry aloud because the candidate that you wanted to run was taken away.</del:text>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:22:15</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:12:50</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_12"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_19"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_23"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_24"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_48">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_48</del:identifier>
    <del:text>A zatГғВӯmco Komise poГ…ВҷГғВЎdГғВЎ tiskovГғВ© konference a chlubГғВӯ se novГғВҪmi plГғВЎny, naГ…ВЎe podniky kolabujГғВӯ. A co prГ…ВҜmysl? NГ„ВӣmeckГғВ© ocelГғВЎГ…ВҷstvГғВӯ, kdysi pГғВҪcha evropskГғВ©ho hospodГғВЎГ…ВҷstvГғВӯ, dnes kolabuje. A co Г„ВҚeskГғВ© firmy? Г„ВҢeskГғВ© automobilky, kterГғВ© zamГ„ВӣstnГғВЎvajГғВӯ tisГғВӯce lidГғВӯ, Г„ВҚelГғВӯ dalГ…ВЎГғВӯm a dalГ…ВЎГғВӯm regulacГғВӯm. Г„ВҢeskГғВ© strojГғВӯrenskГғВ© firmy bojujГғВӯ s nesmyslnou administrativou, kterГғВЎ je brzdГғВӯ ve vГғВҪrobГ„Вӣ a inovacГғВӯch. EvropГ„Вӣ nepomГ…ВҜГ…Вҫe kosmetickГғВЎ ГғВәprava byrokracie. Evropa nepotГ…Вҷebuje dalГ…ВЎГғВӯ papГғВӯrovГғВ© triky. PotГ…Вҷebuje reГғВЎlnГғВ© kroky, mГғВ©nГ„Вӣ regulacГғВӯ, vГғВӯce podpory pro podnikatele a mГғВ©nГ„Вӣ zasahovГғВЎnГғВӯ do Г…Вҫivota bГ„ВӣГ…ВҫnГғВҪch obГ„ВҚanГ…ВҜ a nГғВЎvrat zdravГғВ©ho rozumu do politiky.
EvropskГғВЎ komise dnes hrdГ„Вӣ hlГғВЎsГғВӯ: PodnikatelГғВ©, my vГғВЎs zachrГғВЎnГғВӯme! Jen zapomnГ„Вӣla dodat, Г…Вҫe jim pГ…ВҷiГ…ВЎroubovala k nohГғВЎm betonovГғВ© boty. PodnikatelГғВ© potГ…ВҷebujГғВӯ jasnГғВ© kroky a prГғВЎvnГғВӯ jistotu, a zejmГғВ©na u reportingu ESG je to vГғВӯce neГ…Вҫ dГ…ВҜleГ…ВҫitГғВ©. ProГ„ВҚ nehlasujeme o odloГ…ВҫenГғВӯ reportingu uГ…Вҫ na tГғВ©to schГ…ВҜzi? VГғВЎГ…ВҫenГғВӯ kolegovГғВ©, mГ„Вӣli bychom zaГ…Вҷadit v pГ…ВҷГғВӯpadГ„Вӣ sniГ…ВҫovГғВЎnГғВӯ byrokracie dvojku.</del:text>
    <del:text>E, portanto, quem tem de explicar ГғВ© o senhor deputado: porque ГғВ© que, hГғВЎ trГғВӘs anos, desde a invasГғВЈo da UcrГғВўnia pela RГғВәssia, defende sistematicamente uma polГғВӯtica de apaziguamento de tiranos como Vladimir Putin? Isso ГғВ© que o senhor deputado tem de explicar.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:07:10</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:46:28</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_26"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_39"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_47"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_48"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_145">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_145</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Tomislav Sokol,</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_97">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_97</del:identifier>
    <del:text>En France, nos artisans, nos agriculteurs et nos industriels sont submergГғВ©s par une avalanche de normes et de contraintes bureaucratiques. En cinq ans, 850ГӮВ nouvelles obligations europГғВ©ennes ont ГғВ©tГғВ© imposГғВ©es, reprГғВ©sentant prГғВЁs de 5ГӮВ 000ГӮВ pages de rГғВ©glementation supplГғВ©mentaires. RГғВ©sultat: des dГғВ©lais interminables pour obtenir un simple permis de construire, des dГғВ©marches absurdes pour accГғВ©der aux aides publiques et des TPE/PME pГғВ©nalisГғВ©es face aux grandes entreprises, qui, elles, disposent dГўВҖВҷune armГғВ©e de juristes pour naviguer dans ce labyrinthe administratif.
Un exemple frappant: nos agriculteurs croulent sous les exigences de la PAC, pendant que leurs concurrents extra-europГғВ©ens bГғВ©nГғВ©ficient de rГғВЁgles plus souples. Nos PME industrielles, notamment dans lГўВҖВҷautomobile, voient leur compГғВ©titivitГғВ© affaiblie par des surtranspositions absurdes.
Nous proposons une rГғВ©volution administrative, passant par une pause rГғВ©glementaire, la suppression des surtranspositions nationales et un droit de dГғВ©rogation pour les ГғВүtats membres. Il est temps de libГғВ©rer nos entreprises de cette asphyxie bureaucratique et de redonner ГғВ  nos ГғВ©conomies les moyens de croГғВ®tre et dГўВҖВҷinnover.</del:text>
    <del:text>The spirit of the consensus from the European Council ГўВҖВ“ unprecedented and unthinkable just a few weeks ago ГўВҖВ“ was felt, I would say, in most of the debate very strongly here as well, in this House of European democracy.
As many of you said, we have to think differently. Only in that way can we mobilise Europe's massive resources and start the deterrence build-up we need.
Many of you honourable Members were absolutely right to underscore that we cannot benefit from a peace dividend anymore. To the contrary, we must address the running security deficit. It's a huge task, and I would say that we must work on all levels ГўВҖВ“ European, national. We have to bring together our industry, our economic stakeholders.
As you heard from President von der Leyen, the first-ever Commissioner for Defence, MrГӮВ Kubilius, who also joined our debate this morning, together with the whole College of Commissioners, will be working day and night to achieve these goals.
We all realise that a powerful Europe means just and lasting peace in Ukraine, and a free and sovereign Ukraine means stronger Europe.
My colleague, Commissioner Kos, here with us today, has moved cooperation with Ukraine to a new level. She works tirelessly to support Ukraine in the path towards European membership. And I agree with her that we have to underline that we are living in historic times and therefore extraordinary challenges require extraordinary answers.
As we discussed the last time in this plenary, new geopolitics and transactional fragmentation of the world means that size matters again. Therefore, enlargement of the European family, enlargement of democracy and enlargement of respect for our values are the best answers for today's unstable world. The Commission will work hard to achieve these goals.
Let me conclude by the words of MrГӮВ Glucksmann, who said:
ГӮВ«CГўВҖВҷest lГўВҖВҷheure de la vГғВ©ritГғВ© pour lГўВҖВҷEuropeГӮВ» ГўВҖВ“ГӮВ et je suis tout ГғВ  fait dГўВҖВҷaccord avec lui.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:27:50</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:50:30</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_68"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_84"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_96"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_97"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_163">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_163</del:identifier>
    <del:text>GГ…ВӮosowanie odbГ„Вҷdzie siГ„Вҷ jutro, we wtorek 11 marca 2025 r.</del:text>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:18:45</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:03:15</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_117"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_162"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_163"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_123">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_123</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The Committee on Budgetary Control adopted with great unanimity a number of amendments that would have improved the transparency and the auditing of the facility. Most of them were not taken on board because the rapporteurs wanted to have a swift negotiation with the Council. I can understand that, but the challenge is still there to strengthen the auditing in Moldova and to make sure that taxpayers' money is used in the best possible way. I am sure that we will have many opportunities to come back to that debate on strengthening the national auditing system in Moldova.</del:text>
    <del:text>This is a decisive vote of this Parliament. This is about whether we are going to have a framework programme, an independent research framework programme, in the future or not. Whether it's squeezed into an absurd idea of an all-in-all competitiveness programme, which is squeezing together 35 years of independent research policies.
The committee had been clearly committing to that, and that's the second shot for the Commission today, because the Warsaw Declaration ГўВҖВ“ the unanimous declaration of all research ministers in Warsaw ГўВҖВ“ had been saying no to that endeavour.
We need an independent program. It has a mid-term, a long-term perspective. It must be open, it must be blue sky. It's not an instrument to have a seamless possibility to shift money from A to B. So vote for that and we will have a vivid discussion with the Commission on that.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T20:15:50</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:01:26</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_90"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_122"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_123"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_290">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_290</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Sama jsem patnГғВЎct let pracovala pГ…Вҷi navracenГғВӯ uprchlГғВӯkГ…ВҜ do zemГғВӯ pГ…ВҜvodu a vГғВӯm, Г…Вҫe musГғВӯme bГғВҪt v naГ…ВЎГғВӯ legislativГ„Вӣ nekompromisnГғВӯ a tvrdГғВӯ. NovГғВЎ pГ…ВҷГғВӯsnГ„ВӣjГ…ВЎГғВӯ politika nГғВЎvratГ…ВҜ byla nutnГғВЎ uГ…Вҫ lГғВ©ta. ZГғВЎkon o nГғВЎvratu musГғВӯ vyslat jasnГғВҪ vzkaz: NepГ…ВҷichГғВЎzejte do Evropy nelegГғВЎlnГ„Вӣ, protoГ…Вҫe budete vrГғВЎceni zpГ„Вӣt. V novГғВ©m nГғВЎvrhu o nГғВЎvratech chybГғВӯ povinnГғВҪ tlak na tГ…ВҷetГғВӯ zemГ„Вӣ. EvropskГғВЎ unie musГғВӯ vyuГ…ВҫГғВӯt svГ…ВҜj vliv, aby donutila zemГ„Вӣ pГ…ВҷijГғВӯmat zpГ„Вӣt svГғВ© obГ„ВҚany, obchodnГғВӯ sankce, vГғВӯza nebo konec finanГ„ВҚnГғВӯ pomoci. PГ…ВҷijmГ„Вӣte zpГ„Вӣt svГғВ© obГ„ВҚany, jinak...
(PГ…ВҷedsedajГғВӯcГғВӯ Г…ВҷeГ„ВҚnici odebrala slovo.)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:09:39</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_213"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_289"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_290"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_455">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_455</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Europa ha pasado de marcar el rumbo a quedarse atrГғВЎs: antes nos imitaban, ahora nos superan. Mientras discutimos normativas, el liderazgo industrial y tecnolГғВіgico se nos escapa de las manos. El Pacto por una Industria Limpia es una oportunidad, pero solo si actuamos con inteligencia: menos trabas, mГғВЎs inversiГғВіn, energГғВӯa asequible, industria fuerte.
No podemos permitir que la descarbonizaciГғВіn sea un freno en lugar de un impulso. Europa siempre ha sabido reinventarse. Es el momento de recuperar el liderazgo, de marcar el camino y de construir un futuro prГғВіspero.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:54:35</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_325"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_454"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_455"/>
  </rdf:Description>
