  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_40">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_40</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:text>A takisto by ma zaujГғВӯmalo, Г…Вҫe kto by mal s tГғВҪmi vГ…ВЎetkГғВҪmi nakГғВәpenГғВҪmi zbraГ…ВҲami ГғВӯsГ…ВҘ bojovaГ…ВҘ, pretoГ…Вҫe pre EurГғВіpanov to bude znamenaГ…ВҘ len Г„ВҸalГ…ВЎiu militarizГғВЎciu, Г„ВҸalГ…ВЎie zadlГ…Вҫovanie, Г„ВҸalГ…ВЎiu konsolidГғВЎciu a Г„ВҸalГ…ВЎie zdraГ…Вҫovanie. MrzГғВӯ ma, Г…Вҫe jedinГғВҪ, kto sa na samite postavil proti tomuto vojnovГғВ©mu plГғВЎnu Leyenovej, bol opГғВӨГ…ВҘ iba maГ„ВҸarskГғВҪ premiГғВ©r Viktor OrbГғВЎn, Г…Вҫe vГ…ВЎetci ostatnГғВӯ ГўВҖВ“ Macron, Scholz, Fiala, Fico a Г„ВҸalГ…ВЎГғВӯ ГўВҖВ“ hlasovali za Leyenovej navГғВҪГ…ВЎenie eurГғВіpskej vojenskej a finanГ„ВҚnej pomoci pre ZelenskГғВ©ho namiesto toho, aby sa pridali k tomu Trumpovmu plГғВЎnu a zatlaГ„ВҚili na ZelenskГғВ©ho a dotlaГ„ВҚili ho k mierovГғВҪm rokovaniam. Zradili a sklamali tГғВҪmto mnohГғВҪch voliГ„ВҚov.
Ja viem garantovaГ…ВҘ, Г…Вҫe my v hlasovanГғВӯ Leyenovej vojenskГғВҪ plГғВЎn nepodporГғВӯme a naГ…ВЎich voliГ„ВҚov nezradГғВӯme.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:53:21</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:34:16</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_14"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_33"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_39"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_40"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_535">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_535</del:identifier>
    <del:text>La UniГғВіn Europea debe impulsar las fases dos y tres del alto el fuego o solo quedarГғВЎn dos escenarios posibles: una nueva guerra o el plan del resort de Trump.
Existe una estrategia silenciosa de ocupaciГғВіn por parte de Israel que se ha apropiado el 16ГӮВ % de las tierras agrГғВӯcolas de Gaza, al igual que en Cisjordania y JerusalГғВ©n, donde la expansiГғВіn de asentamientos ilegales israelГғВӯes, la confiscaciГғВіn de tierras y el desplazamiento forzoso se han intensificado. Los puestos fronterizos han aumentado un 228ГӮВ % y se estГғВЎn eliminando barrios enteros. Los palestinos no tienen la culpa del terrorismo de HamГғВЎs,ГӮВ que hay que combatir con firmeza. La ocupaciГғВіn se consolida en prime time.
Mientras tanto, el Gobierno de extrema derecha israelГғВӯ prohГғВӯbe que el OOPS proporcione ayuda a mГғВЎs de 500ГӮВ 000ГӮВ refugiados y asfixia, con un 80ГӮВ % de impuestos sobre la financiaciГғВіn extranjera, a las ONG que no comulgan con dicho Gobierno, silenciando a los ciudadanos israelГғВӯes demГғВіcratas. Debemos seguir hablando de paz en Gaza, de los dos Estados y, sobre todo, del cumplimiento del Derecho internacional.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:54:09</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_372"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_534"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_535"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_200">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_200</del:identifier>
    <del:text>NaГ…Вҫalost, Europska unija sve viГ…ВЎe postaje ovisna o uvozu lijekova iz treГ„ВҮih drГ…Вҫava, a upravo je nedavna pandemija najbolje pokazala koliko smo ranjivi kad je u pitanju nestaГ…ВЎica lijekova i medicinske opreme.
Ovakva situacija dodatno je pogorГ…ВЎana zbog geopolitiГ„ВҚkih okolnosti u kojima se nalazimo. BuduГ„ВҮi da je doГ…ВЎlo vrijeme brutalne sile u meГ„В‘unarodnim odnosima te se svatko treba pobrinuti, koliko god je to moguГ„ВҮe, za vlastite interese.
Krajnje je vrijeme da preuzmemo stvari u svoje ruke, a ovim prijedlogom zakona o kritiГ„ВҚnim lijekovima Г„ВҚinimo korak u pravom smjeru. Zato pozdravljam mehanizme, posebno financijske potpore i ubrzavanje administrativnih procedura za strateГ…ВЎke projekte kojima olakГ…ВЎavamo gradnju tvornica lijekova na europskom tlu.
TakoГ„В‘er, podrГ…Вҫavam zajedniГ„ВҚku nabavu kritiГ„ВҚnih lijekova, Г…ВЎto je posebno vaГ…Вҫno za manje drГ…Вҫave poput moje Republike Hrvatske jer time jaГ„ВҚamo njihovu pregovaraГ„ВҚku moГ„ВҮ i osiguravamo bolje uvjete nabave.
Pri tome izuzetno je vaГ…Вҫno uvoГ„В‘enje dodatnih kriterija odabira u javnoj nabavi lijekova osim cijene, poput sigurnosti opskrbe i proizvodnje na europskom teritoriju, Г…ВЎto Г„ВҮe svakako olakГ…ВЎati dostupnost kritiГ„ВҚnih lijekova za naГ…ВЎe graГ„В‘ane i smanjiti ovisnost o pojedinim dobavljaГ„ВҚima izvan EU-a.
Jedna od stvari koje, meГ„В‘utim, nisu toliko naglaГ…ВЎene je stvaranje zaliha kritiГ„ВҚnih lijekova. Ne smije se nikada viГ…ВЎe dogoditi da pojedine velike drГ…Вҫave Г„ВҚlanice u zdravstvenoj krizi zadrГ…Вҫavaju kljuГ„ВҚne medicinske potrepГ…ВЎtine i time doprinose produbljivanju krize umjesto njenom rjeГ…ВЎavanju. Zato nam treba jaГ„ВҚanje zajedniГ„ВҚkih europskih zaliha i koordinacija na razini EU-a kako bi lijekovi i druge medicinske potrepГ…ВЎtine u sluГ„ВҚaju nestaГ…ВЎice stigli upravo onima koji ih najviГ…ВЎe trebaju.
Sve u svemu, pozdravljam ovaj prijedlog jer on doprinosi ekonomskoj sigurnosti EU-a smanjenjem ovisnosti o stranim dobavljaГ„ВҚima i osiguravanju stabilne opskrbe. Osim toga, njime Г„ВҮe se poveГ„ВҮati konkurentnost EU-a na globalnom farmaceutskom trГ…ВҫiГ…ВЎtu, privuГ„ВҮi ulaganja u istraГ…Вҫivanje i inovacije te stvoriti nova radna mjesta.
Vrijeme je da interes Europske unije i naГ…ВЎih pacijenata doista postane prioritet i drago mi je da sada idemo u pravom smjeru.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:51:52</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_145"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_199"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_200"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_43">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_43</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Dear colleagues, we will start the debate on the Commission statement without the Commission present. I have to say this is really appalling. This is not really a time for us to sit and relax, and I think it is going to be made quite clear to the Commission that it is unacceptable not to have a Commissioner here for this actually really important debate.
Г„ВҺalГ…ВЎГғВӯm bodom programu je vyhlГғВЎsenie Komisie o zniГ…ВҫovanГғВӯ byrokracie a zjednoduГ…ВЎovanГғВӯ podnikania v EГғВҡ: prvГғВ© sГғВәhrnnГғВ© nГғВЎvrhy.</del:text>
    <del:text>I commend the Member States for their clear understanding that Ukraine and Europe's future requires peace through strength ГўВҖВ“ strength for Ukraine to stand up against Putin and against Trump. The US is forcing Ukraine into an unacceptable surrender it could also achieve without their help. If the circumstances are unfavourable for Ukraine, for Europe, we will not accept it. We have to change these circumstances towards a just peace, or accept the ugly consequences.
Now President vonГӮВ derГӮВ Leyen said that the Parliament was right, asking for more military support all along. Translate understanding then into real united action now, and for all the Member States, President Costa ГўВҖВ“ some a bit more than others ГўВҖВ“ that means sending Ukraine the weapons it needs now. It's irritating ГўВҖВ“ it's appalling even ГўВҖВ“ that there are still warehouses where there's critical air defence that Ukraine needs now. Do what is necessary now for Ukraine, for Europe.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:59:10</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:38:39</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_36"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_42"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_43"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_364">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_364</del:identifier>
    <del:text>So Europe has to grow up and be strong ГўВҖВ“ both economically and militarily ГўВҖВ“ so that we can take care of our own independently, hopefully with good cooperation with the United States some time after Trump's term. But if not, we still have to be able to do it independently. We have people, we have money, we have innovation. We can do it.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:59:33</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_261"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_363"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_364"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_127">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_127</del:identifier>
    <del:text>SoluГҲВӣia la problemele de securitate, economice, sociale ГҲВҷi politice din Republica Moldova ar fi unirea celor douГ„Вғ state. PlГ„Вғcile tectonice ale istoriei se miГҲВҷcГ„Вғ ГғВ®n acest moment ГўВҖВ“ cu sprijinul Uniunii Europene, visul romГғВўnilor de o parte ГҲВҷi de alta a Prutului s-ar putea ГғВ®ndeplini.
ГҲВҳtim foarte bine ГғВ®nsГ„Вғ cГ„Вғ stilul Bruxelles-ului ГҲВҷi al Strasbourg-ului este trasul de timp, ГғВ®n speranГҲВӣa cГ„Вғ problemele se vor rezolva de la sine. FГ„ВғrГ„Вғ susГҲВӣinere adecvatГ„Вғ, fГ„ВғrГ„Вғ o diversificare a opГҲВӣiunilor politice pro-europene ГҲВҷi pro-romГғВўneГҲВҷti de la ChiГҲВҷinГ„Вғu, pot exista surprize neplГ„Вғcute la alegerile parlamentare. Inclusiv unioniГҲВҷtii trebuie sprijiniГҲВӣi.
Revenind la mecanismul pe care vreГҲВӣi sГ„Вғ-l instituiГҲВӣi, AUR considerГ„Вғ cГ„Вғ orice sprijin pentru fraГҲВӣii basarabeni este de bun augur. Dar vreau sГ„Вғ fac trei observaГҲВӣii:
- ГғВ®n primul rГғВўnd, moldovenii vor vedea cГ„Вғ din acea sumГ„Вғ totalГ„Вғ de 1,9 miliarde de euro, doar 520 de milioane de euro sunt granturi, restul fiind ГғВ®mprumuturi condiГҲВӣionate. Raportul dintre banii nerambursabili ГҲВҷi credite trebuia sГ„Вғ fie invers;
- ГғВ®n al doilea rГғВўnd, reformele cerute ГғВ®n Republica Moldova vor fi ГғВ®ntoarse de pro-ruГҲВҷi ГғВ®mpotriva actualei administraГҲВӣii ГҲВҷi folosite ГғВ®n alegerile parlamentare. A se vedea ГҲВҷi blocajul PNRR din RomГғВўnia, condiГҲВӣionat tot de reforme care nu s-au realizat. CereГҲВӣi mai mult decГғВўt poate duce un guvern de la ChiГҲВҷinГ„Вғu aflat sub asediu necontenit;
- ГҲВҷi nu ГғВ®n ultimul rГғВўnd, dacГ„Вғ vreГҲВӣi sГ„Вғ rezolvaГҲВӣi problema energeticГ„Вғ a Republicii Moldova, trebuie revizuitГ„Вғ situaГҲВӣia pieГҲВӣei unice europene. RomГғВўnia, care este autosuficientГ„Вғ pe gaze ГҲВҷi electricitate, a ajuns sГ„Вғ plГ„ВғteascГ„Вғ cele mai mari facturi din Uniunea EuropeanГ„Вғ. Acest lucru este relevant pentru cГ„Вғ Republica Moldova a scГ„Вғpat de dependenГҲВӣa de Rusia, importГғВўnd toate gazele ГҲВҷi tot curentul din RomГғВўnia. Noi producem ГҲВҷi importГ„Вғm ГғВ®n acest moment pentru douГ„Вғ state.</del:text>
    <del:text>At the current rate, it will take until 2158, another 134 years, to reach full gender parity at global level, according to data provided by the World Economic Forum. Within the European Union, it will take us more than 60 years. That is why the theme for this year's International Women's Day is 'accelerate action'. We need to take swift and decisive steps to achieve gender equality. We need to address the barriers and biases women face in every aspect of their lives.
Equality between women and men is one of the foundational values of our Union and a strategic interest in all our policies. In the European Union, we have made historic progress with rules on pay transparency, work-life balance, gender balance on company boards and combating violence against women. But we know there is still lots and lots more to do.
This is a special year. We are celebrating the 30th anniversary of the Beijing Platform for Action. CommissionerГӮВ Lahbib is now in New York leading the EU's delegation to the 69th session of the Commission on the Status of Women. She will pass on a clear message: enabling women's full and equal participation in all parts of society is key to achieve the Sustainable Development Goals.
On this International Women's Day, we show that we are serious about accelerating action with a new roadmap for women's rights. The roadmap sets out a long-term political vision to advance women's rights.
Our priorities are strategic. We have to think that 1 in 3 women has suffered violence in their lifetime and that is why we aim to eradicate all forms of violence against women and girls, including femicide, domestic violence, including coercive control, cyber violence, sexual harassment or exploitation. Every girl, every woman in Europe has the right and should feel safe.
Women's health. It has been under researched and under prioritised. That is why we propose a dedicated focus on women's health in full respect of Member States' competences in this field. That includes promoting gender-sensitive medical research, clinical trials, diagnostics and treatments, and it includes ensuring women's access to sexual and reproductive health and rights.
Employment and pay gaps. There is still much work to do there as well. We need to eliminate gender pay and pension gaps to promote equal employment and financial opportunities for women. Women in Europe should be economically independent and enjoy the same opportunities men do.
Our education should be free from discrimination, from sexism, from stereotypes and violence to encourage both girls and boys to seek the future that they want, because women should be at every table where decisions are made.
This is another objective of the roadmap: equal political participation and representation at all levels of political power. Gender balance at all levels of management, so that women's voices can be heard across the public and private sectors and shape the policies of tomorrow.
And we aim at better safety of women in public life, as they are more likely to be victims of hate speech than their male counterparts.
We also need strong institutional mechanisms that deliver on women's rights. This, among others, includes an effective gender mainstreaming approach. The gender mainstreaming principle that was adopted 30 years ago in the Beijing Platform for Action means that all policy areas should apply a gender perspective.
Striving for gender equality is not only the right thing to do, but it is also the smart thing to do. Gender equality is essential for building strong competitive economies, but also for building sustainable, democratic and inclusive societies.
I invite the European Parliament, the Council and other institutions and stakeholders to unite around this roadmap to put forward actions under their remit and make it so that we turn these principles into an enduring reality for every girl and every woman across our European Union.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T20:22:38</del:timestamp>
