  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_314">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_314</del:identifier>
    <del:text>CГўВҖВҷest peu, car cela repose presque exclusivement sur une dГғВ©marche volontaire des ГғВүtats membres. Or, si beaucoup ont dГғВ©jГғВ  augmentГғВ© leurs dГғВ©penses de dГғВ©fense, certains restent obstinГғВ©ment ГғВ  la traГғВ®ne. CГўВҖВҷest peu, car rien ne dit que lГўВҖВҷon rГғВ©soudra nos principales faiblesses, celles qui rГғВ©sultent de la fragmentation de nos industries de dГғВ©fense et celles qui sont le fruit dГўВҖВҷun paradoxe toxique: nos industries exportent en prioritГғВ© hors de lГўВҖВҷUnion europГғВ©enne, et la plupart de nos ГғВүtats achГғВЁtent essentiellement hors dГўВҖВҷEurope. Nous ne pouvons plus nous le permettre et nous devons absolument assumer une prГғВ©fГғВ©rence europГғВ©enne marquГғВ©e ГўВҖВ“ГӮВ enfin!
Le plan dГўВҖВҷUrsulaГӮВ vonГӮВ derГӮВ Leyen arrive aprГғВЁs des dГғВ©cennies dГўВҖВҷindolence. Surtout, il ne dit pas clairement comment nous allons massivement aider lГўВҖВҷUkraine; massivement, parce que notre sГғВ©curitГғВ© en dГғВ©pend; massivement, parce que nous sommes de plus en plus seuls ГғВ  le faire. Saluons donc le Conseil de jeudi dernier, mais soyons lucides: ce nГўВҖВҷest quГўВҖВҷune premiГғВЁre ГғВ©tape. DГғВ©fendre les EuropГғВ©ens est une ardente obligation, qui va nГғВ©cessiter des efforts et, parfois, des sacrifices. PrГғВ©server la paix en Europe est ГғВ  ce prix.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:50:13</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_229"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_313"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_314"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_480">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_480</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Cette annГғВ©e, les travailleurs de lГўВҖВҷacier et de lГўВҖВҷautomobile annoncent 300ГӮВ 000ГӮВ licenciements. Une entreprise ne devrait pas pouvoir distribuer des dividendes record une annГғВ©e et licencier lГўВҖВҷannГғВ©e suivante. En France, on appelle cela la privatisation des profits et la collectivisation des pertes, ce qui crГғВ©e un immense sentiment dГўВҖВҷinjustice et entraГғВ®ne la montГғВ©e des populismes. Il faudrait dГғВ©sormais conditionner le soutien ГғВ  lГўВҖВҷГғВ©conomie et aux entreprises ГғВ  la participation des salariГғВ©s et des pouvoirs publics ГғВ  leur gouvernance. CГўВҖВҷest lГғВ  la vraie nouvelle donne.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:27:01</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_344"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_479"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_480"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_187">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_187</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Fabienne Keller</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Renew"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_288">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_288</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Doch auch RГғВјckkehrzentren, die schon bald ГғВјberfГғВјllt sein werden, bringen nichts, solange es keine RГғВјckfГғВјhrungsabkommen oder Abkommen mit Drittstaaten gibt, an denen Sie seit Jahren fulminant scheitern. Wie wollen Sie die auch abschlieГғВҹen, wenn Sie offensichtlich noch immer nicht dazu bereit sind, finanziellen Druck auszuГғВјben? Davon ist natГғВјrlich noch immer keine Rede. Das Einzige, was sinnvoll wГғВӨre, wГғВӨren nicht nur RГғВјckkehrzentren, sondern auch VerfahrensГўВҖВ‘ und Asylzentren, und zwar nicht in der EU, sondern auГғВҹerhalb.
Was wurde alles groГғВҹartig geredet, versprochen und angekГғВјndigt. Und wieder einmal beweist die EU nach dem zahnlosen AsylГўВҖВ‘ und Migrationspaket ihren mangelnden Willen und ihre UnfГғВӨhigkeit, tatsГғВӨchlich fГғВјr die notwendige Trendwende hier zu sorgen.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:07:09</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_211"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_287"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_288"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_77">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_77</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Nina Carberry</del:name>
    <del:name>ГҺВ“ГҺВөГҺВ¬ГҺВҙГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВ“ГҺВөГҺВ¬ГҺВҙГҺВ·</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_46">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_46</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Growth, not bureaucracy, will drive our economy forward and power the green transition. To deliver, we need two key things. First, clarity and breathing room for our European companies. The 'stop-the-clock' proposal must enter into force as soon as possible. That is why EPP is calling for a faster approach under an urgent procedure.
Second, we have to deliver on content. We can do more to simplify this legislation and the EPP will push for further measures in the upcoming negotiations. We can, and we also call on all constructive forces of this House to join us in this.
Europeans expect us to protect their jobs and improve their lives. The EPP is ready to lead and try to unlock the potential of our economy. This is also what is best for climate and for sustainability. I would argue that a growing European economy is the best climate policy that we could have. On our continent, we have the highest standard and also the most ambitious climate policy in the world. Taking down European economy is counter-productive.
So the big debate here now, and especially I'm turning to my friends and colleagues on the Left, now the question is: will you stand for growth and jobs or red tape and bureaucracy? Europe cannot afford to wait. It is time to act.</del:text>
    <del:text>No dia 13 de fevereiro, ГғВәltimo dia desse plenГғВЎrio, o secretГғВЎrio da Defesa americano, Pete Hegseth, disse a seguinte frase: ГӮВ«Os Estados Unidos jГғВЎ nГғВЈo estГғВЈo disponГғВӯveis para garantir a seguranГғВ§a da EuropaГӮВ». Clarinho como ГғВЎgua. Como disse a presidente da ComissГғВЈo hГғВЎ pouco, o tempo da ilusГғВЈo acabou.
E, por isso, fez bem o Conselho Europeu, o Conselho da passada quinta-feira, em flexibilizar as regras do Pacto de Estabilidade e Crescimento, em criar uma nova linha de financiamento e atГғВ© em alterar o mandato do Banco Europeu de Investimento para permitir crГғВ©ditos em projetos na ГғВЎrea da defesa, o que, aliГғВЎs, mostra bem a forma adormecida como esta instituiГғВ§ГғВЈo europeia estava a olhar para a indГғВәstria da defesa.
Portanto, o Conselho fez bem. Fez bem, mas nГғВЈo chega. Porque ГғВ© urgente definir uma arquitetura de defesa europeia, porque, sem isso, o plano industrial que ГғВ© longamente falado continuarГғВЎ vago, as compras conjuntas continuarГғВЈo descoordenadas e a defesa da Europa continuarГғВЎ dependente de outros, inclusivamente na sua componente nuclear.
Portanto, o fim do tempo da ilusГғВЈo exige estas respostas rГғВЎpidas e decididas, mas jГғВЎ sabemos que a velocidade tem riscos ГўВҖВ” e vale a pena, hoje, falar aqui destes riscos.ГӮВ O risco de, sistematicamente, se ultrapassar e passar ao lado do Parlamento Europeu; o risco de a ComissГғВЈo e a sua presidente passarem a ser essencialmente uma figura decorativa face a iniciativas polГғВӯticas de Macron, Starmer, Merz ou, quem sabe, outros; e o risco de destruir a NATO, para a qual ninguГғВ©m tem hoje uma alternativa credГғВӯvel.
Portanto, ГғВ© esse,ГӮВ Senhores Deputados, o nosso desafio: salvar a Europa ГўВҖВ” a comeГғВ§ar pela UcrГғВўnia, que tanto merece a nossa ajuda ГўВҖВ”, sem destruir as suas instituiГғВ§ГғВөes. E ГғВ© nossa responsabilidade estar ГғВ  altura deste desafio.
(O orador aceita responder a uma pergunta ГӮВ«cartГғВЈo azulГӮВ»)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:01:29</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:43:11</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_24"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_39"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_45"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_46"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_81">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_81</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Maria Grapini</del:name>
    <del:name>Lukas Sieper</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_NI"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_66">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_66</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Este paquete supone un paso en la direcciГғВіn correcta, pero aГғВәn hay margen de mejora. La reducciГғВіn de cargas administrativas debe ir mГғВЎs lejos para que las empresas europeas puedan crecer sin obstГғВЎculos regulatorios innecesarios. Un ejemplo claro son las obligaciones impuestas por la Directiva sobre informaciГғВіn corporativa en materia de sostenibilidad que impone a muchas empresas la redacciГғВіn de informes de sostenibilidad, incluso cuando ya forman parte de grupos empresariales que presentan estos datos de una manera consolidada.
Con el paquete ГғВіmnibus se han introducido cambios que eliminan redundancias, pero las empresas europeas siguen dedicando muchos recursos a cumplir con exigencias burocrГғВЎticas en vez de centrarse en su negocio. La autonomГғВӯa estratГғВ©gica de la que tanto hablamos no serГғВЎ posible si no facilitamos las cosas a quienes producen, innovan y crean riqueza en Europa. Debemos competir en igualdad de condiciones con otras regiones del mundo. Seguimos trabajando para que este paquete sea aГғВәn mГғВЎs ambicioso en la eliminaciГғВіn de cargas administrativas.</del:text>
    <del:text>EU Member States must urgently invest in their own security, as Poland did under Law and Justice leadership.
Recent events have shown that without the United States, Europe is unfortunately nearly defenceless. Regardless of political turbulence or disagreements, we must maintain strong and reliable transatlantic relations. Our security depends on it. And here, from this very place, I once again urge the Prime Minister of Poland to stop blocking President Duda's proposal to convene an EUГўВҖВ‘US summit in Warsaw under the Polish Presidency. Failing to hold it will only deepen the cracks in our relations with our most important ally. We cannot afford such missteps at a time when security challenges are multiplying across Europe and beyond.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:44:43</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:12:28</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_41"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_58"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_65"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_66"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_86">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_86</del:identifier>
    <del:text>KommissionsprГғВӨsidentin von der Leyen hat versprochen, an den Zielen der Gesetze festzuhalten, aber die Anwendung praktikabler zu machen. Klingt gut, stimmt aber nicht. Wenn man pauschal 90ГӮВ % der Unternehmen weitestgehend vom Anwendungsbereich von zentralen Gesetzen ausnehmen will, dann legt man die Axt ans Gesetz. Statt die Gesetze unbrauchbar zu machen, mГғВјssen wir darГғВјber reden, wie wir sie besser umsetzen kГғВ¶nnen. Dazu gehГғВ¶ren beispielsweise ГғВңbergangsplГғВӨne statt pauschale Ausnahmen. Dazu gehГғВ¶rt auch, ja, eine stГғВӨrkere Unterscheidung zwischen groГғВҹen Konzernen und kleinen Handwerksbetrieben.
Aber das, was jetzt vorliegt, schieГғВҹt deutlich ГғВјber das Ziel hinaus. Deshalb bleiben wir GrГғВјne sehr skeptisch und hoffen, dass im Gesetzgebungsprozess noch ГғВ„nderungen gemacht werden kГғВ¶nnen.</del:text>
    <del:text>I also believe that this House will support an even more ambitious position. It goes without saying that the transatlantic disruption caused by the new US administration has brought us long-term geopolitical changes. We must not base European security on voter attitudes in US swing states. The EU needs to plan de-risking policy towards Trump's Washington. This is not America that wants its allies to respect it. This is an America that wants its allies to fear it.
Europe must make some historical and responsible steps ahead. Bold leadership and adequate funds are needed, including through seizing EUR 200 billion of Russian assets. I always repeat that our security does not stop at our borders. That's why we have to act fast and to act now. Time is of the essence.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:13:55</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:36:42</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_59"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_74"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_85"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_86"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_70">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_70</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Dus daarom deze vraag: kan de Commissie zich standaard committeren aan het "think small (business) first"-principe in de Europese wetgeving? Daarnaast ben ik geen voorstander van dubbele afspraken, zoals de CSRD en de CSDDD. Daarnaast bestaan de OESO-richtlijnen al jaren, inclusief een handhavingsinstrument via nationale contactpunten.
Wat denkt de Commissie ervan om bestaande internationale afspraken, zoals de OESO-richtlijnen, te hanteren als uitgangspunt? Het Omnibus-voorstel is een goede eerste stap, maar er is nog veel werk aan de winkel. Minder rapportages zijn nodig, want het gaat uiteindelijk om vertrouwen in de ondernemers, om innovatie en concurrentiekracht.</del:text>
    <del:text>SeГғВұorГғВӯas, ГӮВҝguerra o paz? La UniГғВіn estГғВЎ en una disyuntiva impensable hace unos aГғВұos, especialmente para quienes no hemos vivido la guerra. Crece la inquietud en nuestras sociedades, especialmente entre los jГғВіvenes. Tenemos que hacer partГғВӯcipe a la ciudadanГғВӯa, con transparencia y pedagogГғВӯa, de los cambios que exige la nueva realidad geopolГғВӯtica. No podemos dejar el relato en manos de la extrema derecha, que aprovecharГғВЎ para seguir destruyendo la esencia de la UniГғВіn Europea.
Tienen que decirnos claramente si estГғВЎn con Ucrania y con Europa o si estГғВЎn con Putin. Tenemos que explicar que la paz y la seguridad en nuestro continente pasan por seguir apoyando a Ucrania para lograr urgentemente una paz justa y duradera en la que participemos ucranianos y europeos. Y, a medio y largo plazo, tenemos que rearmar Europa y desarrollar una polГғВӯtica de defensa comГғВәn que nos permita ser autГғВіnomos y garantizar nuestra propia seguridad.
(El orador acepta responder a una pregunta formulada con arreglo al procedimiento de la ГӮВ«tarjeta azulГӮВ»)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:52:32</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:17:02</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_45"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_61"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_69"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_70"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_294">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_294</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Wie weigert mee te werken aan terugkeer, moet dat voelen in de portemonnee. Een verplichte erkenning van terugkeerbesluiten door alle EU-landen. Dit mag geen vrijblijvendheid zijn, maar moet een harde afspraak zijn. Wettelijke ondubbelzinnige regeling van asielopvang in veilige derde landen. Dat debat is al te lang blijven liggen, terwijl andere landen laten zien dat het werkt. Commissaris, ik wens u daarbij heel veel succes. Grenzen stellen is essentieel om draagvlak te behouden.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:15:32</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_217"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_293"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_294"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_414">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_414</del:identifier>
    <del:text>My home country, Finland, shares the EUГўВҖВҷs longest border with RussiaГўВҖВ”over 1,300 kilometres.
The Finnish Defence Forces have shown how decades of commitment is now bearing fruit.
Conscription, military training, and investments in defence have long been among the EUГўВҖВҷs best.
We are ready to defend our borders.
Meanwhile, some EU countries have neglected their duties, keeping defence spending minimal while expecting others to bear the burden.
Now the era of free riding is over ГўВҖВ” we cannot start to fund countries that have failed to prepare.
Defence is not a charity - itГўВҖВҷs everyoneГўВҖВҷs duty.</del:text>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_132"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_36">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_36</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Le peuple rГғВ©unionnais a perdu cinq des siens. Des milliers de foyers ont perdu lГўВҖВҷaccГғВЁs ГғВ  lГўВҖВҷГғВ©lectricitГғВ© et ГғВ  lГўВҖВҷeau. Les paysans perdent ГғВ  nouveau leurs rГғВ©coltes, des chouchous ГғВ  la canne, et ГғВ  Saint-BenoГғВ®t, lГўВҖВҷune des villes les plus pauvres de lГўВҖВҷГғВ®le, des centaines de familles vivent encore en centre dГўВҖВҷhГғВ©bergement.
La France a dГғВ©clarГғВ© lГўВҖВҷГғВ©tat de calamitГғВ© naturelle. Elle doit aussi dГғВ©clarer le blocage des prix, et lГўВҖВҷEurope doit prГғВӘter main forte. Nous devons aussi impГғВ©rativement dГғВ©velopper une culture du risque. DГўВҖВҷabord, dans lГўВҖВҷamГғВ©nagement du territoire: il faut cesser de construire en zone inondable et dans les ravines, tenir compte des conclusions des scientifiques et investir lГўВҖВҷargent public dans la protection des populations et de la nature, plutГғВҙt que dans de nouveaux projets routiers, inutiles. Ensuite, dans la solidaritГғВ©, parce que les plus vulnГғВ©rables sont toujours en premiГғВЁre ligne; alors plaГғВ§ons-les au cГ…В“ur de la future stratГғВ©gie europГғВ©enne dГўВҖВҷadaptation au dГғВ©rГғВЁglement climatique.
Chers collГғВЁgues, ne faisons pas de La RГғВ©union un nouveau symbole de notre inaction, mais au contraire plaГғВ§ons-la au cГ…В“ur de toutes nos actions.</del:text>
    <del:text>If Article 5 is under pressure and it's not a total guarantee, then NATO is not as strong as it should be. It's a deterrence. It's not an aggressive force.
And yes, we have to rebuild our European defence industry. That's absolutely clear. We have to be able to build up our own military and not buying it somewhere else.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:44:40</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:29:46</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_20"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_29"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_35"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_36"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_323">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_323</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Die Welt brennt, und Russland bombardiert mehr denn je die Ukraine, und wir konnten uns heute Morgen noch einmal ein Bild davon machen, was sich dort alles abspieltГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ das ist unmenschlich, das ist schrecklich, und noch schrecklicher ist es, dass so etwas ignoriert wird.
Europa stellt sich aufГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ auch im Rahmen der NATO mГғВјssen wir stГғВӨrker werden: die europГғВӨischen Staaten, die EU-Staaten, aber auch die europГғВӨischen Staaten, die nicht in der EU sind. Und das ist die gute Nachricht: 29 von 32ГӮВ NATO-Staaten haben jetzt die Chance, auch unabhГғВӨngiger zu werden.
Wir mГғВјssen aber auch wettbewerbsfГғВӨhiger werden. WettbewerbsfГғВӨhiger, damit wir eben auch in die Zukunft gehen kГғВ¶nnen, denn das Geld, was wir heute in die Hand nehmen, brauchen wir, aber es muss am langen Ende auch wieder erwirtschaftet werden. Das, was wir in der Ukraine sehenГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ ich komme noch einmal darauf zurГғВјckГӮВ ГўВҖВ“, zeigt ja Bilder, wie wir sie aus dem Ersten Weltkrieg kennen, aber auch die moderne, schreckliche KriegsfГғВјhrung, und darauf mГғВјssen wir Antworten finden in Forschung, in Technik.
Ich bin dem neuen Kommissar fГғВјr Verteidigung und Sicherheit sehr dankbar, dass er mit groГғВҹem Elan an die Arbeit herangegangen ist. Und natГғВјrlich ist das harte Arbeit, jetzt die Nationen zu ГғВјberzeugen, die einzelnen Staaten, dass sie auch Europa vertrauen kГғВ¶nnen. Und das wird die Zukunft weisen, dass wir auch vertrauenswГғВјrdig sind, dass wir das Geld, was wir in die Hand nehmen, auch sinnvoll und richtig einsetzen. Und das WeiГғВҹbuch mussГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ hoffe ichГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ sehr klar und deutlich sein. Die Zeit von ГўВҖВһlalaГўВҖВң und ГўВҖВһwir gucken malГўВҖВң und ГўВҖВһbusiness as usualГўВҖВң ist vorbei.
Meine Damen und Herren, so wie ich gerade angefangen habe, sage ich Ihnen, dass die Welt brennt, und wir in Europa kГғВ¶nnen den Unterschied machen als grГғВ¶ГғВҹtes Friedensprojekt der Welt.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:06:13</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_235"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_322"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_323"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_70">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_70</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Andreas Schwab</del:name>
    <del:name>OndГ…Вҷej DostГғВЎl</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_NI"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_403">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_403</del:identifier>
    <del:text>But in both cases, I think that we will be stronger allies and we will be a more secure continent by investing more and investing better in our defence. And that's why the ReArm Europe was necessary. We need to support it. It's probably not enough, but it's a decisive step in building the European defence capabilities. And that's why we also look forward to the white paper to be delivered next week, to see the ways how to spend not only more, but also to spend better and to produce more in the European Union.
We knew that we need to assume more responsibilities for our security. Now, that is not a choice. That is a necessity.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:50:33</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_289"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_402"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_403"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_521">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_521</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Die Aussprache ist geschlossen.
Die Abstimmung findet morgen, Mittwoch, den 12.ГӮВ MГғВӨrz 2025, statt.
Schriftliche ErklГғВӨrungen (Artikel 178)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:31:05</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_14"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_520"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_521"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_56">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_56</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Se o problema ГғВ© a burocracia que atinge as pequenas e mГғВ©dias empresas, porque ГғВ© que nГғВЈo se facilita a vida ГғВ s pequenas e mГғВ©dias empresas e se opta, por outro lado, por atribuir a empresas que nГғВЈo sГғВЈo pequenas e mГғВ©dias empresas, nomeadamente as designadas small midГўВҖВ‘caps, o mesmo tratamento que ГғВ s PME?
Essas sГғВЈo opГғВ§ГғВөes erradas, que escondem um problema de fundo que a senhora deputada devia explicar: a forma como este pacote Omnibus verdadeiramente favorece as grandes multinacionais e as grandes empresas, em vez de contribuir para os objetivos que lhe servem de pretexto.</del:text>
    <del:text>Nu. Nu ne mai putem permite refugii iluzorii ГғВ®n dependenГҲВӣe strategice, nici militare ГҲВҷi nici energetice. Acum este momentul ca Uniunea EuropeanГ„Вғ sГ„Вғ devinГ„Вғ un adevГ„Вғrat constructor al propriei sale securitГ„ВғГҲВӣi. Propunerile actuale ale Comisiei sunt un pas vital, dar avem nevoie de mai mult decГғВўt de alocГ„Вғri financiare. Avem nevoie de o industrie de apГ„Вғrare robustГ„Вғ ГҲВҷi unificatГ„Вғ. Avem nevoie de forГҲВӣe interoperabile, capabile de desfГ„ВғГҲВҷurare rapidГ„Вғ. Avem nevoie de o abordare strategicГ„Вғ comunГ„Вғ, de o ГғВ®nГҲВӣelegere unitarГ„Вғ a ameninГҲВӣГ„Вғrilor actuale. Trebuie sГ„Вғ devenim stГ„ВғpГғВўnii propriului nostru destin ГҲВҷi garantul propriei noastre securitГ„ВғГҲВӣi. Doar atunci ne vom putea proteja cu adevГ„Вғrat valorile, cetГ„ВғГҲВӣenii ГҲВҷi viitorul.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:27:52</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:57:35</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_33"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_48"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_55"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_56"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_220">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_220</del:identifier>
    <del:text>JednГғВҪm zo spГғВҙsobov, ako tieto nerovnosti vyrovnaГ…ВҘ, je spoloГ„ВҚnГғВҪ eurГғВіpsky prГғВӯstup k rГғВҪchlejГ…ВЎej dostupnosti liekov. PandГғВ©mia COVID-19 nГғВЎm ukГғВЎzala, ako rГғВҪchlo a neГ„ВҚakane mГғВҙГ…Вҫeme Г„ВҚeliГ…ВҘ kritickГғВ©mu nedostatku liekov, a nemГғВҙГ…Вҫeme si dovoliГ…ВҘ byГ…ВҘ zГғВЎvislГғВӯ od dodГғВЎvok z tretГғВӯch krajГғВӯn, ako je Г„ВҢГғВӯna Г„ВҚi India. MusГғВӯme investovaГ…ВҘ do eurГғВіpskych kapacГғВӯt na vГғВҪrobu liekov, podporiГ…ВҘ vГғВҪskum a zabezpeГ„ВҚiГ…ВҘ dostupnosГ…ВҘ liekov pre vГ…ВЎetkГғВҪch. To vГ…ВЎak zvlГғВЎdneme len spoloГ„ВҚne. Obrana, ГғВЎno, konkurencieschopnosГ…ВҘ, ГғВЎno, no rovnakГғВ© ГғВЎno platГғВӯ pre kvalitnГғВә zdravotnГғВә starostlivosГ…ВҘ pre vГ…ВЎetkГғВҪch obГ„ВҚanov a obГ„ВҚianky EurГғВіpy.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:20:50</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_163"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_219"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_220"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_311">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_311</del:identifier>
    <del:text>ГҺВ”ГҸВ…ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҸВ…ГҸВҮГҸВҺГҸВӮ, ГҸВ„ГҺВҝ ReArm EU, ГҺВұГҺВҪ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВҶГҺВ№ГҺВ»ГҸВҢГҺВҙГҺВҝГҺВҫГҺВҝ, ГҺВҙГҺВөГҺВҪ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВ„ГҺВөГҺВ»ГҺВөГҺВҜ ГҸВҢГҸВғГҺВҝ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВ„ГҺВөГҺВ»ГҺВөГҸВғГҺВјГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ® ГҺВёГҺВұ ГҺВёГҺВӯГҺВ»ГҺВұГҺВјГҺВө ГҺВ»ГҸВҚГҸВғГҺВ· ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҸВҖГҸВҒГҺВҝГҺВІГҺВ»ГҺВ®ГҺВјГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҺВӯГҸВҮГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВјГҺВө. ГҺВ”ГҺВөГҺВҪ ГҺВёГҺВӯГҺВ»ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВјГҺВө ГҺВҪГҺВӯГҺВұ ГҺВҙГҺВ¬ГҺВҪГҺВөГҺВ№ГҺВұ, ГҺВұГҺВ»ГҺВ»ГҺВ¬ ГҺВәГҺВҝГҺВ№ГҺВҪГҺВ¬ ГҺВөГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҸВүГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВҠГҺВәГҺВ¬ ГҸВҮГҸВҒГҺВ·ГҺВјГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҺВҙГҺВҝГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ¬ ГҺВөГҸВҒГҺВіГҺВұГҺВ»ГҺВөГҺВҜГҺВұ. ГҺВ“ГҺВ№ГҺВұ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВӯГҸВҮГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВјГҺВө ГҺВјГҺВ№ГҺВұ ГҺВөГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҸВүГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВҠГҺВәГҺВ® ГҺВұГҺВјГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ® ГҺВӯГҺВҪГҸВүГҸВғГҺВ· ГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВјГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВҒГҺВөГҺВҜ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҸВ…ГҸВҖГҺВөГҸВҒГҺВұГҸВғГҸВҖГҺВҜГҺВ¶ГҺВөГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВ„ГҺВөГҺВ»ГҺВөГҸВғГҺВјГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ¬ ГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҸВғГҸВҚГҺВҪГҺВҝГҸВҒГҺВұ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВӮ ГҸВғГҸВ…ГҺВјГҺВјГҺВ¬ГҸВҮГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВӮ ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВӮ, ГҺВҙГҺВөГҺВҪ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВұГҺВ№ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВҚГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВјГҸВҢГҺВҪГҺВҝ ГҺВөГҸВҖГҺВ№ГҸВҖГҺВ»ГҺВӯГҺВҝГҺВҪ ГҸВҮГҸВҒГҺВ®ГҺВјГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВұ. ГҺВ‘ГҸВҖГҺВұГҺВ№ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВҚГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВҖГҸВҒГҺВҝГҺВіГҸВҒГҺВ¬ГҺВјГҺВјГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҸВҢГҸВҖГҸВүГҸВӮ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝ EDIP, ГҺВјГҺВө ГҺВұГҸВ…ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВҒГҺВҝГҸВҚГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВҪГҸВҢГҺВҪГҺВөГҸВӮ, ГҸВҺГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҺВҝГҺВ№ ГҺВөГҸВҖГҺВөГҺВҪГҺВҙГҸВҚГҸВғГҺВөГҺВ№ГҸВӮ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВұГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВјГҺВөГҸВ„ГҸВүГҸВҖГҺВҜГҸВғГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВҪ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝ ГҺВӯГҺВ»ГҺВ»ГҺВөГҺВ№ГҺВјГҺВјГҺВұ ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҸВҒГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҺВіГҺВ№ГҺВәГҸВҺГҺВҪ ГҺВјГҺВӯГҸВғГҸВүГҺВҪ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВҙГҺВ№ГҺВұГҺВ»ГҺВөГҺВ№ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҺВіГҺВ№ГҺВәГҸВҢГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВ„ГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҺВӯГҸВҮГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВјГҺВө. NГҺВұ ГҺВҙГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВұГҺВҪГҺВ·ГҺВёГҺВҝГҸВҚГҺВҪ ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҺВ•ГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҸВҺГҸВҖГҺВ·, ГҺВөГҺВҪГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВҮГҸВҚГҺВҝГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҺВөГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҸВүГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВҠГҺВәГҺВ® ГҺВұГҺВјГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ® ГҺВІГҺВ№ГҺВҝГҺВјГҺВ·ГҸВҮГҺВұГҺВҪГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ® ГҺВІГҺВ¬ГҸВғГҺВ· ГҸВғГҺВө ГҸВҢГҺВ»ГҺВұ ГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҺВәГҸВҒГҺВ¬ГҸВ„ГҺВ· ГҺВјГҺВӯГҺВ»ГҺВ·, ГҺВіГҺВ№ГҺВұ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВјГҺВөГҺВ№ГҸВүГҺВёГҺВҝГҸВҚГҺВҪ ГҺВҝГҺВ№ ГҺВөГҺВҫГҺВұГҸВҒГҸВ„ГҺВ®ГҸВғГҺВөГҺВ№ГҸВӮ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҸВҢ ГҸВ„ГҸВҒГҺВҜГҸВ„ГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҸВҮГҸВҺГҸВҒГҺВөГҸВӮ. OГҺВ№ ГҺВөГҸВҖГҺВөГҺВҪГҺВҙГҸВҚГҸВғГҺВөГҺВ№ГҸВӮ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВјГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҺВіГҺВҜГҺВҪГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВҪ ГҸВғГҺВө ГҺВІГҺВ¬ГҸВҒГҺВҝГҸВӮ ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВҝГҺВ№ГҺВҪГҸВүГҺВҪГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ®ГҸВӮ ГҸВғГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҺВҝГҸВҮГҺВ®ГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҺВәГҺВҝГҺВ№ГҺВҪГҸВүГҺВҪГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВҝГҸВҚ ГҺВәГҸВҒГҺВ¬ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВӮ.
ГҺВӨГҺВ№ ГҸВғГҺВ·ГҺВјГҺВұГҸВғГҺВҜГҺВұ ГҺВӯГҸВҮГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВӯГҸВҮГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВјГҺВө ГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВҮГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҸВҢ ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҸВҒГҺВұГҸВ„ГҸВҢ ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҸВғГҸВҚГҺВҪГҺВҝГҸВҒГҺВұ, ГҺВөГҺВ¬ГҺВҪ ГҸВ…ГҸВҖГҺВҝГҺВҪГҺВҝГҺВјГҺВөГҸВҚГҸВғГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВјГҺВө ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҺВұГҸВғГҸВҶГҺВ¬ГҺВ»ГҺВөГҺВ№ГҺВұ ГҸВ„ГҸВүГҺВҪ ГҺВәГҺВҝГҺВ№ГҺВҪГҸВүГҺВҪГҺВ№ГҸВҺГҺВҪ ГҺВјГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҺВұГҸВ…ГҺВҫГҺВ¬ГҺВҪГҺВҝГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҸВӮ ГҺВұГҺВҪГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВҢГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВ„ГҺВөГҸВӮ; ГҺВ”ГҺВөГҺВҪ ГҸВ…ГҸВҖГҺВ¬ГҸВҒГҸВҮГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВөГҸВ…ГҺВ·ГҺВјГҺВөГҸВҒГҺВҜГҺВұ ГҸВҮГҸВүГҸВҒГҺВҜГҸВӮ ГҺВұГҸВғГҸВҶГҺВ¬ГҺВ»ГҺВөГҺВ№ГҺВұ. ГҺВ”ГҺВөГҺВҪ ГҸВ…ГҸВҖГҺВ¬ГҸВҒГҸВҮГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВұГҸВғГҸВҶГҺВ¬ГҺВ»ГҺВөГҺВ№ГҺВұ ГҸВҮГҸВүГҸВҒГҺВҜГҸВӮ ГҺВөГҸВ…ГҺВ·ГҺВјГҺВөГҸВҒГҺВҜГҺВұ. ГҺВ§ГҸВҒГҺВөГҺВ№ГҺВұГҺВ¶ГҸВҢГҺВјГҺВұГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҺВәГҺВҝГҺВ№ГҺВҪГҺВҝГҸВҚГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВҪГҸВҢГҺВҪГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҺВөГҺВҫГҺВұГҺВіГҸВүГҺВіГҸВҺГҺВҪ ГҺВөГҺВҫГҺВҝГҸВҖГҺВ»ГҺВ№ГҸВғГҺВјГҺВҝГҸВҚ, ГҸВҺГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВјГҺВ· ГҺВІГҸВҒГҺВөГҺВёГҺВҝГҸВҚГҺВҪ ГҺВөГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҸВүГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВҠГҺВәГҺВ¬ ГҸВҢГҸВҖГҺВ»ГҺВұ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВөГҺВ№ГҺВ»ГҺВҝГҸВҚГҺВҪ ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҺВәГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҺВ№ГҺВұГҸВҒГҸВҮГҺВҜГҺВұ ГҺВәГҸВҒГҺВұГҸВ„ГҸВҺГҺВҪ ГҺВјГҺВөГҺВ»ГҸВҺГҺВҪ. ГҺВӨГҺВӯГҺВ»ГҺВҝГҸВӮ, ГҺВёГҺВұ ГҸВҖГҸВҒГҺВӯГҸВҖГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВәГҺВ¬ГҺВҪГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВјГҺВө ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВҒГҺВұГҺВҜГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҺВёГҺВөГҸВғГҺВјГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ¬ ГҺВІГҺВ®ГҺВјГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВұ, ГҸВҺГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҺВ· ГҸВҒГҺВ®ГҸВ„ГҸВҒГҺВұ ГҺВіГҺВ№ГҺВұ ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҺВәГҺВҝГҺВ№ГҺВҪГҺВ® ГҺВ¬ГҺВјГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҺВұ, ГҸВ„ГҺВҝ ГҺВ¬ГҸВҒГҺВёГҸВҒГҺВҝ 42 ГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВҒГҺВ¬ГҺВіГҸВҒГҺВұГҸВҶГҺВҝГҸВӮ 7 ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВЈГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҺВёГҺВ®ГҺВәГҺВ·ГҸВӮ, ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВјГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҺВөГҺВҜГҺВҪГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВәГҺВөГҺВҪГҺВ® ГҸВҖГҺВөГҸВҒГҺВ№ГҺВөГҸВҮГҺВҝГҺВјГҺВӯГҺВҪГҺВҝГҸВ…, ГҺВұГҺВ»ГҺВ»ГҺВ¬ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВ„ГҺВөГҺВ»ГҺВөГҺВҜ ГҸВ„ГҺВ· ГҺВІГҺВұГҸВғГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ® ГҺВөГҺВіГҺВіГҸВҚГҺВ·ГҸВғГҺВ· ГҺВұГҸВғГҸВҶГҺВұГҺВ»ГҺВөГҺВҜГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҸВҢГҺВ»ГҸВүГҺВҪ ГҸВ„ГҸВүГҺВҪ ГҺВәГҸВҒГҺВұГҸВ„ГҸВҺГҺВҪ ГҺВјГҺВөГҺВ»ГҸВҺГҺВҪ, ГҺВұГҸВҖГҸВҢ ГҸВ„ГҺВ· ГҺВҰГҺВ№ГҺВҪГҺВ»ГҺВұГҺВҪГҺВҙГҺВҜГҺВұ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҺВ•ГҸВғГҺВёГҺВҝГҺВҪГҺВҜГҺВұ ГҺВјГҺВӯГҸВҮГҸВҒГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҺВ•ГҺВ»ГҺВ»ГҺВ¬ГҺВҙГҺВұ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҺВҡГҸВҚГҸВҖГҸВҒГҺВҝ. ГҺВ•ГҸВ…ГҸВҮГҺВұГҸВҒГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҸВҺ.</del:text>
