  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_46">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_46</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Kira Marie Peter-Hansen</del:name>
    <del:name>Roberto Vannacci</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Verts_ALE"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PfE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_324">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_324</del:identifier>
    <del:text>We must defend the rules-based international order, basing decisions on facts, treating partners with respect, and we must finally stand on our own feet. This means weapons and funding, but most crucially, it means attracting the brightest minds in science, tech and engineering. And here, dear colleagues, is the perfect match because many in the US also reject this administration's agenda ГўВҖВ“ they too, are desperately looking for an alternative. So let's roll out the red carpet, launch a new blue card for a new era, a fast-track visa for skilled professionals from the US who want to work in Europe and build a future based on ethics, sustainability and fair growth. And to the scientists, engineers and innovators in the US: come to Europe. When autocrats embolden autocrats, democrats stand with democrats.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:08:50</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_236"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_323"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_324"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_291">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_291</del:identifier>
    <del:name>ГҺВ“ГҺВөГҸВҺГҸВҒГҺВіГҺВ№ГҺВҝГҸВӮ ГҺВ‘ГҸВ…ГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВ¬ГҸВӮ</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_85">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_85</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Europa sigue enredada en su propia telaraГғВұa de normativas mientras que la industria china avanza con agilidad y sentido prГғВЎctico. En lugar de crear un entorno flexible para la innovaciГғВіn y la inversiГғВіn, seguimos aГғВұadiendo mГғВЎs reglas, mГғВЎs condiciones, mГғВЎs obstГғВЎculos... Y, mientras tanto, nuestras empresas pagan el precio en forma de pГғВ©rdida de competitividad, deslocalizaciГғВіn y destrucciГғВіn de empleo. Un ejemplo claro es la reciente normativa sobre la prohibiciГғВіn definitiva de la venta de motores de combustiГғВіn para el 2035, que pone en jaque a la industria automotriz europea.
Esta imposiciГғВіn estГғВЎ empujando a nuestras empresas al cierre. Es hora de devolver la libertad a nuestras empresas y dejar de castigar al progreso con burocracia.</del:text>
    <del:text>Mais do que nunca, todos compreendemos que a seguranГғВ§a europeia estГғВЎ estreitamente ligada ao desfecho da guerra na UcrГғВўnia. O rearmamento da UniГғВЈo Europeia, nomeadamente para responder ГғВ s ameaГғВ§as hГғВӯbridas, nГғВЈo ГғВ© uma escolha, ГғВ© uma emergГғВӘncia de dissuasГғВЈo.
A UcrГғВўnia precisa de apoio imediato, incluindo da mobilizaГғВ§ГғВЈo dos ativos russos congelados, e as conclusГғВөes do Conselho mostram a compreensГғВЈo de que vivemos uma rutura histГғВіrica.
Mas precisamos de ir mais longe. Da mesma forma que fomos capazes de o fazer na resposta ГғВ  pandemia, tambГғВ©m no investimento em seguranГғВ§a e defesa precisamos de maior solidariedade e coordenaГғВ§ГғВЈo entre os Estados-Membros, nomeadamente atravГғВ©s de mutualizaГғВ§ГғВЈo da dГғВӯvida e de compras conjuntas.
E, ao mesmo tempo, precisamos de fazer tudo para manter a mesma ambiГғВ§ГғВЈo de investimento nas ГғВЎreas sociais e ambientais da UniГғВЈo Europeia, que sГғВЈo a nossa razГғВЈo de ser.
Por ГғВәltimo, precisamos de ser claros com os nossos cidadГғВЈos: o momento que vivemos ГғВ© grave, e provavelmente nГғВЈo o ultrapassaremos sem sacrifГғВӯcios.ГӮВ A paz justa que queremos para a UcrГғВўnia ГғВ© a paz que nos protegerГғВЎ, enquanto sociedades democrГғВЎticas e livres, a todos.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:12:40</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:35:20</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_58"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_73"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_84"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_85"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_84">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_84</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Aquella agenda ideolГғВіgica resultaba ser un lastre para nuestras empresas y la competitividad europea. Aun asГғВӯ, este paquete ГғВіmnibus no supondrГғВЎ la eliminaciГғВіn de aquellas trabas. Lo que se estГғВЎ haciendo es aplazar los problemas. Que nadie piense que el consenso de populares y socialistas va a retractarse de la oportunidad de llevar todos esos disparates hasta el final.
Lo que necesitan las empresas europeas es mГғВЎs libertad, menos impuestos, menos burocracia, menos regulaciГғВіn y acabar con la hiperinflaciГғВіn legislativa. Solo asГғВӯ se crece y se genera empleo.
Si Europa pretende ocupar el lugar en el mundo que merece, lo primero, lo mГғВЎs aconsejable, es que los emprendedores europeos no se encuentren en la UniГғВіn Europea con El castillo de Kafka, que es la gran pesadilla de la modernidad, que toma forma de burocracia absurda, infinita y desalentadora, como esta casa.</del:text>
    <del:text>Mano Г…Вҫinia viena ГўВҖВ“ Europa bus stipri, jei padГ„В—sime Ukrainai laimГ„В—ti. Ir mes galime, tik reikia patikГ„В—ti, kad galime. ГўВҖВһReArm EuropeГўВҖВң turi bГ…В«ti Г„ВҜgyvendinama solidariai tarp Europos SГ„В…jungos nariГ…Ві ir solidariai su Ukraina, kuri jau yra ES narГ„В— de facto, nes savo krauju gina mus.
Ukrainos fronte sprendГ…Вҫiamas Europos likimas. KaГ…Вҫkas paskaiГ„ВҚiavo, kad iki Г…ВЎiol kiekvienam Europos SГ„В…jungos pilieГ„ВҚiui Europos karinГ„В— parama Ukrainai nekainavo nГ„В— dviejГ…Ві puodeliГ…Ві kavos. ValstybГ„В—s narГ„В—s tikrai gali skirti Ukrainai daugiau. Sutarkim dГ„В—l ne maГ…Вҫiau kaip 0,25ГӮВ proc. nuo BVP iГ…ВЎ kiekvienos Г…ВЎalies. IГ…ВЎkelkim ambicijГ„В…: Ukraina ГўВҖВ“ Europos SГ„В…jungos narГ„В— iki 2030ГӮВ m. Pasikartokim istorijos pamokas ir priimkim iГ…ВЎГ…ВЎГ…В«kius. ГўВҖВһKeep calm, carry onГўВҖВң ГўВҖВ“ Winston Churchill.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:11:13</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:33:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_57"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_72"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_83"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_84"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_30">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_30</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:text>So we need to step out, and we need to fill the gap left by Americans. And we need to do it now. It's not a matter of months or years, it's a matter of hours, days, maximum weeks. If we fail in Ukraine, if Ukraine falls, then we will not merely be back to square one, we will be in a much, much darker place, starting to rebuild Europe's security from shambles. We must not let this happen.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:29:39</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:21:34</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_14"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_26"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_29"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_30"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_541">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_541</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Svaret ГғВӨr att kapitulation inte ligger i deras intresse utifrГғВҘn det lГғВҘngsiktiga mГғВҘlet att utrota Israel. Svaret ГғВӨr att de inte oroar sig fГғВ¶r Gazas civila, som de frГғВӨmst ser som civila skГғВ¶ldar som kan offras i kampen mot Israel. SГғВҘ lГғВӨnge som dessa omstГғВӨndigheter kvarstГғВҘr kommer ingen lГғВҘngvarig fred att kunna uppnГғВҘs. DГғВӨrfГғВ¶r behГғВ¶ver EU ГғВ¶ka trycket pГғВҘ palestinierna och deras ledare i sГғВҘvГғВӨl Gaza som pГғВҘ VГғВӨstbanken, genom att villkora bistГғВҘndet och rikta sanktioner mot Hamas ekonomiska struktur.
Den palestinska myndigheten behГғВ¶ver i handling ta avstГғВҘnd frГғВҘn Hamas, och Gaza demilitariseras. Det palestinska folket behГғВ¶ver inse att vГғВӨgen till fred fГғВ¶rutsГғВӨtter ett totalt avstГғВҘndstagande frГғВҘn terrorism.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T23:02:48</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_218"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_540"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_541"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_154">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_154</del:identifier>
    <del:text>And the same can be said about the trilogues, so I would like to also thank the Commission, particularly Commissioner Marta Kos, as well as the Polish Presidency and Ambassador Agnieszka Bartol, for those very, very constructive negotiations that helped us to come to a swift and very good outcome.
I'm also reassured by the debate here in this plenary hall today. I think that there is a very strong degree of unity and also a shared sense of purpose, with a very few exceptions. I do believe that Moldova, at this critical moment, needs our help, and I do believe that we also need Moldova. It's not perhaps the largest of the European countries, but it is far too important to be neglected. They deserve their place in our Union.</del:text>
    <del:text>Als ik een dochter zou hebben, dan zou ik alvast een helmpje gaan kopen om haar te beschermen, want op deze manier worden vrouwen volledig in de steek gelaten door politici zoals u. Helaas.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:02:27</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:51:57</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_87"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_112"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_153"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_154"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_293">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_293</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Wzywam do uГ…ВӮatwienia paГ…В„stwom narodowym stosowania nadzoru i detencji. JeГ…Вӣli paГ…В„stwo decyduje w trybie administracyjnym, Г…Вјe dana osoba ze wzglГ„ВҷdГғВіw bezpieczeГ…В„stwa ma opuГ…ВӣciГ„ВҮ jego terytorium, ma absolutne prawo, a wrГ„Вҷcz obowiГ„В…zek egzekwowania tej decyzji. Europa musi odzyskaГ„ВҮ kontrolГ„Вҷ nad wГ…ВӮasnym terytorium. W przeciwnym wypadku nadal pozostanie szerokГ„В… autostradГ„В… dla nielegalnej imigracji.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:13:34</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_216"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_292"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_293"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_477">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_477</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:23:25</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_288"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_476"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_477"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_462">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_462</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Und jetzt gehen Sie mit dem Clean Industrial Deal einen wichtigen Schritt, und er greift viele der zentralen Forderungen der CDU und EVP auf: die StГғВӨrkung des Standorts Europas, die FГғВ¶rderung von Forschung und Innovation und die Garantie bezahlbarer Energie. Aber das reicht nicht. Europa braucht mehr Tempo bei der Umsetzung, mehr Pragmatismus, mehr Vertrauen in den Markt und seine Unternehmen. Die Zeit zum Handeln ist jetzt.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:03:58</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_330"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_461"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_462"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_139">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_139</del:identifier>
    <del:name>HГғВ©lder Sousa Silva</del:name>
    <del:name>Jessika Van Leeuwen</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_380">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_380</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Jaume Asens LlodrГғ</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Verts_ALE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_280">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_280</del:identifier>
    <del:text>A moГ…Вјe teraz naleГ…Вјy sobie zadaГ„ВҮ pytanie skГ„В…d te miliony nielegalnych ГўВҖВ“ podkreГ…Вӣlam nielegalnych ГўВҖВ“ imigrantГғВіw w naszym europejskim domu. Czy przypadkiem, tak jak juГ…Вј byГ…ВӮa o tym mowa, to nie polityka, idiotyczna polityka takich paГ…В„stw jak Niemcy ГўВҖВ“ typu Herzlich willkommen Angeli Merkel ГўВҲВ’ do tej sytuacji doprowadziГ…ВӮa. MoГ…Вјe najwyГ…Вјszy czas, Г…Вјeby w tym miejscu padГ…ВӮy sГ…ВӮowa przepraszam pod adresem funkcjonariuszy polskiej Policji, StraГ…Вјy Granicznej za to, Г…Вјe wtedy, kiedy bronili naszego europejskiego domu przed tym zalewem nielegalnych imigrantГғВіw, to rГғВіwnieГ…Вј z tej sali padaГ…ВӮy idiotyczne sГ…ВӮowa: ГўВҖВһWpuГ…ВӣГ„ВҮcie ich, a pГғВіГ…Вәniej siГ„Вҷ zobaczy, kim oni sГ„В…ГўВҖВқ. Kim oni sГ„В… okazaГ…ВӮo siГ„Вҷ na ulicach Monachium i innych europejskich miast. Stop tej idiotycznej polityce otwartych drzwi naszego europejskiego domu.
(MГғВіwca nie zgodziГ…ВӮ siГ„Вҷ na pytanie zasygnalizowane przez podniesienie niebieskiej kartki przez Lukas Sieper)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:56:18</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_205"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_279"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_280"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_112">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_112</del:identifier>
