  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_50">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_50</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Autrement, vous avez le choix de ne pas faire cette nГғВ©gociation avec nous, mais avec lГўВҖВҷextrГғВӘme droite. Si vous nГғВ©gociez avec lГўВҖВҷextrГғВӘme droite, alors cela veut dire que vous cassez la capacitГғВ© ГғВ  avoir une confiance dans cette majoritГғВ© vonГӮВ derГӮВ Leyen, qui a ГғВ©lu la prГғВ©sidente de la Commission. Or vous avez besoin de cette majoritГғВ© vonГӮВ derГӮВ Leyen; lГўВҖВҷEurope a besoin de cette majoritГғВ© von der Leyen pour rГғВ©pondre ГғВ  la crise gГғВ©opolitique que nous connaissons et construire cette Europe-puissance dont on a plus que jamais besoin. Ce nГўВҖВҷest pas avec lГўВҖВҷextrГғВӘme droite que vous allez le faire. Ce nГўВҖВҷest pas avec ceux qui viennent de rappeler que la pire responsabilitГғВ© sur le secteur de lГўВҖВҷacier, ce serait le texte sur la CSRD, alors que ce sont ГғВ©videmment les amis de lГўВҖВҷextrГғВӘme droite, comme DonaldГӮВ Trump, qui veulent imposer des droits de douane qui vont faire trГғВЁs mal au secteur de lГўВҖВҷacier.
Vous avez le choix: soit vous faites une simplification intelligente avec nous, soit vous faites la tronГғВ§onneuse avec lГўВҖВҷextrГғВӘme droite. CГўВҖВҷest lГўВҖВҷHistoire qui vous regarde.</del:text>
    <del:text>Therefore, it is essential that the EU strengthens its support for Ukraine. In addition, the EU should set a strategic goal of reducing our dependencies on the US. This means: creating a European security architecture, redirecting all financing currently going to the US arms industry to Europe; reducing energy dependencies; and limiting the powers of the digital oligarchs.
Changes to the fiscal rules must enable all of these investments. I do understand that the goal might also require more investment in European defence. But it would be a historic mistake to finance this by cutting welfare, because that would only cement the rise to power of Putin's and Trump's allies in Europe: the extreme right. And for once, the EU needs to be smarter than this.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:10:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:48:20</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_28"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_42"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_49"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_50"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_255">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_255</del:identifier>
    <del:name>ГҺВ’ГҺВұГҺВіГҺВіГҺВӯГҺВ»ГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВңГҺВөГҸВҠГҺВјГҺВұГҸВҒГҺВ¬ГҺВәГҺВ·ГҸВӮ</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_162">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_162</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Laurence Trochu</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_544">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_544</del:identifier>
    <del:text>CГўВҖВҷest lГғВ , la caractГғВ©ristique de cette Union europГғВ©enne, aujourdГўВҖВҷhui: un mГғВ©pris pour la vie des Palestiniens! Parce que oui, vous avez rГғВ©ussi ГғВ  faire un discours en disant: ГӮВ«Ah! La situation ГғВ  Gaza empireГўВҖВҰГӮВ», sans mentionner pourquoi elle empire. Pourquoi est-ce quГўВҖВҷelle empire? Eh bien, parce quГўВҖВҷIsraГғВ«l bloque toute aide humanitaire, toute nourriture, et mГғВӘme lГўВҖВҷГғВ©lectricitГғВ©. QuГўВҖВҷest-ce que cela veut dire? Sans ГғВ©lectricitГғВ©, pas de dГғВ©salinisation de lГўВҖВҷeau, et donc pas dГўВҖВҷeau potable. Ainsi, les gens, les familles, les enfants nГўВҖВҷont pas dГўВҖВҷeau potable, et vous, vous ГғВӘtes lГғВ  en train de rigoler! Comment est-ce possible, Monsieur le Ministre? Comment est-ce possible, sГўВҖВҷil vous plaГғВ®t?
Alors, aujourdГўВҖВҷhui, cette complicitГғВ© europГғВ©enne et ce manque de respect pour la vie des Palestiniens doivent cesser, parce que cela va se payer cash! Je vous le promets!</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T23:06:49</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_22"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_543"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_544"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_290">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_290</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Presidente.</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:hasRole rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/role_participant_290"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_147">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_147</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Planul de creГҲВҷtere al Uniunii Europene este un semnal clar. Republica Moldova trebuie sprijinitГ„Вғ sГ„Вғ se decupleze definitiv de influenГҲВӣele rГ„ВғsГ„Вғritene. Reforma, modernizarea, distanГҲВӣarea faГҲВӣГ„Вғ de moГҲВҷtenirea sovieticГ„Вғ, toate acestea trebuie ГғВ®ncurajate cu fermitate.
Am votat pentru un sprijin de 1,9 miliarde de euro pentru Republica Moldova. Nu este doar un ajutor financiar, este o declaraГҲВӣie politicГ„Вғ cГ„Вғ suntem alГ„Вғturi de fraГҲВӣii noГҲВҷtri de peste Prut.
Uniunea face puterea ГҲВҷi poate ГғВ®ntr-o zi aceastГ„Вғ reunire politicГ„Вғ, economicГ„Вғ ГҲВҷi sufleteascГ„Вғ va fi desГ„ВғvГғВўrГҲВҷitГ„Вғ sub acelaГҲВҷi tricolor ГғВ®n Uniunea EuropeanГ„Вғ.
PГғВўnГ„Вғ atunci, Republica Moldova are nevoie de sprijinul nostru. Acum, aici, concret.</del:text>
    <del:text>L'aborto ГғВЁ una scelta difficile, e spesso dolorosa: ma negarlo significa condannare le donne a sofferenze e pericoli.
La road map affronta temi cruciali, come la violenza di genere, le disuguaglianze economiche. Ma senza impegni concreti resta solo carta e la carta da sola non protegge nessuna donna, non garantisce i diritti e non cambia la realtГғВ .
L'Europa non puГғВІ permettersi passi indietro. Mentre negli Stati Uniti i diritti delle donne sono erosi, noi dobbiamo essere un baluardo. Servono azioni e non simboli, perchГғВ© la libertГғВ , la dignitГғВ  e i diritti non si negoziano mai.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T20:52:16</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:42:13</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_114"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_107"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_146"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_147"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_217">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_217</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Pero ahora vemos claramente que la escasez de fГғВЎrmacos es tambiГғВ©n uno de los talones de Aquiles de la seguridad en Europa. Tanto que hablamos de defensa, recordemos que la seguridad es un concepto mГғВЎs amplio y que tiene que ver tambiГғВ©n con el suministro de fГғВЎrmacos para actuar ante las enfermedades de los europeos y europeas. No lo olvidemos, porque la seguridad de las cadenas de suministro no puede quedar solamente en manos de las ayudas de Estado o de la simplificaciГғВіn administrativa. Hacen falta fondos europeos para fomentar esta autonomГғВӯa estratГғВ©gica y creo que falta ambiciГғВіn en la propuesta. Esperamos mejorarla en este Parlamento, pero, desde luego, esos medicamentos esenciales, ademГғВЎs, deben ser fabricados en Europa en la medida de lo posible.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:16:25</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_160"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_216"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_217"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_126">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_126</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Branko Grims</del:name>
    <del:name>Vilija BlinkeviГ„ВҚiГ…В«tГ„В—</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_19">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_19</del:identifier>
    <del:text>MrГӮВ Г…ВһtefГ„ВғnuГҲВӣГ„Вғ, go ahead.</del:text>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:18:52</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:03:39</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_16"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_18"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_19"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_132">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_132</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ovaj fond, vrijedan gotovo 1,9 milijardi eura, potaknut Г„ВҮe Moldovu na provedbu nuГ…Вҫnih reformi, jaГ„ВҚanje institucija i ubrzanje integracije u europske, gospodarske i politiГ„ВҚke tokove kroz usko povezivanje investicija s reformama, sliГ„ВҚno kao i za plan rasta za takozvani zapadni Balkan.
PoveГ„ВҮano pretfinanciranje i dodatna bespovratna sredstva osigurat Г„ВҮe ne samo da drГ…Вҫava izdrГ…Вҫi trenutne izazove, veГ„ВҮ i ostvari konkretne pomake na svom europskom putu. Ulaganje u sigurnost, ulaganje u demokraciju i stabilnost naГ…ВЎeg susjedstva ulaganje je u sigurniju i prosperitetniju Europu za sve nas.
Г„ВҢestitam izvjestiteljima Siegfriedu MureГ…Вҹanu i Svenu Mikseru na njihovom trudu i na uspjeГ…ВЎnom zavrГ…ВЎetku pregovora.</del:text>
    <del:text>Every victory we have made for women's rights, it has been a hard fight to win it and it has brought prosperity and development to the entire humanity. This movement is so eager on attacking fundamental rights and human rights.ГӮВ The EU is no exception.ГӮВ Ladies and gentlemen, the anti-gender movement is growing in our continent and in this House.
The trend of mainstreaming misogyny must end now. We have to mainstream gender equality. This is a call for action to us all feminists to mobilise, unite and to rebuild a better world based on feminism free from patriarchy. We must increase funding for gender equality in the next MFF; enshrine the right to abortion in the EU Charter of Fundamental Rights; criminalise rape with a consent-based definition of rape; and finally, the EU needs a feminist foreign policy.
It will take us 130 years to eradicate extreme poverty for women and girls, and 60 years to reach gender equality in Europe. It is time to put in a higher gear.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T20:31:43</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:25:15</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_99"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_96"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_131"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_132"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_173">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_173</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Eine Studie von RГғВјstungslobbyisten aus Deutschland mit dem bezeichnenden NamenГӮВ Sparta gibt darГғВјber nun Auskunft. Es geht um die Schaffung einer ГўВҖВһasymmetrischen ГғВңberlegenheitГўВҖВң. Es geht um ГўВҖВһdigitale FГғВјhrungsГғВјberlegenheit, AufklГғВӨrungsГўВҖВ‘ und WirkГғВјberlegenheit, die sofort verfГғВјgbar und kurzfristig einsetzbar sein sollenГўВҖВң.
Mit Landesverteidigung hat dies ganz offensichtlich nichts mehr zu tun. Auch nicht mit einem Gleichgewicht der militГғВӨrischen KrГғВӨfte und noch weniger mit der strukturellen NichtangriffsfГғВӨhigkeit, wie sie die NATO frГғВјher fГғВјr sich postuliert hat. Hier soll der Krieg als Mittel der Politik wieder hoffГғВӨhig gemacht werden. DafГғВјr hat die EuropГғВӨische Union sicherlich nicht den Friedensnobelpreis erhalten.</del:text>
    <del:text>Pourtant, une fois de plus, la Commission europГғВ©enne dГғВ©ГғВ§oit. UrsulaГӮВ vonГӮВ derГӮВ Leyen cГғВЁde face aux conservateurs. Elle nous livre une opГғВ©ration de communication digne de la politiqueГӮВ RSE dГўВҖВҷun grand groupe privГғВ©, oГғВ№ lГўВҖВҷГғВ©galitГғВ© femmes-hommes est dГғВ©fendue uniquement sous le prisme de bГғВ©nГғВ©fices ГғВ©conomiques. JГўВҖВҷaccueille donc ce texte avec luciditГғВ©. CГўВҖВҷest un premier pas, mais il est insuffisant.
Nous ne pourrons pas nous contenter de dГғВ©clarations dГўВҖВҷintention. Il nous faut des engagements clairs, ГғВ  la hauteur des enjeux. ГғВҖ lГўВҖВҷheure oГғВ№ Poutine, mais aussi tous les impГғВ©rialistes et les intГғВ©gristes religieux que nous combattons, nГўВҖВҷattaquent pas seulement nos frontiГғВЁres europГғВ©ennes, mais mГғВЁnent une guerre contre les femmes, il nous faut assumer une diplomatie fГғВ©ministe europГғВ©enne et leur opposer notre modГғВЁle fГғВ©ministe europГғВ©en ambitieux, universaliste et combatif.</del:text>
