  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_171">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_171</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Let us be very clear: Ireland's neutrality and our long-standing commitment to UN peacekeeping missions has made the world safer. It is attacks on the UN and on neutrality that is making the world less safe.
From our role in leading negotiations on the Treaty of the Non-Proliferation of Nuclear Weapons to being the only country to have an unbroken record of UN peacekeeping service since 1958, Ireland's neutrality has been a beacon in this world.
The cynical moves to scrap the triple lock will move us away from the UN and threatens Ireland's neutrality. The most recent poll shows that 75ГӮВ % of Irish people support our continued neutrality. Yet the Irish Government seems determined to throw its lot in with the EU, to undermine our neutrality at every turn, while the EU is engaging in an arms race. It's time to save the triple lock.</del:text>
    <del:text>Tekst koji je zapravo predstavljen je dobar i pokazuje da unatoГ„ВҚ otporima koje imamo na najviГ…ВЎim razinama u Komisiji postoji dovoljno snage da se Г…Вҫenska prava i zaГ…ВЎtite, ali i unaprijede. No, moramo biti svjesni da je ovaj tekst samo iscrtavanje svojevrsne vizije i da nam tek pravi posao predstoji u novoj strategiji rodne ravnopravnosti.
Ta strategija mora ukljuГ„ВҚivati konkretne obaveze i prijedloge te opipljive zakonodavne i nezakonodavne mjere. Osim toga, ono Г…ВЎto je vaГ…Вҫno za reГ„ВҮi da strategiju trebaju pratiti vrlo konkretna financijska sredstva i traГ…Вҫit Г„ВҮemo zasebnu i jasnu proraГ„ВҚunsku liniju za ostvarivanje svih prioriteta u podruГ„ВҚju rodne ravnopravnosti jer u vremenima kakva su danas, prepuna nestabilnosti i usmjeravanja sredstava prema obrani i sigurnosti, vaГ…Вҫno je naglasiti da je rodna ravnopravnost jedan od temeljnih uvjeta za druГ…ВЎtvenu sigurnosti i napredak.
NeГ„ВҮemo dozvoliti da se ova tema marginalizira i da se napori u ovom dijelu umanje ili zanemare. U to budite sigurni.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:27:57</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:12:42</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_7"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_123"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_170"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_171"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_377">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_377</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Temos de garantir que a UniГғВЈo estГғВЎ preparada para enfrentar todo o tipo de ameaГғВ§as, desde as hГғВӯbridas ГғВ s convencionais, estabelecendo uma forte dissuasГғВЈo, reduzindo as nossas dependГғВӘncias e reforГғВ§ando a nossa autonomia.
Mas qualquer ideia de tentar escolher entre investimentos em seguranГғВ§a e defesa, ou em coesГғВЈo social, ou em coesГғВЈo, resultaria numa derrota certa em ambas as frentes. Qualquer estratГғВ©gia de investimento tem de ser abrangente, terГғВЎ de abordar tanto as nossas vulnerabilidades em capacidades militares como as do nosso tecido social.
Estas sГғВЈo decisГғВөes estratГғВ©gicas para a UniГғВЈo e para o seu futuro. Isso significa que o Parlamento Europeu nГғВЈo deve ser excluГғВӯdo dos processos de decisГғВЈo no que diz respeito aos programas de despesa subjacentes ГғВ s opГғВ§ГғВөes tomadas para a UniГғВЈo Europeia.
A recente proposta do ReArm inclui novos emprГғВ©stimos conjuntos com base no artigo 122.ГӮВә do Tratado sobre o Funcionamento da UniГғВЈo Europeia ГўВҖВ” e nГғВЈo podemos deixar de lamentar o recurso, novamente, a este artigo, que exclui o Parlamento da decisГғВЈo.ГӮВ O Parlamento Europeu ГғВ© a ГғВәnica instituiГғВ§ГғВЈo com poderes legislativos, orГғВ§amentais e de supervisГғВЈo, com legitimidade democrГғВЎtica conferida pela eleiГғВ§ГғВЈo direta dos seus membros.
Estamos cГғВЎ para decidir em prol dos cidadГғВЈos europeus.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:17:27</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_271"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_376"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_377"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_45">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_45</del:identifier>
    <del:text>But I still believe that there are enough Commission officials listening to this broadcast anyway. And I think that this House should not be stuck because of this.
So I would like to give the floor to Tomas TobГғВ© to open the debate.</del:text>
    <del:text>They wonder when we will take responsibility. Right now, we are only excited because Trump woke us up. Basically, he just showed us that there is no such thing as a free lunch. And we are upset? The fact that we needed this wake-up call about defence is so disturbing for our citizens.
We need to remember that Europe was stronger, and can be strong again. We need to remember that still the end of the Cold War was not the end of history, that we cannot earn respect if we do not change our mindset.
We need to invest in our defence and values, and stand firm for our principles ГўВҖВ“ not only when it's comfortable, but also when it is not. Because to the question of whether our citizens can count on us, the answer must be 'yes'!</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:00:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:41:47</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_38"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_44"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_45"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_440">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_440</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Es ist schon gesagt worden, die Klimaziele erreichen wir nur mit einer wettbewerbsfГғВӨhigen Wirtschaft. Aber zur Wahrheit gehГғВ¶rt halt, dass die ArbeitsplГғВӨtze, die in dieser Wirtschaft geschaffen werden, langfristig nur dann da sind, wenn die Wirtschaft wettbewerbsfГғВӨhig ist. WettbewerbsfГғВӨhigkeit erreicht man nicht durch mehr Subventionen oder durch zusГғВӨtzliche Regulierung, sondern WettbewerbsfГғВӨhigkeit erreicht man dadurch, dass man Direktinvestitionen nach Europa holt, WettbewerbsfГғВӨhigkeit erreicht man dadurch, dass europГғВӨische Firmen innovative Produkte herstellen und dass die Abgabenlast gesenkt wird.
Ich wГғВјrde mich freuen, wenn wir einen viel, viel stГғВӨrkeren Fokus auf diesen Punkt setzen: Wie kГғВ¶nnen wir die Kosten runter kriegen? Wie kГғВ¶nnen wir die Unternehmen langfristig wettbewerbsfГғВӨhig kriegen, und nicht: Wie schaffen wir neue Regulierungen und neue Subventionen?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:35:29</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_196"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_439"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_440"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_510">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_510</del:identifier>
    <del:text>En lo que afecta a las comunidades kurdas parece haber esperanza a los dos lados de la frontera, aunque con lГғВіgicas y ritmos diferentes. El acuerdo inicial alcanzado anoche tiene al menos dos raГғВӯces: las masacres del ataque de estos dГғВӯas y el riesgo de descontrol, y la llamada de ГғВ–calan al desarme y disoluciГғВіn de la organizaciГғВіn terrorista PKK, cuyas ondas han alcanzado a las fuerzas militantes turcas del norte de Siria.
Es un acuerdo inicial y, por tanto, sujeto a sacudidas, pero nuestra voluntad polГғВӯtica hacia ese marco es que haya una Siria unida, soberana, inclusiva y en manos de los propios sirios. Por lo tanto, fuera TurquГғВӯa, fuera Israel y fuera Rusia.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:14:14</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_361"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_509"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_510"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem10">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Topic"/>
    <del:identifier>creitem10</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Resumption of the sitting</del:name>
    <del:name>Appointment of a member of the Single Resolution Board (A10-0025/2025 - Aurore Lalucq) (vote)</del:name>
    <skos:broader rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem5"/>
    <skos:broader rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem9"/>
    <skos:narrower rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem12"/>
    <skos:narrower rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem15"/>
