  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_257">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_257</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Rihards Kols</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_75">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_75</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:text>Ich verlange einen ambitionierten Vorschlag, der Verteidigung als europГғВӨische Aufgabe versteht, der echtes europГғВӨisches Geld in die Hand nimmt, ohne den sozialen Zusammenhalt zu schwГғВӨchen. Das verlangt gemeinsame Verschuldung fГғВјr gemeinsame Verteidigungsaufgaben, ohne nationale Schulden zu erhГғВ¶hen.
Lasst uns mutig sein! Die ГғВӨuГғВҹeren Gefahren unseres Kontinents sind die Pandemie unserer Zeit.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:59:06</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:23:35</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_48"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_65"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_74"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_75"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_353">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_353</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Wir werden unsere Union verteidigen, koste es, was es wolle. Wir werden an unseren KГғВјsten kГғВӨmpfen, wir werden an unseren Grenzen kГғВӨmpfen. Wir werden auf unseren Feldern und StraГғВҹen kГғВӨmpfen, und wenn es sein muss, auf jedem HГғВјgel und in jedem Tal Europas. Denn Europa ist unsere Heimat, und fГғВјr unsere Heimat werden wir uns wehren. Wir wollen keinen Krieg, aber wenn es sein muss, dann werden wir fГғВјr unsere Freiheit kГғВӨmpfen.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:47:09</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_81"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_352"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_353"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_203">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_203</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Atto normativo che era largamente atteso, non soltanto per ciГғВІ che ГғВЁ emerso all'indomani della pandemia, quando abbiamo scoperto come Europa che la gran parte della nostra produzione avveniva al di fuori dei 27 Paesi e quindi era difficile un approvvigionamento, soprattutto in momenti di difficoltГғВ .
Oggi c'ГғВЁ una questione molto importante che questo atto inizia ad affrontare ed ГғВЁ quella di rendere competitiva e di rendere realizzabile la produzione di medicinali, soprattutto generici, anche in Europa, mentre oggi sappiamo che la principale criticitГғВ  sta tutta qui: nel fatto che produrre il farmaco in Europa ГғВЁ diventato antieconomico.
E allora ГғВЁ un lavoro che inizia col Critical Medicines Act, ГғВЁ un lavoro che ГғВЁ stato preso dalla bussola della competitivitГғВ . Noi siamo ottimisti perchГғВ© ГғВЁ anche questa una questione di sovranitГғВ .</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:57:35</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_148"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_202"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_203"/>
  </rdf:Description>
