  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_8">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_8</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Costas Mavrides</del:name>
    <del:name>Nicola Procaccini,</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_356">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_356</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Marco Tarquinio</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_514">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_514</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Have we learned our lessons from the other so-called 'Arab Spring', which was nothing but the change from winter to winter in many Arab countries? We don't yet know. The outrage and violence last weekend show a different picture. We should align with international organisations, Commissioner. We should align with organisations important for us in Europe, especially in the field of border management, such as the UNODC.
We should also align with our strong partner in the region, Israel, which has taken care to ensure that the military threat from whatever regime will not increase but decrease, and which takes care of stability in the region, in the buffer zone there.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:19:48</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_212"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_513"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_514"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_268">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_268</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:40:48</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_199"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_267"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_268"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_133">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_133</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Neste processo, ficou patente que, quando chamado com urgГғВӘncia a pronunciar-se, o Parlamento Europeu estГғВЎ apto a responder, fazendo da solidariedade europeia a sua prioridade. E, enquanto codecisor, autoridade orГғВ§amental, estГғВЎ ГғВ  altura daquelas que sГғВЈo as suas atribuiГғВ§ГғВөes pelo Tratado ГўВҖВ” e continuarГғВЎ a estar, sem dГғВәvida, em todos os processos.
O Parlamento fez ainda ajustes importantes neste mecanismo, nomeadamente no aumento da taxa de prГғВ©-financiamento de 7ГӮВ % para 18ГӮВ % e na alteraГғВ§ГғВЈo da componente ГӮВ«subsГғВӯdioГӮВ» de 16ГӮВ % para 20,5ГӮВ %. Defendemos tambГғВ©m uma maior capacidade administrativa da MoldГғВЎvia e, por isso, temos mais financiamento dedicado ao fortalecimento das suas instituiГғВ§ГғВөes.
Por fim, o Parlamento tem ainda uma supervisГғВЈo reforГғВ§ada, num diГғВЎlogo entre o Parlamento e a ComissГғВЈo, para rever o progresso na implementaГғВ§ГғВЈo deste mecanismo.
Fica claro o nosso compromisso com o povo moldavo e o nosso empenho no percurso da MoldГғВЎvia rumo ГғВ  adesГғВЈo ГғВ  UniГғВЈo Europeia.</del:text>
    <del:text>Le droit ГғВ  lГўВҖВҷavortement est un droit fondamental. Des femmes comme Justyna se mettent en danger tous les jours pour lГўВҖВҷacquГғВ©rir, le prГғВ©server et le rГғВ©tablir. Pourtant, la Commission nГўВҖВҷa pas jugГғВ© bon dГўВҖВҷen faire mention dans sa feuille de route sur les droits des femmes. Nous ne le rГғВ©pГғВ©terons jamais assez: nos corps, nos choix. Je compte, Madame la Commissaire, sur vous pour dГғВ©fendre avec courage ce droit durant ce mandat, avec autant de courage que Justyna. Pour Justyna et toutes celles qui se battent chaque jour, merci!</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T20:33:05</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:26:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_100"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_97"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_132"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_133"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_274">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_274</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Antonio LГғВіpez-IstГғВәriz White</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_317">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_317</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ja, wer hat uns verraten? Die Christdemokraten. Die CDU stimmt hier mit den Sozialisten, Kommunisten und mit den GrГғВјnen, obwohl es rechts hier rechtskonservative Mehrheiten gibt. Und das ist Verrat am WГғВӨhler, mein lieber Kollege. Das will Merz in Deutschland genauso tun; da will man sogar das Grundgesetz ГғВӨndern wegen 800ГӮВ Milliarden neuer SchuldenГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ 300ГӮВ Milliarden fГғВјr Waffen, 500ГӮВ Milliarden, um die Infrastruktur waffenГўВҖВ‘ und panzertauglich zu machen. Sie wollen uns in den Krieg treiben. Das ist esГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ und das vГғВ¶llig illegal, denn Merz will das sogar mit dem alten, abgewГғВӨhlten Bundestag machen, weil er die Mehrheiten in dem neuen Bundestag gar nicht hat. Das ist wirklich verfassungswidrig. Es gibt da ГғВјberhaupt keine EilbedГғВјrftigkeit.
Die Menschen wollen keine Kriegstreiberei, die Menschen wollen Frieden. Weil das so ist, mГғВјssen Sie hier solche Spielchen spielen wie am Vormittag mit diesen NGOs. Deswegen bauen Sie hier Russland zu einem Feind auf. Von wegen Russland will uns angreifen; das ist doch vГғВ¶lliger Schwachsinn. Was will denn Russland, wenn sie uns hier besetzen? Wir haben doch gar nichts auГғВҹer Schulden ГўВҖВ“ 2,5ГӮВ Billionen Schulden. Meinen Sie, das russische Volk will das abzahlen fГғВјr uns? Und die 800ГӮВ Milliarden obendrauf? Sicher nicht.
(Die PrГғВӨsidentin entzieht dem Redner das Wort.)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:55:42</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_232"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_316"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_317"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_415">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_415</del:identifier>
    <del:text>They are therefore deemed to have been approved and have been published on the plenary webpage.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:56:42</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_406"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_415"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_126">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_126</del:identifier>
    <del:text>De discussie ging echter niet over deze kwesties, maar voortdurend over OekraГғВҜne, waarbij MoldaviГғВ« zelfs als frontlinie werd aangeduid. Daar kunnen ze zelf toch ook niet blij mee zijn.
Er is al forse financiГғВ«le steun gekoppeld aan het toetredingsproces, maar er is nog meer hulp nodig: twee miljard aan leningen en giften. De Europese Commissie heeft tegen de regels in geen risicoГўВҖВ‘inschatting gemaakt. De wensen van de Commissie begrotingscontrole, waaronder een onafhankelijke rekenkamer en transparantie inzake de bestedingen, werden afgewezen. Het gaat om heel veel geld, meer dan 10ГӮВ % van het bnp, dus kan een land dat ГғВјberhaupt verwerken?
Ik heb tegengestemd. Niet alleen vanwege het ontbreken van een analyse vooraf, het ontbreken van controle tijdens het proces en achteraf en het ontbreken van een overzicht van wie uiteindelijk het geld krijgt, maar omdat ik vind dat je voortgang in het toetredingsproces niet kunt kopen. Je onderschat de menselijke factor als je denkt met subsidies corruptie te bestrijden of het gevangeniswezen humaner te maken of de 45ГӮВ % tegenstemmers in MoldaviГғВ« ook enthousiast te maken voor de Unie. Straks zijn op papier alle maatregelen doorgevoerd, maar is er praktisch niets veranderd, behalve dan dat het land lid is.
Samenlevingen kunnen groeien naar een hoger niveau, maar dat gaat niet sneller als je dat aan de Europese Unie uitbesteedt. Ook niet voor twee miljard.</del:text>
    <del:text>This year is an important year for gender equality. The world marks the 30th anniversary of the Beijing Platform for Action, and the Commission sets out its vision for the next five years and its roadmap. But before looking forward, we should also look back with satisfaction at the legislation that was recently put in place, most of which resulted from the agreement between Council and Parliament.
We have improved pay transparency, helping to reduce the pay gap between women and men. We have introduced rules for improving the gender balance in company boards, bringing equality and diversity into corporate boardrooms. We have created minimum standards for equality bodies, giving victims of discrimination an ally in claiming their rights. And we have provided women in Europe the protection of the first ever directive on combating violence against women and domestic violence.
Through these and other achievements, we can surely say that the College administrators have delivered for Europe's women. Therefore, let me take this opportunity to thank the Parliament for tirelessly campaigning for women's rights and for its constructive partnership with the Council in this endeavour.
But the work is never over. There is still a gender pay gap that stands at almost 13ГӮВ %. There is still an employment gap of more than 10ГӮВ %, with women and girls still performing a disproportionate share of informal care tasks. And we must, in particular, address the disproportionate impact that armed conflict and economic crisis have on women and girls.
At times when some voices may try to reverse the progress we have made in the EU to promote and protect women's rights, we should concentrate our efforts on stepping up action and working with all partners to promote a model in our Union which is more inclusive and provides a more just society.
We will continue to do so through policy and legislative measures, as well as by tackling the root causes of inequality.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T20:20:31</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:09:04</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_93"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_2"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_125"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_126"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_159">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_159</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Vivimos en una UniГғВіn Europea donde mГғВЎs de 92 millones de personas siguen en riesgo de exclusiГғВіn o en riesgo de pobreza. No son simples cifras, son seres humanos y es una realidad que nos interpela y que tenemos que atender. Este Fondo Social Europeo Plus lo hace y ustedes estГғВЎn presentando enmiendas para restar las garantГғВӯas de los mГғВЎs vulnerables, de los niГғВұos, de las niГғВұas, de quienes nos necesitan. Nos estГғВЎn pidiendo que saquemos a esta infancia de la pobreza y ustedes quieren mГғВЎs armas. Desde luego, con esta actitud demuestran la Europa que quieren, y esta no es la que defendemos las personas progresistas que queremos una Europa igual para todas y todos.</del:text>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:09:42</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:58:54</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_119"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_20"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_158"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_159"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_276">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_276</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Mika Aaltola</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_390">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_390</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Europe must reclaim its own security. We are at the beginning of an important journey to develop a European army. Together we can turn our vision into reality, but this will require strong commitment from all of us.
This is not just about buying equipment. It's about coming together. We must address challenges with a united military force. We need to significantly expand our military capabilities. Yes, challenges will come, just as they did with introducing a common currency ГўВҖВ“ the euro. But today, the euro is a pillar of European stability. Tomorrow we have to add a European army.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:33:04</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_278"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_389"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_390"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_284">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_284</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:02:26</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_207"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_283"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_284"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_177">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_177</del:identifier>
    <del:text>A well-functioning business aviation industry helps attract investment to Europe, yet it was excluded from the Taxonomy Regulation. This omission is baffling. I urge the Commission to address this in the upcoming Omnibus initiatives.
Regarding sustainable fuels ГўВҖВ“ the so-called SAFs ГўВҖВ“ we need a globally standardised definition. The Commission must push for this. SAFs should also be available in sufficient quantities at all European airports, big and small.
Finally, I call on the Commission to actively support the development of electric vertical take-off and landing technology in Europe.</del:text>
    <del:text>Zum PrinzipГӮВ 1: Freiheit von genderbasierter Gewalt. Das Verbrechen der Vergewaltigung ist als EU-weiter Straftatbestand zu definieren; das muss sofort geschehen. OnlineГўВҖВ‘Gewalt ist aktiv zu bekГғВӨmpfen. Der DSA muss konsequent umgesetzt werden, und die Plattformen mГғВјssen in die Pflicht genommen werden, menschenverachtende Inhalte sofort zu lГғВ¶schen. Und die laufenden Verfahren mГғВјssen auch zГғВјgig abgeschlossen werden, auch wenn es sich um Riesenkonzerne handelt.
Zum PrinzipГӮВ 2: Zugang zu sexueller und reproduktiver Gesundheit. Das bedeutet auch das Recht auf sichere Abtreibung, auch das muss klar zum Ausdruck kommen.
Die PrinzipienГӮВ 3 bis 5: Gleichstellung am Arbeitsmarkt und Familienleben. Die LohntransparenzГўВҖВ‘Richtlinie muss in allen Mitgliedstaaten rasch umgesetzt werden, und Berufe, wo viele Frauen tГғВӨtig sind, wo hauptsГғВӨchlich Arbeit am Menschen geleistet wird, gehГғВ¶ren dringend aufgewertet. Wenn mehr Mittel fГғВјr die Verteidigung umgeschichtet werden, dann darf das nicht auf Kosten der Frauen gehen.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:35:43</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:21:31</del:timestamp>
