  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_387">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_387</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:30:08</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_386"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_387"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_471">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_471</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Let's be clear: we needed to get rid of Russian fossil fuels yesterday. An industry that can't be produced at home can't defend the home. Europe's supply chains for critical raw materials must be secured. We must utilise our key resources better and expand circularity. When it comes to regulation, we must finally build the single European energy market, supported by a free market economy, and ensure that our companies can keep up in the global competition. Weak industry means weak defence. Let us choose to scale up our sustainable industry for our autonomy, a strong economy and strong defence.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:14:58</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_338"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_470"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_471"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_525">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_525</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:35:36</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_524"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_525"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_44">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_44</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Kosma ZГ…ВӮotowski</del:name>
    <del:name>Jeroen Lenaers</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_170">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_170</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Liesbet Sommen</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_302">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_302</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Dario Tamburrano,</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_139">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_139</del:identifier>
    <del:text>However, Moldova still faces substantial external challenges. The ongoing threats from Russia, including the instability in the region of Transnistria, continue to jeopardise Moldova's sovereignty and European aspirations.
Despite these pressures, Moldova has remained determined, pushing forward with its reforms and advancing EU standards with unwavering resolve. And the growth facility is not just a financial tool, it is a clear message of our united support for Moldova.</del:text>
    <del:text>GwaГ…ВӮty towarzyszГ„В… wszystkim wojnom. W Rwandzie mГғВіwiono Г…ВјoГ…ВӮnierzom, Г…Вјe kobiety Tutsi inaczej smakujГ„В…. W czasie wojny na BaГ…ВӮkanach mГғВіwiono Г…ВјoГ…ВӮnierzom gwaГ…ВӮcicielom, Г…Вјe gwaГ…ВӮcГ„В…c muzuГ…ВӮmanki z BoГ…Вӣni, Г…ВӮamie siГ„Вҷ ich wartoГ…Вӣci. W Ukrainie gwaГ…ВӮt stanowi czГ„ВҷГ…ВӣГ„ВҮ rosyjskiej strategii militarnej. I mГғВіwiГ„Вҷ o tym dlatego i dzisiaj, poniewaГ…Вј naszym podstawowym zadaniem teraz, kiedy trwajГ„В… rozmowy pokojowe ГўВҖВ“ oczywiГ…Вӣcie musimy mГғВіwiГ„ВҮ o zwiГ„Вҷkszeniu pieniГ„Вҷdzy na wsparcie militarne, musimy mГғВіwiГ„ВҮ caГ…ВӮy czas o bezpieczeГ…В„stwie ГўВҖВ“ ale naszym zadaniem tutaj jest mГғВіwienie rГғВіwnieГ…Вј o sprawiedliwoГ…Вӣci dla ofiar potwornych zbrodni, tej strasznej wojny, ktГғВіra jest. I mam proГ…ВӣbГ„Вҷ do Pani Komisarz, aby przy rozmowach pokojowych nie tylko byГ…ВӮo wiГ„Вҷcej kobiet, ale rГғВіwnieГ…Вј kwestia sprawiedliwoГ…Вӣci, przemocy wobec kobiet byГ…ВӮa juГ…Вј teraz poruszana.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T20:41:49</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:33:46</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_106"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_102"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_138"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_139"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_71">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_71</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Victor Negrescu</del:name>
    <del:name>Dan Nica</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_153">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_153</del:identifier>
    <del:text>We have worked together. I would like to first and foremost thank my co-rapporteur Sven Mikser on behalf of the AFET Committee, but also the shadow rapporteurs that have worked closely with us. We have managed to reach a common agreement with the Council, which includes the top priorities of the European Parliament. As a result of our work, the support for Moldova will come fast and will come in a more comprehensive form.
I would like to thank Commissioner Kos and all colleagues from the Commission for acting really and truly as an honest broker. And I would also like to thank the Polish Presidency of the Council of the European Union, who understood the strategic importance of this file.
In these difficult times, when we are seeing that our common European values, that human rights, the democracy, that the rule of law are challenged by autocrats all around the world, we are giving a strong signal of unity. 27 Member States of the European Union stand by the side of a candidate country, understanding that supporting a candidate country, making it stronger, makes us stronger as well.
Thank you everyone following this positive debate, we are encouraged that tomorrow the planning of the European Parliament will give its final and positive vote by a large majority to this Reform and Growth Facility for the Republic of Moldova.</del:text>
    <del:text>Nevertheless, to my question: you don't see yourself as a threat to women's rights? Because I am so much more afraid of you and what you can do with your power here ГўВҖВ“ to my rights, to my girls' rights ГўВҖВ“ with your anti-gender approach and with your racist approach. Don't you consider yourself as a threat to us?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:00:41</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:51:10</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_86"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_104"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_152"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_153"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_482">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_482</del:identifier>
    <del:text>De industriГғВ«le ruggengraat van Europa, van onze familiebedrijven wordt gebogen onder bureaucratische en prijsballast. Voorzitter, technologieneutraliteit. De verbrandingsmotor verdient eerherstel. Het is tijd voor een fundamentele herziening van de Green Deal. Niet de realiteit moet zich aanpassen aan Brussel, maar Brussel moet zich aanpassen aan de gewijzigde realiteit.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:29:33</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_217"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_481"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_482"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_291">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_291</del:identifier>
    <del:text>MusГғВӯme pokraГ„ВҚovat v reformГғВЎch: pГ…ВҷГғВӯsnГ„ВӣjГ…ВЎГғВӯ kontrola vnГ„ВӣjГ…ВЎГғВӯch hranic, silnГғВҪ Frontex, efektivnГғВӯ pГ…ВҷeshraniГ„ВҚnГғВӯ spoluprГғВЎce a systГғВ©m, kterГғВҪ bude nejen naГ…Вҷizovat, ale i vykonГғВЎvat. A to si myslГғВӯm, Г…Вҫe musГғВӯme dГғВЎle dopracovat v dalГ…ВЎГғВӯm nГғВЎvrhu.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:11:00</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_214"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_290"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_291"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_491">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_491</del:identifier>
    <del:text>I really beg everyone who is speaking today to keep the time, because we are already very late.
And I announce directly at the beginning that we can just take five people for the catch-the-eye procedure. So we will open it shortly and then I will close it when we have five announced, because otherwise we will be here until midnight.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:38:17</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_14"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_484"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_491"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_334">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_334</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Jens Geier</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_279">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_279</del:identifier>
    <del:name>KlГғВЎra Dobrev</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_52">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_52</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Beatrice Timgren</del:name>
    <del:name>Christel Schaldemose</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_52">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_52</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Je vous imagine ГғВ  la Commission europГғВ©enne: la planГғВЁte est en train de cramer ГғВ  +ГӮВ 4ГӮВ ГӮВ°C, les multinationales continuent dГўВҖВҷengranger des profits en violant les droits de lГўВҖВҷhomme, et lГғВ  vous vous dites: ГӮВ«EurГғВӘka! DГғВ©barrassons-nous des seules rГғВ©gulations qui existent pour demander des comptes aux entreprises!ГӮВ»
Avec ce paquet ГӮВ«omnibusГӮВ», vous offrez un blanc-seing aux entreprises qui vont dГғВ©truire la planГғВЁte et exploiter les travailleurs. Vous jetez le devoir de vigilance des multinationales ГғВ  la poubelle, en limitant la responsabilitГғВ© aux seuls partenaires directs, trahissant son principe mГғВӘme, et en supprimant les sanctions financiГғВЁres. Tant pis si des entreprises comme Shein, Total ou Vinci continuent allГғВЁgrement de violer les droits de lГўВҖВҷhomme et de dГғВ©truire lГўВҖВҷenvironnement en toute impunitГғВ©.
Aussi longtemps que nous serons ici, vous pouvez compter sur mon groupe pour se battre afin de protГғВ©ger ces rГғВ©glementations et dГўВҖВҷempГғВӘcher les multinationales de faire leur loi et de gГғВ©nГғВ©rer des profits au dГғВ©triment de nos vies.</del:text>
    <del:text>This is the situation we are in today and it's a wake up call like never before for Europe, a wake up call that should not have been necessary. For years and years, we have been discussing the need for Europe to get serious about its own defence. Many European leaders have stood here in this room, passionately arguing the necessity of this.
So it's fair to ask exactly what we have achieved in all these years, and the clear answer is not enough. So in that sense, I really welcome the determination and the ambition shown by President von der Leyen and the European leaders last week. This ambition needs now to be translated into immediate and tangible European action.
Extraordinary circumstances ask for extraordinary measures, and we must be brave and bold not only to be able to help Ukraine, which is, of course, of crucial importance, but ultimately to help ourselves, because Ukraine's interests are Europe's interests, we are defending common European values. We are defending international law and the rules-based order. We are defending the very basic principle that the aggressor should not be rewarded at the expense of the victim.
Today, we must defend a future for our children in freedom and safety on our European continent.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:14:50</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:50:52</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_29"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_44"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_51"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_52"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_165">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_165</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Nikos Papandreou</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_5">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_5</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The corrigenda are available on the plenary webpage. Their titles will be published in the minutes of this sitting.</del:text>
    <del:text>On the other hand, what happened in the White House two weeks ago was simply a scandal. To say Ukraine is responsible for the war is simply a lie. And even with our long history, with our US friends in mind, we must call a lie a lie. No one can twist the truth. Putin doesn't want to end the war; he wants to end Ukraine. And as Europeans we will never allow this.
After the speech of Vice President Vance in Munich and what happened with Zelenskyy in the Oval Office, one reality is clear: dear friends, we are alone. The world is in turmoil. Europe has to wake up. We have to become responsible for ourselves. Our security is not in the hands of Washington or Moscow. It must be in our hands.
Since 1952, MadamГӮВ President ГўВҖВ“ the CommissionГӮВ President referred to this ГўВҖВ“ more than 70 years ago, we had the first idea of building up a defence union. I have to say, we wasted a lot of time in the last 70 years for discussing it endlessly. Last Thursday, putting EURГӮВ 800ГӮВ billion on the table to build up a European defence was an important step, showing that Europe finally takes its defence into its own hands. Money is in this regard a precondition, but is only the starting point of doing so. We need to go further.
The first point: we would save a lot of taxpayers' money if we act together. We have 17 tankГӮВ models in the European Union. The Americans only have one. We need standardisation. We need an obligatory common procurement. And we need to build up a true European market for defence goods, with all the further mergers in the industry side. This is not yet fully foreseen in the plan of Thursday.
Secondly, we need joint European projects, like a missile or drones defence system, especially in the east side of Europe; a cyber-defence brigade where everybody understands that cyber is not any more a national issue; a satellite surveillance system where we are not any more depending on US data. And every European citizen would immediately understand it's better to do these kinds of investments together.
I would love to see, then, parts of the troops with the European flags on their uniform. This is not yet foreseen in the plans of last Thursday.
Europe has to answer the offer of France to define the French nuclear shield as a kind of a European shield. This is not yet part of the plan of last Thursday.
Imagine for a second that Trump finally would invite Europe to go to the negotiation table to Saudi Arabia. Who would represent Europe then? Commission President? Council President? High Representative? Merz? Macron? Who would speak on behalf of Europe and on which basis could he or she then speak and act? Unanimity as a precondition for having a voice, then, in Saudi Arabia? Dear colleagues, that shows clearly we are ridiculous. We are not up to the task in this moment of time to give a proper answer. Kissinger said years ago, decades ago, 'Whom shall I call when I want to speak with Europe?' Let's be honest, he didn't give a proper answer on this until now.
Europe stands at a self-defining moment. Personally, I think we should once in the future elect the president of the European Union directly by the citizens of Europe. This is naive. This is a dream. Without dreamers, as Adenauer, DeГӮВ Gasperi, Schuman, VГғВЎclav Havel and WaГ…ВӮГ„Вҷsa, no one of us would sit today in this Chamber of the European Parliament.
The truth is that the plan of 1952 was more ambitious on a European spirit than what is on the table today. We need dreams that create hope and the determination to implement them. This method brought 70ГӮВ years of peace and then finally the reunification of the European Union 35ГӮВ years ago.
Finally, dear colleagues, because the purpose of the European defence union is to defend our democracy, even more democratic legitimacy of the process is needed. The Parliament must be fully involved. Bypassing the Parliament with Article 122 is a mistake. Europe's democracy stands on two pillars: it's the citizens and it's the Member States. We need both for our security.
Last Thursday was a great starting point, and I truly congratulate Ursula vonГӮВ derГӮВ Leyen and AntГғВіnio Costa for the strong message ГўВҖВ“ the will to invest into our defence and to our strength. But this can only be a starting point. The main task of our generation is to create a true European defence union. The European People's Party is ready to do so.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:06:09</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T09:21:04</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_4"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_4"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_5"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_77">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_77</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Voor onze bedrijven schiet het helemaal niet op. Zij zinken steeds verder weg in een oceaan van regels, formulieren en verplichtingen. Wat we echt nodig hebben, is niet een "omnibus", maar een kettingzaag. Massale deregulering, het afschaffen van overbodige EU-agentschappen, het mes in de ambtenarij: niet pappen en nat houden en procedures, maar snijden, schrappen en slopen.</del:text>
    <del:text>HovorГғВӯme o stovkГғВЎch miliГғВЎrd na zbrojenie ako spГғВҙsob, ktorГғВҪm pomГғВҙГ…Вҫeme aj Ukrajine, ale tej zaГ„ВҚГғВӯnajГғВә zГғВәfalo chГғВҪbaГ…ВҘ nie peniaze, nie zbrane, ale Г„Вҫudia. Ako chcete rieГ…ВЎiГ…ВҘ tento problГғВ©m? DeportГғВЎciou Ukrajincov z ГғВәzemia EurГғВіpskej ГғВәnie alebo nasadenГғВӯm naГ…ВЎich vojakov?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:01:17</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:26:51</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_51"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_67"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_76"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_77"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_14">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_14</del:identifier>
    <del:name>PredsedajГғВәci .</del:name>
    <del:name>Die PrГғВӨsidentin.</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_199">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_199</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Estrella GalГғВЎn</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_The_Left"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_99">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_99</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Dass jetzt hier in diesem Parlament so viel Kritik kommt, Frau Kommissarin, zeigt eigentlich, dass Sie relativ gut einen Mittelweg gefunden haben, der am Ende auch mehrheitsfГғВӨhig sein kann. Ich glaube, dass wir an einigen Stellen einfach auch noch Beispiele brauchen, die zeigen, dass das, was hier teilweise von Sozialdemokraten und GrГғВјnen vorgebracht wurde, einigermaГғВҹen fehl am Platz ist. Denn es geht nicht darum, zu deregulieren in breitem Stil.
Es geht darum, die Verantwortung bei den Unternehmen vor Ort zu belassen, die sich ja alle mit der Gesetzeslage auch selber konform erklГғВӨren mГғВјssen, aber darГғВјber eben kГғВјnftig nicht mehr jedes Jahr im Einzelnen berichten mГғВјssen. Das ist ein wichtiger Fortschritt, der viel zur Vereinfachung beitrГғВӨgt, der auch viel zu Vertrauen von Unternehmen wieder im Markt beitrГғВӨgt.
Und BГғВјrokratie bedeutet ja nichts anderes als Verwaltungsaufwand. Das Gesetz bedeutet nicht, dass nichtkonformes Handeln kГғВјnftig akzeptiert wГғВјrde, sondern es bedeutet, dass ГғВјber die Einhaltung der Gesetze nicht zusГғВӨtzlich berichtet werden mussГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ andere Staaten der Welt schaffen das auch. Deswegen sollten wir den Weg, den Mario Draghi in seinem Bericht durchaus klar vorgelegt hat, jetzt weiter konsequent verfolgen und zГғВјgig auf seine Umsetzung setzen. So kann Europa wieder wettbewerbsfГғВӨhig werden.</del:text>
    <del:text>First, peace without defence is an illusion. We need to invest more, better and faster in our own defence. It is what we are doing and we need to do more, to invest more, to invest together, to develop common projects for sure. Last week we made a decisive step, but not the last one. We need to continue and we will continue.
Second, defence is broader than ReArm. We need to invest in our strategic autonomy to reduce our dependencies on energy, to secure supply chains, to fight disinformation and protect the integrity of our democratic process and to keep our borders under control.
Third, the European Union and the Member States do not need to choose to invest in peace or to invest in health systems, education or housing. ReArm and the escape clause provide additional funds for defence. Strengthening our societies, protecting our citizens and boosting our economies is essential to strengthening our defence.
Fourth, this war is not only about Ukraine. In fact, this war is about international law: a rules-based international order. Protecting the universal values enshrined in the United Nations Charter ГўВҖВ“ sovereignty, territorial integrity, self-determination, respect of international recognised borders ГўВҖВ“ is essential in Ukraine, as it is essential in the Democratic Republic of the Congo, in the Kingdom of Denmark or in Cyprus. So we need to stand for the international law, because international law must be a must win this war.
A last remark: we need to invest more in diplomacy. We need to engage with partners around the world and widen a global network with, of course, our transatlantic partners and beyond ГўВҖВ“ by enlargement, by trade ГўВҖВ“ and stand for a multilateral system, and champion global causes like climate change, fighting poverty or engaging to develop the pact for the future.
These five remarks synthesise what we need to continue to do to ensure our security and to contribute to support for Ukraine for a comprehensive, just and lasting peace.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:30:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:55:31</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_70"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_7"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_98"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_99"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_230">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_230</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Korona-ajan alku paljasti heikkoutemme. Tarvittavat vГғВӨlineet olivat Kiinassa ja eurooppalaiset paniikissa. Sama ei saa enГғВӨГғВӨ toistua.
Kuten moneen muuhunkin asiaan, eurooppalaiset tehtaat ovat vastaus tГғВӨhГғВӨnkin. Vahva ja itsenГғВӨinen lГғВӨГғВӨketeollisuus, joka ei kuikuile itГғВӨГғВӨn taikka lГғВӨnteen. Euroopan ei pidГғВӨ olla maanosa, joka jГғВӨГғВӨ aina pahan paikan tullen odottelemaan apua. Se, jos mikГғВӨ, on heikkoutta.
Ja muistakaa, juuri nyt on tekojen hetki. Jos toimet aloitetaan seuraavan kriisin vyГғВ¶ryessГғВӨ pГғВӨГғВӨlle, silloin on jo myГғВ¶hГғВӨistГғВӨ.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:34:43</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_132"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_229"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_230"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_452">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_452</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Con 32 milioni di lavoratori diretti e il 65% delle attivitГғВ  di ricerca, l'industria genera innovazione e occupazione. Ma negli ultimi trent'anni la quota dell'industria sul PIL ГғВЁ diminuita di oltre cinque punti. Sono in gravissime difficoltГғВ  industrie come l'automotive, la chimica, l'acciaio ed altre ancora. Ci stiamo deindustrializzando.
In un mondo fortemente competitivo, incerto e con regole non uniformi, dobbiamo proporre soluzioni piГғВ№ favorevoli all'industria, ai lavoratori, ai cittadini.
Il Clean Industrial Deal ГғВЁ un segnale di cambiamento ma dobbiamo essere piГғВ№ ambiziosi: abbassare i costi dell'energia, eliminare la concorrenza sleale, tornare sui nostri passi quando le decisioni prese sono sbagliate.
Dobbiamo impegnarci di piГғВ№ per crescita e competitivitГғВ  per sostenere il nostro welfare, il migliore al mondo.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:50:42</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_323"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_451"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_452"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_382">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_382</del:identifier>
    <del:name>ГҺВқГҺВҜГҺВәГҺВҝГҸВӮ ГҺВ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҸВҖГҺВ¬ГҸВӮ</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_The_Left"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_245">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_245</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Without a functioning system on returns, the European migration system will never function properly. At the moment, only 20ГӮВ % of rejected asylum seekers are actually returned. This is not acceptable, and it undermines public support and trust in our migration policies. There is a need for a simple, fast and efficient returns directive, where mutual recognition of return decisions between Member States is essential. And there I see already ГўВҖВ“ with my critical eyes ГўВҖВ“ room for improvement, dear Commissioner.
Furthermore, rejected asylum seekers and the countries of origin must be required to cooperate with their return, and there should be consequences for those who do not. This requires intensive cooperation with these countries. We need agreements, Commissioner.
Let me be clear: the Renew Europe Group is adamant that human rights are always being taken into account. And from now on, in view of previous lessons learned, it's important that Parliament takes responsibility and works together.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:06:21</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_180"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_244"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_245"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_376">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_376</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Laat ons van deze crisis gebruikmaken, deze kans benutten, om het geld efficiГғВ«nt in te zetten, om het Europees in te zetten. Better together European. Dat moet het adagium zijn, anders is het een missed opportunity. We moeten het samen kunnen doen. De laatste Eurobarometer is duidelijk: de grootste zorg van de Europeanen is hun bescherming, is hun veiligheid. U heeft dus een stevig mandaat, niet alleen geld, maar u heeft een stevig mandaat om samen te werken aan die Europese defensie. Doe het nu. U heeft onze steun.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:16:07</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_270"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_375"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_376"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_230">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_230</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Reinier Van Lanschot,</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_7">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_7</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The dates are available on the plenary webpage and the deadlines are as follows: amendments, today at 7ГӮВ p.m.; roll-call votes, Tuesday, 11ГӮВ March at 4ГӮВ p.m. The vote will then take place on Wednesday, 12ГӮВ March at noon.
ГўВҒВӮ
I would like to inform the House that I have received multiple requests for points of order. I will go through them one by one.
First, I give the floor to MsГӮВ Iratxe GarcГғВӯa PГғВ©rez.</del:text>
    <del:text>La premiГғВЁre, la plus urgente, se construira par la diplomatie. LГўВҖВҷorganisation dГўВҖВҷun sommet de la famille occidentale, idГғВ©e formulГғВ©e par la PremiГғВЁre ministre italienne, GiorgiaГӮВ Meloni, devrait nous permettre de dГғВ©finir clairement nos objectifs pour la souverainetГғВ© de lГўВҖВҷUkraine, les exigences que nous devons mettre sur la table et les garanties de sГғВ©curitГғВ© ГғВ  offrir ГғВ  ce pays alliГғВ©, afin quГўВҖВҷil ne subisse plus jamais les assauts de lГўВҖВҷagresseur russe.
La deuxiГғВЁme boussole, ГғВ  plus long terme, est de bГғВўtir lГўВҖВҷautonomie des nations dГўВҖВҷEurope, pour faire en sorte que personne dГўВҖВҷautre que nous ne dГғВ©termine nos intГғВ©rГғВӘts et les conditions de notre sГғВ©curitГғВ©. Si elle est capable de repenser une diplomatie libre et indГғВ©pendante, la France peut redevenir la force dГўВҖВҷentraГғВ®nement du continent et lГўВҖВҷinterlocutrice ГғВ©vidente et naturelle de ce nouveau monde, parce que la France est dotГғВ©e dГўВҖВҷune armГғВ©e de mГғВ©tier reconnue, dГўВҖВҷune base industrielle dГўВҖВҷexception, dГўВҖВҷun siГғВЁge permanent au Conseil de sГғВ©curitГғВ© de lГўВҖВҷONU, de la dissuasion nuclГғВ©aire et, bien sГғВ»r, parce quГўВҖВҷelle est lГўВҖВҷhГғВ©ritiГғВЁre dГўВҖВҷun pacte vingt fois sГғВ©culaire entre la grandeur dГўВҖВҷune nation et la libertГғВ© du monde.
Madame von der Leyen, permettez-moi de vous dire que tous vos choix politiques se sont, hГғВ©las, fracassГғВ©s sur le mur du rГғВ©el. Avec le pacte vert, vous avez optГғВ© pour la dГғВ©croissance, alors quГўВҖВҷil fallait produire sans entrave. Vous avez dГғВ©savouГғВ© le nuclГғВ©aire, optГғВ© pour lГўВҖВҷinflation de normes et de taxes, et encouragГғВ© les achats de matГғВ©riel amГғВ©ricain plutГғВҙt que dГўВҖВҷappliquer la prГғВ©fГғВ©rence europГғВ©enne en matiГғВЁre de dГғВ©fense. Ce nГўВҖВҷest quГўВҖВҷau prix de changements dГўВҖВҷorientation profonds que lГўВҖВҷEurope restera une actrice de lГўВҖВҷhistoire, dissuadera les menaces et imposera le respect aux empires.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:07:20</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T09:31:13</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_6"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_6"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_7"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_247">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_247</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Hablemos claro: usted estГғВЎ hablando de retornos, pero es un eufemismo, porque lo que estamos haciendo es dar vГғВӯa libre a las expulsiones forzadas. Hoy se estГғВЎ dando un paso mГғВЎs debilitando las obligaciones internacionales que la UniГғВіn Europea tiene para garantizar los derechos humanos.
Son varias las razones por las que esta propuesta es inaceptable. En primer lugar, porque es anacrГғВіnica y no tiene en cuenta las aportaciones positivas de las personas migrantes ni tampoco el millГғВіn de personas al aГғВұo que, segГғВәn la propia ComisiГғВіn ha dictaminado, necesitamos para mantener nuestro Estado de bienestar. ГӮВҝPor quГғВ© van ustedes en contra de los intereses de la UniГғВіn Europea?
En segundo lugar, porque es inoperativa, pues estГғВЎn demostrados la ineficiencia y el coste desproporcionado de las expulsionesГӮВ frente a opciones de regularizar y dar derechos. Y, en tercer lugar, es cruel, porque externaliza las violaciones de derechos humanos generando GuantГғВЎnamos en paГғВӯses fuera de la UniГғВіn Europea...</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:09:09</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_182"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_246"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_247"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_326">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_326</del:identifier>
    <del:name>JГғВјri Ratas</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_87">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_87</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Tel le fasciste argentin JavierГӮВ Milei ГўВҖВ“ГӮВ et sa tronГғВ§onneuseГӮВ ГўВҖВ“, vous dГғВ©tricotez mГғВ©thodiquement le pacte vert. La taxonomie verte europГғВ©enne? Dehors. Le devoir de vigilance? Dehors. LГўВҖВҷobligation de transparence sur la durabilitГғВ© des entreprises? Dehors. LГўВҖВҷajustement carbone aux frontiГғВЁres? Dehors. Vous donnez carte blanche ГғВ  Shein, ГғВ  Lactalis et ГғВ  TotalEnergies pour polluer et maltraiter leurs salariГғВ©s ГғВ  loisir, en Europe comme ГғВ  lГўВҖВҷГғВ©tranger. La simplification, cГўВҖВҷest lГўВҖВҷalibi des multinationales pour massacrer les droits sociaux et environnementaux. Vous pensez ГғВ  leur argent; nous pensons aux vivants. Vous ГғВӘtes avec les puissants; nous sommes avec les gens.</del:text>
    <del:text>OtГғВіГ…Вј, choГ„ВҮ wiem, Г…Вјe jeszcze na tej sali sГ„В… osoby, ktГғВіre by chciaГ…ВӮy robiГ„ВҮ interesy z Putinem ГўВҖВ“ choГ„ВҮ ich jest coraz mniej na szczГ„ВҷГ…Вӣcie ГўВҖВ“ i szerzГ„В… tutaj rosyjskГ„В… propagandГ„Вҷ, m.in. to, co mГғВіwi Russia Today, to jest najwyГ…Вјszy czas, Г…Вјeby powiedzieГ„ВҮ stop i doГ…ВӣГ„ВҮ. DoГ…ВӣГ„ВҮ juГ…Вј tego. My dzisiaj musimy zbudowaГ„ВҮ europejskГ„В… polisГ„Вҷ ubezpieczeniowГ„В… i Г…Вјeby tak byГ…ВӮo, musimy zainwestowaГ„ВҮ ogromne pieniГ„В…dze w uzbrojenie. I ten plan Komisji Europejskiej, Г…Вјeby wydaГ„ВҮ do oГ…Вӣmiuset miliardГғВіw euro wГ…ВӮaГ…Вӣnie na uzbrojenie jest bardzo dobrym pomysГ…ВӮem, tylko musimy to zrobiГ„ВҮ szybko, bez debat, bez konsultacji, bez rocznych dyskusji. Po prostu musimy to zrobiГ„ВҮ zaraz, bo my nie mamy czasu.
I chcГ„Вҷ powiedzieГ„ВҮ jeszcze jednГ„В… rzecz. Polska chce przenieГ…ВӣГ„ВҮ z KPO, z krajowego planu odbudowy prawie 30 mld zГ…ВӮ na to, Г…Вјeby wГ…ВӮaГ…Вӣnie zainwestowaГ„ВҮ w uzbrojenie, bo bezpieczeГ…В„stwo dla Europy jest dzisiaj najwaГ…Вјniejsze.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:15:16</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:38:23</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_60"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_75"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_86"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_87"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_539">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_539</del:identifier>
    <del:text>En Palestina, una espiral de violencia ha terminado con el respeto a los derechos humanos y en el vГғВіrtice de esa violencia estГғВЎ la ocupaciГғВіn ilegal de Palestina por parte de Israel, que tiene en vigor un sistema deГӮВ apartheid polГғВӯtico que trata a los palestinos como infrahumanos sin derechos.
Denunciamos el genocidio de 60ГӮВ 000 personas en Gaza y ahora debemos exponer las condiciones inhumanas de vida en la zona, los cortes de luz y agua y la ausencia de atenciГғВіn sanitaria. Israel no atiende a razones porque no es un paГғВӯs democrГғВЎtico, pero la UniГғВіn Europea debe exigirle que se permita la entrada del OOPS, de la ayuda humanitaria y de todo tipo de suministros y que cumpla con sus compromisos de alto el fuego.
SeГғВұora comisaria, a estas alturas seguir manteniendo en vigor el Acuerdo de AsociaciГғВіn con Israel no es negligencia, es colaboracionismo con crГғВӯmenes de guerra. EstГғВЎn hundiendo el prestigio reputacional internacional de la UniГғВіn Europea. No en nuestro nombre.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T23:00:13</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_376"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_538"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_539"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_259">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_259</del:identifier>
    <del:text>DovoГ„Вҫte eГ…ВЎte zdГғВҙrazniГ…ВҘ, Г…Вҫe solidГғВЎrny mechanizmus EГғВҡ v oblasti migrГғВЎcie bol odmietnutГғВҪ viacerГғВҪmi krajinami a Г…Вҫe mechanizmus je navyГ…ВЎe evidentne nespravodlivГғВҪ, pretoГ…Вҫe nezohГ„ВҫadГ…ВҲuje enormnГғВә zГғВЎГ…ВҘaГ…Вҫ krajГғВӯn, ako je Slovensko, MaГ„ВҸarsko, Rumunsko Г„ВҚi PoГ„Вҫsko, ktorГғВ© uГ…Вҫ prijali miliГғВіny uteГ„ВҚencov z Ukrajiny. SlovenskГғВҪ predseda vlГғВЎdy Robert Fico uГ…Вҫ desaГ…ВҘ rokov upozorГ…ВҲuje na tieto problГғВ©my a opakovane volГғВЎ po zГғВЎkladnej reforme eurГғВіpskej nГғВЎvratovej politiky. Preto vГғВӯtame zmenu prГғВӯstupu EurГғВіpskej komisie a drГ…ВҫГғВӯme vГғВЎm palce, aby sa vГғВЎm to podarilo.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:27:22</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_191"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_258"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_259"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_204">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_204</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Spitalele din Satu Mare din RomГғВўnia s-au confruntat de curГғВўnd cu lipsa hidrocortizonului. De asemenea, lipsesc ГғВ®n continuare multe medicamente antiepileptice, ГғВ®n special pentru copii ГҲВҷi nu numai. AceastГ„Вғ lege propune independenГҲВӣГ„Вғ strategicГ„Вғ, coordonare a politicilor de stocuri, producГҲВӣie europeanГ„Вғ ГҲВҷi achiziГҲВӣii coordonate ГҲВҷi poate, ГғВ®ntr-adevГ„Вғr, sГ„Вғ scadГ„Вғ dependenГҲВӣa de lanГҲВӣurile de aprovizionare globale ГҲВҷi sГ„Вғ creascГ„Вғ accesul europenilor la medicamente. TotuГҲВҷi, fГ„ВғrГ„Вғ mecanisme clare de implementare, bugete adecvate ГҲВҷi sancГҲВӣiuni pentru nerespectarea obligaГҲВӣiilor, acest act riscГ„Вғ sГ„Вғ rГ„ВғmГғВўnГ„Вғ doar o declaraГҲВӣie de intenГҲВӣie.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:58:59</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_149"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_203"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_204"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_102">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_102</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Es insostenible seguir lastrando de esta manera nuestra competitividad en un momento en el que necesitamos, mГғВЎs que nunca, competir en un mundo cada vez mГғВЎs complejo e inseguro. Y la ComisiГғВіn hace bien rectificando el camino; sin embargo, nuestras empresas ya han invertido millones para adaptarse a la normativa sobre divulgaciГғВіn de informaciГғВіn no financieraГӮВ y ahora se preguntan cuГғВЎnto mГғВЎs tienen que reinvertir para readaptarse de nuevo.
Por ello es vital no retrasar, sino congelar, la aplicaciГғВіn de estas reglas y trabajar en una nueva norma que sea seria, que dГғВ© certidumbre y seguridad a nuestros sectores productivos, que favorezca la creaciГғВіn de un ecosistema europeo de pequeГғВұas y medianas empresas y empresas emergentes,ГӮВ que permita la atracciГғВіn y la retenciГғВіn del talento y que permita innovar.
Competir no es una opciГғВіn, por mucho que los socialistas y los verdes digan lo contrario: es una necesidad para mantener nuestro Estado de bienestar y hoy, mГғВЎs que nunca, nuestra seguridad.
Pero toda revisiГғВіn ha de hacerse con cabeza y evaluando su impacto. Si no, por muchas BrГғВәjulas que aprobemos, seguiremos perdidos buscando el norte.</del:text>
    <del:text>Today we pay tribute to the courageous women across Europe who are standing up for the values so many of us far too often take for granted. Women who embody the spirit of courage, defiance and the audacity to believe in a better world, who are on the front lines of the struggle for a future of freedom, who are putting everything on the line as they refuse to give up on what they believe in: Sviatlana Tsikhanouskaya, leader of the democratic forces of Belarus; Palina Sharenda-Panasiuk, a former political prisoner in Belarus; Leniie Umerova, a former political prisoner from Crimea, and Tata Kepler, a Ukrainian medical volunteer and activist.
Dear friends, dear ladies, your brave actions are an inspiration to this House and to all who cherish liberty everywhere. Thank you for being an example for girls and boys across Europe and the world. Thank you.
(Applause)
In Ukraine today, hundreds of women and men are fighting every day for that dream of peace and freedom. We know their sacrifice and we honour what they stand for.
In Belarus, too many women and men are arbitrarily imprisoned and denied their rights under the boot of dictatorship. We know what they have given up and their plight is not forgotten.
So Sviatlana, Palina, Leniie, Tata, thank you. This House thanks you. Europe thanks you. I now pass the floor to my friend and a force that the world needs to hear more of, Sviatlana Tsikhanouskaya.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:36:05</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T12:13:00</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_73"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_101"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_102"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_100"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_148">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_148</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:text>Wenn die EUГўВҖВ‘Kommissare von Gleichheit zwischen MГғВӨnnern und Frauen sprechen, dann verdrehen sie die EUГўВҖВ‘VertrГғВӨge in ihr Gegenteil. Zu dieser Rechtsverdrehung gesellt sich dann auch noch eine Tatsachenverdrehung, denn MГғВӨnner und Frauen sind nun mal nicht gleich. Frauen kГғВ¶nnen Kinder gebГғВӨren und MГғВӨnner eben nicht. Jedes Kindergartenkind kann den Unterschied zwischen einem Mann und einer Frau mit bloГғВҹem Auge erkennen. Das ist eine Anerkennung, die Sie hier aber beharrlich verweigern.
Wenn man von falschen Ideen und falschen Tatsachen ausgeht, dann kann natГғВјrlich auch eine Roadmap fГғВјr Frauenrechte nur falsch sein. Diese gehГғВ¶rt als Desinformation in die Tonne gekloppt, samt der unsГғВӨglichen GenderГўВҖВ‘Ideologie. Halten Sie sich doch einfach aus dem Leben von uns Frauen heraus! Damit wГғВӨre uns am meisten geholfen.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T20:53:52</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:43:23</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_115"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_108"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_147"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_148"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_237">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_237</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Sarah Knafo</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ESN"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_111">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_111</del:identifier>
    <del:text>ГҲВҳi, doamna comisarГ„Вғ, suprareglementarea poate sГ„Вғ ducГ„Вғ la ГҲВҷtergerea locurilor de muncГ„Вғ. Trebuie sГ„Вғ ГғВ®nГҲВӣelegem, am lucrat mult mai mult ГғВ®n economie, ГғВ®n industrie decГғВўt ГғВ®n politicГ„Вғ, trebuie sГ„Вғ ГғВ®nГҲВӣelegem cГ„Вғ trebuie sГ„Вғ tratГ„Вғm la pachet drepturile lucrГ„Вғtorilor, cu condiГҲВӣii pentru IMM-uri, mai ales, ГҲВҷi pentru companii, pentru cГ„Вғ doar companiile creeazГ„Вғ locuri de muncГ„Вғ ГҲВҷi dacГ„Вғ reglementГ„Вғm, suprareglementГ„Вғm, pot sГ„Вғ se erodeze aceste locuri de muncГ„Вғ.
Dar ГҲВҷi dacГ„Вғ dereglementГ„Вғm, putem sГ„Вғ ajungem pe termen lung sГ„Вғ erodГ„Вғm locurile de muncГ„Вғ.
De aceea trebuie o analizГ„Вғ foarte bunГ„Вғ, ГҲВҷi poate vina cea mai mare pe care o are Uniunea EuropeanГ„Вғ, Comisia EuropeanГ„Вғ, este aceea cГ„Вғ se fac reglementГ„Вғri care se bat cap ГғВ®n cap. ГҲВҳi un agricultor, un fermier, o IMM nu mai ГҲВҷtie ce sГ„Вғ facГ„Вғ ГғВ®n momentul ГғВ®n care apar ГғВ®n conflict aceste legislaГҲВӣii.
De aceea, trebuie cu foarte mare atenГҲВӣie sГ„Вғ analizГ„Вғm ce dereglementГ„Вғm ГҲВҷi mai ales, sГ„Вғ nu mai adГ„ВғugГ„Вғm birocraГҲВӣie care nu aduce nimic, nici competitivitate, nici siguranГҲВӣa locului de muncГ„Вғ, nici sustenabilitate, nici posibilitatea companiilor de a mГ„Вғri salariile.</del:text>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:50:10</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T12:54:16</del:timestamp>
