  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_429">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_429</del:identifier>
    <del:text>VyzГғВҪvГғВЎm proto Komisi, aby prioritnГ„Вӣ Г…ВҷeГ…ВЎila problГғВ©m zvanГғВҪ ETS. ETS1 musГғВӯ bГғВҪt pГ…ВҷedvГғВӯdatelnГ„ВӣjГ…ВЎГғВӯ a ETS2 musГғВӯ bГғВҪt minimГғВЎlnГ„Вӣ o dva roky odloГ…Вҫena. Co ale potГ…Вҷebujeme nejvГғВӯce, je levnГғВЎ energie pro naГ…ВЎe firmy. UvidГғВӯme, jak budou vypadat konkrГғВ©tnГғВӯ legislativnГғВӯ nГғВЎvrhy, ale zatГғВӯm dohodu o Г„ВҚistГғВ©m prГ…ВҜmyslu hodnotГғВӯm jako hodnГ„Вӣ promarnГ„Вӣnou pГ…ВҷГғВӯleГ…Вҫitost.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:20:48</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_306"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_428"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_429"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_254">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_254</del:identifier>
    <del:name>ГҺВқГҺВ№ГҺВәГҸВҢГҺВ»ГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҺВҰГҺВұГҸВҒГҺВұГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВҚГҸВҒГҺВ·ГҸВӮ</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_The_Left"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_349">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_349</del:identifier>
    <del:text>NemГғВЎme desiatky rokov, moГ…Вҫno mГғВЎme mesiace, aby sme vytvorili spoloГ„ВҚnГғВә obranu, ktorГғВЎ Rusko odstraГ…ВЎГғВӯ, ale presne o tom odstraГ…ВЎenГғВӯ je tГғВЎto debata. O asertГғВӯvnosti a o naГ…ВЎej jednote. A o tom by mala byГ…ВҘ aj debata o bielej knihe. ГғВҒno, bude nГғВЎs to nieГ„ВҚo stГғВЎГ…ВҘ, ale bude to cena prevencie a udrГ…ВҫateГ„ВҫnГғВ©ho mieru urГ„ВҚite niГ…ВҫГ…ВЎia ako cena vojny. A aby zvГғВҪГ…ВЎenГғВ© nГғВЎklady nepadli na tГғВҪch najbliГ…ВҫГ…ВЎГғВӯch, na to mГғВЎme v EurГғВіpskej ГғВәnii a v Г„ВҚlenskГғВҪch Г…ВЎtГғВЎtoch nГғВЎstroje.
TakГ…Вҫe vГ„ВҚera bolo neskoro. My sa musГғВӯme poistiГ…ВҘ a investГғВӯcia do spoloГ„ВҚnej bezpeГ„ВҚnosti je naГ…ВЎou poistkou. EurГғВіpa sa musГғВӯ brГғВЎniГ…ВҘ.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:42:42</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_121"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_348"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_349"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_308">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_308</del:identifier>
    <del:text>As I said, the direction of travel is clear: a Europe with more responsibility for its defence ГўВҖВ“ the pace of our work is clearly accelerating towards that aim. Indeed, the European Council, at its special meeting on 6ГӮВ March, marked an important moment in this context. As we have discussed this morning, leaders held a first discussion on the ReArm Europe plan set out by the President of the Commission and provided guidance for future EU actions. Let me briefly summarise how the Council of the European Union is working on boosting Europe's defence readiness.
We must strive for a stronger and more capable Union in the field of security and defence. Work in the Council takes place along five main priorities for EU security and defence. Firstly, we must spend more and better, and strengthen our defence, technological and industrial base. Deliberations are ongoing towards a Council general approach on the regulation establishing a European defence industry programme. We are looking forward to negotiations with Parliament. The Council is also currently conducting a strategic review of the Permanent Structured Cooperation, which will result in a revision of its legal framework.
Secondly, the EU must continue its unwavering support for Ukraine's independence, sovereignty and its territorial integrity. We must use all of our financial regulatory power to provide financial and military aid as long as it takes.
Thirdly, we need to increase the EU's ability to act, notably by effectively using both military and civilian means in a joined up manner. Efforts to operationalise the EU rapid development capacity are well underway, and military exercises will continue in 2025, increasing the EU's ability to act.
Fourthly, we must strengthen the EU's resilience and security, its access to strategic environments such as the space, maritime and air domains. To secure our access to these domains, we have agreed on strategies on cyber defence and space, and we updated the EU maritime security strategy. In OctoberГӮВ 2024, the Council approved the first ever EU cyber census, which tracks our progress in implementing the EU policy on cyber defence.
Finally, the EU should continue to strengthen and expand tailored and mutually beneficial partnerships with bilateral and multilateral partners. We stepped up political dialogue with NATO and we have also concluded a security and defence partnership with six key partners and more will follow. We must also preserve our transatlantic bonds. The step undertaken recently by the US administration may worry us, but this is our existential interest and we should keep it above the current political developments.
These are the basic aspects of what the Council considers as the priorities for developing the EU's defence capacities. We look forward to examining how these priorities are addressed in the upcoming white paper. To conclude, let me reaffirm that we are committed to building a safe and secure Europe with the same determination and a great sense of urgency. There is still a lot of work ahead of us.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:27:52</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_2"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_307"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_308"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_71">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_71</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:text>But, as you are from the Socialist Party from Spain, just a very small, tiny question: what is your opinion on why Spain has provided so little help to Ukraine currently? Because when you look at the GDP, the real help ГўВҖВ“ military aid ГўВҖВ“ it has given to Ukraine, it's almost nothing compared to Poland, Estonia, Denmark, Finland and so on. So, why is there so much talk and no actions? What is the problem in Spain with the Socialists? Why are you not acting?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:53:46</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:18:50</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_46"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_62"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_70"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_71"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_50">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_50</del:identifier>
    <del:name>CГғВ©sar Luena</del:name>
    <del:name>Kathleen Funchion</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_The_Left"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_226">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_226</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Conhecemos, nos nossos paГғВӯses, a experiГғВӘncia da rutura de medicamentos vitais (como anestГғВ©sicos, antibiГғВіticos, mesmo insulina), como conhecemos o diagnГғВіstico das nossas fragilidades: dependГғВӘncia de menos de um punhado de origens geogrГғВЎficas em matГғВ©riasГўВҖВ‘primas e erosГғВЈo da base industrial europeia.
A nossa aГғВ§ГғВЈo ГғВ© urgente porque os resultados exigem tempo, e as respostas legislativas sГғВЈo mesmo a parte mais fГғВЎcil daquilo que precisamos de fazer. Sim, precisamos de uma lista de medicamentos crГғВӯticos, de stocks de contingГғВӘncia, de novas prГғВЎticas de aprovisionamento pГғВәblico. Precisamos mesmo de investir no fabrico europeu.
Mas nГғВЈo basta. Precisamos de reconhecer que apenas com uma coordenaГғВ§ГғВЈo e investimento europeus comuns poderemos ser bemГўВҖВ‘sucedidos nesta estratГғВ©gia, e que a disponibilidade de medicamentos no mercado nГғВЈo serve os cidadГғВЈos europeus, se o acesso, sob o ponto de vista da comportabilidade financeira, estiver em causa.
Sim, precisamos tambГғВ©m de falar do preГғВ§o dos medicamentos, e estes sГғВЈo aspetos dos quais nГғВЈo vamos desistir.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:29:13</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_73"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_225"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_226"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_321">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_321</del:identifier>
    <del:text>PerchГғВ©, chi ГғВЁ il nemico? E quali sarebbero gli scenari strategici? PerchГғВ© se il nemico ГғВЁ la Russia, la Russia spende in termini assoluti, in difesa, due volte e mezzo in meno di quanto non spenda l'Unione europea e ha un PIL piГғВ№ basso dell'Italia ed ГғВЁ un nono di quello dell'Unione europea ed ha una popolazione che ГғВЁ un terzo di quella dell'Unione europea ed ha una capacitГғВ  industriale che ГғВЁ ridicola di fronte alla capacitГғВ  industriale del Vecchio continente.
Ma come: negli ultimi tre anni ci avete dipinto una Russia infognata nel Donbass e che perde di fronte a un modesto avversario come l'Ucraina e oggi ce la volete dipingere come il nemico dell'intera Unione europea? Fate pace con il cervello.
La realtГғВ  ГғВЁ che Bruxelles vuole ingoiare la sovranitГғВ  nazionale con la scusa e il pretesto della difesa comune. Quello di cui abbiamo bisogno sono nazioni forti con eserciti....
(La Presidente toglie la parola all'oratore)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:03:10</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_46"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_320"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_321"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_313">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_313</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Martin HojsГғВӯk</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Renew"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_512">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_512</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Il Paese rimane instabile: i diritti non sono garantiti, come dimostrano anche le esecuzioni sommarie dei cittadini alawiti sulla costa occidentale, negli ultimi giorni. Vogliamo sperare che le parole della nuova leadership siriana sull'inclusione delle minoranze e delle donne non siano soltanto parole.
L'Europa ha il dovere di ascoltare e proteggere il popolo siriano, tutto: le organizzazioni della societГғВ  civile, le diverse confessioni religiose, quello straordinario esperimento che ГғВЁ il confederalismo del Rojava, fondato su democrazia, ecologia e femminismo.
Ci auguriamo che il vertice sul futuro della Siria possa andare in questa direzione. Purtroppo, lo scarso coinvolgimento della societГғВ  civile non ГғВЁ un bel segnale. Rimane cruciale, nel breve termine, l'impegno di garantire aiuti umanitari alla popolazione e il sostegno. nel lungo periodo. a un percorso veramente democratico e inclusivo per il futuro della Siria.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:17:22</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_198"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_511"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_512"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_174">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_174</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Pasti mora skrajno nedemokratiГ„ВҚni cordon sanitaire. In nedopustna je zloraba pravosodja, da se nekomu onemogoГ„ВҚi kandidaturo na volitvah. Potrebujemo popolno svobodo govora in spoГ…ВЎtovanje volilnih odloГ„ВҚitev ljudstva.
Potrebujemo vrnitev k pravim vrednotam. To so krГ…ВЎГ„ВҚanske vrednote. Bog vas Г…Вҫivi, Bog Г…Вҫivi Evropo. Bog Г…Вҫivi mojo domovino, Slovenijo.</del:text>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:31:54</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:17:02</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_126"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_173"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_174"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_285">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_285</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Rasmus Andresen</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Verts_ALE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_37">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_37</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Antonella Sberna</del:name>
    <del:name>Anders Vistisen</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PfE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_397">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_397</del:identifier>
    <del:text>To that, I would say common defence makes common sense, that security requires more than a Commission proposal and a Council consent, but a strong common effort to build a strong European industry, from steel to chemicals, from raw materials to weapons, and from food to space technology.
Above all else, it requires real unity, a grand political coalition of pro-Europeans crossing national and ideological lines, leaving the cultural wars behind and building consensus around universally accepted European values and interests.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:42:34</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_284"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_396"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_397"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_68">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_68</del:identifier>
    <del:text>La Commission prГғВ©tend simplifier, mais elle ne fait quГўВҖВҷexempter temporairement certaines entreprises de rГғВ©glementations excessives, sans remettre en cause la logique bureaucratique qui les sous-tend. Qui peut croire que lГўВҖВҷon sauvera lГўВҖВҷindustrie europГғВ©enne avec des formulaires? LГўВҖВҷГӮВ«omnibusГӮВ» ne change rien au fond du problГғВЁme. Ce problГғВЁme, cГўВҖВҷest la surrГғВ©glementation structurelle, qui asphyxie notre ГғВ©conomie. AujourdГўВҖВҷhui, la mise en conformitГғВ© coГғВ»te 3 ГғВ  4ГӮВ % du PIB, et une entreprise europГғВ©enne dГғВ©pense 2,5ГӮВ fois plus en formalitГғВ©s quГўВҖВҷune entreprise amГғВ©ricaine. LГўВҖВҷГғВ©lГғВ©phant dans la piГғВЁce, cГўВҖВҷest ce bloc de rГғВ©glementations vertes, qui nous prive de croissance. Tant que nous ne remettrons pas ГғВ  plat cette machine bureaucratique, ces ajustements resteront anecdotiques.</del:text>
    <del:text>Meinen Sie mit dem Herzen Europas das, was Ihre Fraktionskollegen von der CDU zu verantworten haben, dass es zu Massenvergewaltigungen in Deutschland kommt, dass es zu Terror in Deutschland kommt? Wollen Sie, dass das auch in Ungarn stattfindet? Glauben Sie, dass das der Punkt ist, wo Sie sagen, dass das Herz Europas Sie dahin zurГғВјckfГғВјhrt?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:49:54</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:15:32</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_43"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_60"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_67"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_68"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem28">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Topic"/>
    <del:identifier>creitem28</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Closure of the sitting</del:name>
    <skos:broader rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem22"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_545">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_545</del:identifier>
    <del:text>I believe the EU should push for a twoГўВҖВ‘state solution and challenge its biggest ally. Now, more than ever, we should act independently from the United States in order to stop the genocide of Palestinians and finally achieve a twoГўВҖВ‘state solution.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T23:08:02</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_378"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_544"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_545"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_319">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_319</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Mariateresa Vivaldini</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_334">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_334</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ten tweede, commissaris, maakt u gebruik van artikelГӮВ 122 van het Verdrag om het Parlement buitenspel te zetten. Van mij mag het, maar dat gaat de kwaliteit niet verbeteren. Een goed Europees defensiebeleid voer je niet in achterkamertjes.
Ten derde, commissaris, komt u volgende week met een witboek. Ik hoop dat het duidelijker en concreter is dan u vandaag bent geweest. Er moeten echt grote Europese programmaГўВҖВҷs in staan en een routekaart voor een Europees leger. Ook dit zeg ik hier al tien jaar. U wilt de geschiedenis ingaan? Wel, commissaris, maak die routekaart voor dat Europees leger, of u mist de afspraak met de geschiedenis.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:22:28</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_78"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_333"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_334"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_209">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_209</del:identifier>
    <del:text>We remember from the last big crisis that we had a problem that some big Member States essentially kept everything that they could for themselves at the time where some other Member States had much bigger needs and where these medical countermeasures were more necessary there.
So, my question is: would you support that we do whatever we can to add to this Critical Medicines Act also provisions of common stockpiling and more coordination so that we make sure that patients actually get those medicines, which they need in times of crisis?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:06:18</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_154"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_208"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_209"/>
  </rdf:Description>
