  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_17">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_17</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Nora Mebarek,</del:name>
    <del:name>TamГғВЎs Deutsch</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PfE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_378">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_378</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Notre premiГғВЁre ligne de dГғВ©fense doit ГғВӘtre une bonne diplomatie. Or, ГғВ  cet ГғВ©gard, lГўВҖВҷUnion pourrait faire beaucoup mieux. Nos relations sont tendues avec Washington, difficiles avec PГғВ©kin et inexistantes avec Moscou. Ce nГўВҖВҷest pas toujours la faute des autres. Nous devons rГғВ©apprendre ГғВ  pratiquer la diplomatie, ГғВ  communiquer, ГғВ  ГғВ©couter et ГғВ  comprendre, mГғВӘme dans des circonstances apparemment adverses.
Notre deuxiГғВЁme ligne de dГғВ©fense est la dissuasion. Nous voulons amГғВ©liorer nos armГғВ©es, mais essayons dГўВҖВҷГғВ©viter une course ГғВ  lГўВҖВҷarmement. Faisons plutГғВҙt renaГғВ®tre les mesures de confiance et veillons ГғВ  ne pas dГғВ©penser de sommes dГғВ©mesurГғВ©es et ГғВ  ne pas contracter des dettes faramineuses pour couvrir des dГғВ©penses militaires. Nos sociГғВ©tГғВ©s connaissent encore bien dГўВҖВҷautres besoins, souvent plus pressants. Le rГғВ©armement est une activitГғВ© dangereuse ГғВ  maints ГғВ©gards, vers lГўВҖВҷextГғВ©rieur comme vers lГўВҖВҷintГғВ©rieur: gardons-le sous contrГғВҙle.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:19:02</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_272"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_377"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_378"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_192">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_192</del:identifier>
    <del:text>DerriГғВЁre ces financements se cache un vГғВ©ritable rГғВ©seau militant qui, avec lГўВҖВҷargent des contribuables, encourage lГўВҖВҷimmigration massive, bloque les expulsions et combat les ГғВүtats qui dГғВ©fendent leur souverainetГғВ©. Bruxelles finance ceux qui sabotent nos dГғВ©mocraties, rГғВ©pandent le poison wokiste ou imposent une ГғВ©cologie punitive aux EuropГғВ©ens, pendant que nos industries sГўВҖВҷeffondrent et que nos peuples sГўВҖВҷappauvrissent.
Il est temps de mettre fin ГғВ  cette propagande financГғВ©e par lГўВҖВҷUnion europГғВ©enne. LГўВҖВҷargent des EuropГғВ©ens doit servir ГғВ  lГўВҖВҷintГғВ©rГғВӘt des EuropГғВ©ens, pas aux idГғВ©ologies bruxelloises et ГғВ  ses lobbys.</del:text>
    <del:text>Written Statements (Rule 178)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:56:15</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:44:54</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_140"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_191"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_192"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_495">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_495</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Het liefst wil je dat SyriГғВ«rs zelf aan zet zijn voor de wederopbouw. Hiervoor is ruimte nodig, mogelijkheden om te investeren en internationale samenwerking. Daarom moeten wij pragmatisch kijken naar het schorsen van de sancties. Ook zullen wij openstaan om diplomatieke posten te heropenen in SyriГғВ«. De Syrische de facto overheid zal moeten laten zien dat ze alle bevolkingsgroepen, alle etnische minderheden vertegenwoordigt, waaronder ook religieuze minderheden, vrouwen en kinderen.
Geweldsuitbarstingen zoals die van afgelopen week, waarbij meer dan duizend mensen het leven lieten in gerichte aanvallen op bevolkingsgroepen, zullen wij niet en kunnen wij als EU niet accepteren. SyriГғВ« heeft een lange weg te gaan. Zo zullen er democratische verkiezingen georganiseerd moeten worden, zal er hulp op gang moeten komen en zal er toegang moeten zijn tot zorg, onderwijs en schoon water als basisvoorzieningen voor iedereen in SyriГғВ«. Het is nu aan de EU om te kijken op welke gebieden wij kunnen samenwerken met SyriГғВ« en onder welke voorwaarden.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:53:34</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_350"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_494"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_495"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_223">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_223</del:identifier>
    <del:name>ГҗВ•ГҗВјГҗВёГҗВ» ГҗВ ГҗВ°ГҗВҙГҗВөГҗВІ</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_304">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_304</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Peter Liese</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_269">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_269</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Nell'esperienza di chi studia la materia sono le frontiere chiuse che generano le migrazioni illegali e che generano lo strapotere dei trafficanti di esseri umani. Dovremmo ricominciare ad aprire le frontiere e a dare visti.
E, tra l'altro, sempre gli stessi accademici ci dicono che le persone si muovono perchГғВ© qui c'ГғВЁ un bisogno di manodopera. ГғВҲ questo il pull factor: siamo noi.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:41:31</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_198"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_268"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_269"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_105">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_105</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Thomas Geisel</del:name>
    <del:name>Chiara Gemma</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_NI"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_493">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_493</del:identifier>
    <del:text>And I would again say that we closed already the catch-the-eye procedure. So for those who are now arriving, there is no chance for catch-the-eye or for blue cards.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:44:52</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_492"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_493"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_55">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_55</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Estes dГғВ©fices, de facto, existem. Mas hoje quero falar-vos de excessos: a Europa tem excesso de regulaГғВ§ГғВЈo, de percentagens e de debate inconsequente.
Nos ГғВәltimos anos, o PPE, o PSD e eu prГғВіpria temos alertado para o excesso regulatГғВіrio que estrangula a capacidade das empresas europeias de investir, criar empregos e gerar riqueza. Finalmente, temos relatГғВіrios que nos dГғВЈo razГғВЈo e um ambiente polГғВӯtico que nos dГғВЎ ГўВҖВ” a todos ГўВҖВ” a oportunidade de fazer diferente.
Por outro lado, hГғВЎ excesso de percentagens no discurso polГғВӯtico. Falamos de 99,8ГӮВ % de PME na Europa, esquecendo que isto representa 26 milhГғВөes de empresas. Referimo-nos a 52ГӮВ % de valor acrescentado das PME, mas esquecemo-nos de que, por detrГғВЎs, estГғВЈo 90 milhГғВөes de trabalhadores. NГғВіs nГғВЈo temos de decidir para as percentagens, temos de agir para as pessoas.
Finalmente, temos excesso de debate inconsequente. Um debate alimentado por uma esquerda que acusa a ComissГғВЈo de querer matar o Green Deal quando foi a mesma presidente da ComissГғВЈo quem o lanГғВ§ou e por uma extremaГўВҖВ‘direita queГӮВ na Europa sГғВі vГғВӘ o ГғВәnico alvo para alimentar a sua propaganda.
NГғВіs aqui estamos, como sempre estivemos, no espaГғВ§o da moderaГғВ§ГғВЈo. Naquele espaГғВ§o que aprovou o Green Deal e que quer libertar recursos para as empresas o poderem cumprir. O espaГғВ§o que quer que as empresas invistam e criem emprego e nГғВЈo se percam em burocracias. O espaГғВ§o que quer simplificar a vida a quem gera riqueza e facilitar a vida de quem trabalha.
To conclude, Ms Bischoff and dear Pascal, the EPP is ready to work with everyone ГўВҖВ“ with everyone. We are just not ready to destroy whatever is left of our European competitiveness.</del:text>
    <del:text>We need bullets, drones, missiles streaming quickly, unimpeded by delays. Last year we produced 500 artillery shells. Ukraine burns through that in two months. Scaling up ГўВҖВ“ experts say years. We don't have years. Bureaucracy kills. Delays kill. Either we act or we fail. Ukraine needs firepower now. Tanks, jets, not just applause. Drop the taboos ГўВҖВ“ landmines, cluster bombs ГўВҖВ“ because Russia has no red lines. It's time to turn plants into production, factories into force. Support Ukraine now. Peace through strength now.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:25:33</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:56:09</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_32"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_47"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_54"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_55"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_73">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_73</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ich mГғВ¶chte noch einmal ganz besonders, weil der Umweltausschuss da federfГғВјhrend ist, die VorschlГғВӨge fГғВјr CBAM unterstГғВјtzen. Wir brauchen einen Grenzausgleichsmechanismus, um unsere Unternehmen, die sich auf den Weg zur KlimaneutralitГғВӨt gemacht haben, vor billigen, dreckigen Importen zu schГғВјtzen. Das ist nГғВ¶tig. Aber wenn ein MittelstГғВӨndler ein Paket Schrauben bestellt, dann brauchen wir doch keine Berichtspflichten fГғВјr den. Oder ein 16-jГғВӨhriger Jugendlicher, der ein Ersatzteil fГғВјr sein Moped bestellt hat und dann einen Fragebogen zu CBAM zugeschickt bekommt ГўВҖВ“ das ist doch absurd!
Wir mГғВјssen uns auf die groГғВҹen Mengen konzentrieren. Das macht der Kommissionsvorschlag. Deswegen sollten wir diesen Vorschlag so schnell wie mГғВ¶glich annehmen, Vereinfachung einfach mal machen.
(Der Redner ist damit einverstanden, auf eine Frage nach dem Verfahren der ГўВҖВһblauen KarteГўВҖВң zu antworten.)</del:text>
    <del:text>Pour cela, nous devons dГғВЁs maintenant ГғВ©carter la dangereuse illusion dГўВҖВҷune force armГғВ©e au service dГўВҖВҷune Europe fГғВ©dГғВ©rale. LГўВҖВҷUnion europГғВ©enne peut et doit, bien sГғВ»r, faciliter le financement de ce rГғВ©armement, mais elle ne peut en aucun cas en ГғВӘtre la gГғВ©nГғВ©rale en chef; cГўВҖВҷest aux armГғВ©es nationales de dГғВ©fendre nos nations. LГўВҖВҷurgence qui doit nous occuper est dГўВҖВҷГғВ©tablir une prГғВ©fГғВ©rence europГғВ©enne en matiГғВЁre dГўВҖВҷachats militaires. Si cette prioritГғВ© ne devient pas la pierre angulaire de la nouvelle architecture de dГғВ©fense de notre continent, alors toute vellГғВ©itГғВ© dГўВҖВҷindГғВ©pendance restera illusoire.
Allons au bout du chemin: le rГғВ©armement militaire nГўВҖВҷa de sens quГўВҖВҷaccompagnГғВ© dГўВҖВҷun rГғВ©armement dГғВ©mographique et identitaire. Il est grand temps que cette institution cesse de regarder les menaces uniquement ГғВ  lГўВҖВҷaune de ses Г…В“illГғВЁres idГғВ©ologiques.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:56:28</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:20:27</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_48"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_63"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_72"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_73"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_24">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_24</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Tomas TobГғВ©,</del:name>
    <del:name>ГҺВҡГҸВҺГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҺВ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВұГҺВҙГҺВ¬ГҺВәГҺВ·ГҸВӮ</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_NI"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_63">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_63</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Deshalb frage ich mich auch ganz ehrlich: Haben einige Kollegen von Sozialdemokraten und GrГғВјnen noch nicht mitbekommen, wie schlecht es um die europГғВӨische Wirtschaft steht? Ich finde es wirklich unverantwortlich, wie sich hier einige jedweder Vereinfachung und BГғВјrokratieabbau verweigern. Und leider, wenn ich nach Berlin kucke, macht mir das schwarz-rote Sondierungspapier auch nicht sehr viel Hoffnung, dass die Union es tatsГғВӨchlich ernst meint mit echten Reformen jenseits des Wahlkampfs.
Deswegen mein absoluter Appell an die Kommission: Wir brauchen noch viel mehr Vereinfachung, wir brauchen Abbau von ГғВјberflГғВјssigen Gesetzen und Regulierungen, und deswegen brauchen wir jede Menge neue Omnibusse. Und der nГғВӨchste muss ein Digital-Omnibus sein, denn wir mГғВјssen die ГғВјberbordenden Digitalgesetze vereinfachen. Wir mГғВјssen endlich bei Innovationen an der Weltspitze sein und nicht bei der Regulierung.</del:text>
    <del:text>Ich mГғВ¶chte auf eine Sache noch einmal hinweisen, die unser Fraktionsvorsitzender Manfred Weber vorhin vollkommen zu Recht dargestellt hat: Wir sind gut in den Krisenzeiten. Aber schaffen wir es in den Krisenzeiten nicht nur als EuropГғВӨische Union, die Mitgliedstaaten dabei zu unterstГғВјtzen, ihre Hausaufgaben zu erledigen, sondern schaffen wir es auch gemeinsam mit den Mitgliedstaaten, endlich in Europa den nГғВӨchsten Schritt zu gehen?
Wir haben es doch gesehen bei der Corona-Krise: Der Corona-Wiederaufbaufonds war ein Riesenschritt der EuropГғВӨischen Union, um den Mitgliedstaaten zu helfen. Aber wir haben es nicht geschafft, die europaweiten Stromnetze z.ГӮВ B. zu bauen, europaweite Eisenbahnnetze zu ertГғВјchtigen. Wir haben es nicht geschafft, Europa als Kontinent mit einem gemeinsamen groГғВҹen Projekt zusammenzubringen.
Und auch jetztГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ ReArm Europe ist dringend nГғВ¶tig. Aber auch hier gilt doch wieder: Es fehlen genau die gemeinsamen europГғВӨischen Projekte. Es geht doch nicht nur darum, die Mitgliedstaaten jetzt alleine dabei zu unterstГғВјtzen, die nГғВ¶tige AufrГғВјstung zu machen, endlich verteidigungsfГғВӨhig zu werden, sondern wir mГғВјssen doch gemeinsame europГғВӨische Projekte durchsetzen.
Ich kann den Rat nur aufrufen, Herr Costa, ich kann die Mitgliedstaaten nur aufrufen: Bitte machen Sie im Rat Druck, dass wir einige Projekte auch gemeinsam machen! Die Beispiele, die Manfred Weber heute genannt hat: mit dem gemeinsamen ГғВңberwachungssatellitensystem, mit einem gemeinsamen Luftabwehrschirm, mit einem vielleicht auch gemeinsamen FlugzeugtrГғВӨger, HubschraubertrГғВӨger, DrohnentrГғВӨger oder was auch immer. Wir mГғВјssen doch bitte auch als EuropГғВӨer gemeinsam ein groГғВҹes Projekt voranbringen, um auch nach auГғВҹen zu zeigen: Wir meinen die europГғВӨische EinigungГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ gerade auch in KrisenzeitenГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ ernst.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:38:52</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:07:20</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_38"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_55"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_62"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_63"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_537">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_537</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The fact is that after Israel once again cut off electricity to Gaza, nine out of ten people no longer have access to safe drinking water. Nine out of ten.
The fact is that after Israel once again halted the delivery of humanitarian aid to Gaza, the genocide is only escalating. Generations are being wiped out before our eyes. And still the powerful are turning a blind one or worse.
If those of you who had even a shred ГўВҖВ“ just a shred ГўВҖВ“ of humanity in you, you would not look away. You would not excuse the inexcusable. You would do something that should have been done long ago. You would deliver.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:57:42</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_374"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_536"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_537"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_385">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_385</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Some important elements must be addressed in this strategic document. As the foundation for our approach to European defence, we must take into account the security challenges of all Member States. When building the future of our defence, it is crucial that we are more open and comprehensive, including by considering the threats that our borders are facing, big and small, and from the east and the south, as we have heard here. The borders and the states of the eastern and south-eastern flank must engage in defence cooperation with our partners in enlargement countries that are participating in our CSDP missions that fully align with our Common Foreign and Security policy. By involving enlargement countries industry in defence procurement, we will fortify the security of European borders.
Finally, all the stakeholders should be engaged in buildingГӮВ European defence. Only by having a state in our common defence vision, all Member States and citizens will embrace this paper as their textbook for future defence of our citizens. Once again, I warmly welcome the announcement that the US is engaging again to help Ukraine at this moment while we are building our European defence, and the good news from Riyadh is an encouraging step in our transatlantic relations.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:27:07</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_35"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_384"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_385"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_95">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_95</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Wir mГғВјssen uns wirklich fragen, ob diese Hilfsmittel das erreichen, wofГғВјr sie mal von einer Mehrheit hier im Hause gegen meine Stimme geschaffen wurden. Bei der Richtlinie ГғВјber Nachhaltigkeitsberichterstattung und beim LieferkettensorgfaltspflichtenГўВҖВ‘Gesetz fГғВӨllt die Antwort eigentlich klar aus: In der heutigen Form sind sie kein hilfreiches Instrument, um die Ziele zu erreichen. Sie sind unnГғВ¶tig kompliziert, sie sorgen fГғВјr hohe BГғВјrokratielasten, sie schaffen hГғВ¶chstens ArbeitsplГғВӨtze fГғВјr Consultants und RechtsanwГғВӨlte, aber WettbewerbsfГғВӨhigkeit schaffen sie nicht.
Deswegen ist es richtig, dass die EuropГғВӨische Kommission nun zielgerichtet Anpassungen vorgeschlagen hat. Die VorschlГғВӨge gehen in die richtige Richtung, aber ich hГғВӨtte mir schon etwas mehr Ambitionen gewГғВјnscht, liebe Frau Kommissarin. Insbesondere im Bereich der Taxonomie wollen Sie alles nur auf Level zwei mit delegierten Rechtsakten lГғВ¶sen. Ich glaube, die Mutter aller Probleme ist die Taxonomie, und hier erwarte ich noch weitere VorschlГғВӨge von der Kommission. Auch an der Stelle mГғВјssen wir noch deutlich entrГғВјmpeln.</del:text>
    <del:text>Andamos agora a correr para recuperar o tempo perdido.ГӮВ A seguranГғВ§a nГғВЈo ГғВ©, tГғВЈoГўВҖВ‘sГғВі, mais uma polГғВӯtica pГғВәblica, mas a condiГғВ§ГғВЈo existencial de todas as polГғВӯticas pГғВәblicas.
O tempo da guerra ГғВ© tambГғВ©m distinto do tempo da burocracia em Bruxelas. Enquanto a Europa delibera, as linhas da frente movem-se, as capacidades industriais de defesa alteram-se, e as vulnerabilidades aprofundam-se.
Com o plano ReArm Europe, ГғВ© inegГғВЎvel que se abre uma nova janela de oportunidade para a Europa. ГғВү mesmo tempo de mudar.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:24:51</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:47:38</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_66"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_82"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_94"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_95"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_8">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_8</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Now we face new challenges, like the threat of war. Let us not forget how we handled COVID-19. We need to be bold and stay united. By learning from that time we can build a more resilient and cohesive Europe. This will help us face any future crisis with determination and unity.</del:text>
    <del:text>MrГӮВ Procaccini, can I give the floor to the President of the European Council first, because he has just arrived?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:07:50</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T09:33:48</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_2"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_7"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_8"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_548">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_548</del:identifier>
    <del:text>FГғВ¶r hur kan EU trГғВӨffa israeliska representanter och prata om samarbete nГғВӨr folkmord pГғВҘgГғВҘr? Hur kan EU acceptera att medlemslГғВӨnder struntar i den internationella brottmГғВҘlsdomstolens arresteringsorder mot israeliska ministrar? Hur kan EU blunda nГғВӨr Israel saboterar vapenvilan, hindrar nГғВ¶dhjГғВӨlp frГғВҘn att nГғВҘ Gaza och lГғВҘter bulldozrarna rulla in i VГғВӨstbanken?
EU mГғВҘste nu klart och tydligt pГғВҘ riktigt, inte bara i ord, stГғВ¶tta de initiativ som finns kring ГғВҘteruppbyggnad av Gaza och pГғВҘ riktigt, inte bara i ord, ta avstГғВҘnd frГғВҘn alla fГғВ¶rslag som innebГғВӨr folkfГғВ¶rdrivning och brott mot internationell rГғВӨtt.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T23:11:44</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_381"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_547"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_548"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_346">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_346</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Deklaracja niezachwianego wsparcia dla Ukrainy musi wyraГ…ВјaГ„ВҮ siГ„Вҷ w konkretach. Potrzeba odwaГ…Вјnych dziaГ…ВӮaГ…В„, by to aktywa rosyjskie finansowaГ…ВӮy obronГ„Вҷ Ukrainy. BiaГ…ВӮa ksiГ„Вҷga to mapa drogowa, ktГғВіrej musimy siГ„Вҷ trzymaГ„ВҮ konsekwentnie, odwaГ…Вјnie i hojnie. Musimy dozbroiГ„ВҮ EuropГ„Вҷ. Musimy zabezpieczyГ„ВҮ nasze granice. MuszГ„В… byГ„ВҮ jak tarcza. Musimy zapeГ…ВӮniГ„ВҮ nasze magazyny i musimy wykorzystaГ„ВҮ ten czas.ГӮ
Europe: stay the course.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:38:15</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_250"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_345"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_346"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_289">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_289</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Davor Ivo Stier</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_449">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_449</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Dans le mГғВӘme esprit, ce pacte doit aussi faire de lГўВҖВҷEurope la cheffe de file de lГўВҖВҷГғВ©conomie circulaire ГўВҖВ“ГӮВ entre autresГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ dans le monde, afin de diminuer notre dГғВ©pendance aux matiГғВЁres premiГғВЁres critiques. CГўВҖВҷest pour cela que nous saluons le fait que vous ayez repris dans ce pacte le principe consistant ГғВ  nГўВҖВҷacheter quГўВҖВҷune seule fois: une fois les matГғВ©riaux entrГғВ©s sur notre territoire, nous devons les garder ici et ils doivent y rester. En les recyclant et en les rГғВ©utilisant, nous rГғВ©duisons notre dГғВ©pendance, nous baissons les coГғВ»ts et nous sГғВ©curisons nos ressources.
GrГғВўce ГғВ  une ГғВ©nergie propre et ГғВ  une ГғВ©conomie circulaire, nous bГғВўtirons une Europe plus forte et plus autonome.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:46:39</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_320"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_448"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_449"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_15">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_15</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Andrius Kubilius,</del:name>
    <del:name>Andrzej Halicki</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_39">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_39</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Anna Cavazzini</del:name>
    <del:name>JoГғВЈo Cotrim De Figueiredo</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Verts_ALE"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Renew"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_120">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_120</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The growth facility ГўВҖВ“ which at EURГӮВ 1.9ГӮВ billion for the years 2025 to 2027 is the largest ever financial support package for Moldova ГўВҖВ“ demonstrates that the European Union is also living up to our end of the bargain, and is helping Moldovan people and the country's institutions to prepare to assume the responsibilities of an EU Member State as soon as possible.
There is a real urgency to our action. The Commission submitted its proposal for the growth facility, which was modelled on the Western Balkans facility, last year. Since then, the already previously complicated political and economic situation in Moldova has become even more challenging, exacerbated by the energy crisis that was caused by the discontinuation of gas supply by Russia's Gazprom. Meanwhile, the true extent and nature of Russia's brazen interference in Moldova's democratic processes has become increasingly apparent.
We do understand the existential nature of these challenges. Therefore, I would like to commend the Commission for the decision to provide emergency energy assistance to Moldova, launching the comprehensive energy strategy. I would also like to underline how swiftly we managed to complete our parliamentary debates on the growth facility, and the interinstitutional negotiations with the Council and Commission.
Meanwhile, even despite the unprecedented swiftness of these talks, we managed to strengthen the facility by raising the pre-financing rate that my co-rapporteur already mentioned and increasing the non-repayable component of the facility by another EURГӮВ 100ГӮВ million, to a total of EURГӮВ 520ГӮВ million.
I am optimistic that after the adoption of the growth plan, the implementation of the facility will start delivering towards the long-term strategic goals of boosting Moldova's economic competitiveness, and making its institutions and its energy infrastructure more resilient. It will also help the country to further strengthen its ability to withstand and resist attempts by malicious external actors in Russia to interfere in Moldova's democratic processes.
But alongside the strategic transformation of Moldova's economy, it is also important for the implementation of the facility to make an immediate positive impact on the Moldovan people's lives. Let us recall that, even before the recent acute energy crisis, Moldova's economy had suffered a lot because of the effects of Russia's aggression against Ukraine.
So there is a real urgency, and we need to show that we are truly committed. In that light. I would also like to commend the Polish Presidency, which is working hard to see the opening of the first clusters in the accession negotiations.
During the AFET visit to Moldova less than two weeks ago, we saw the magnitude of the challenges, we saw who we are up against, but we also saw the dedication of Moldovan pro-European leaders. I hope that at tomorrow's vote Parliament will once again show our overwhelming support to the legitimate aspirations of the Moldovan people to live in a democratic, prosperous and European country.</del:text>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T20:03:52</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T12:57:39</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_87"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_119"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_120"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_143">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_143</del:identifier>
    <del:text>AstГ„Вғzi, Uniunea EuropeanГ„Вғ face mai mult decГғВўt sГ„Вғ-ГҲВҷi reafirme sprijinul pentru Republica Moldova. AstГ„Вғzi, Uniunea EuropeanГ„Вғ face un pas decisiv pentru viitorul pe care cetГ„ВғГҲВӣenii Republicii Moldova ГғВ®l meritГ„Вғ. Un viitor al prosperitГ„ВғГҲВӣii, al reformelor reale, al unei economii care creeazГ„Вғ oportunitГ„ВғГҲВӣi pentru toГҲВӣi. Acolo unde Rusia ГғВ®ncearcГ„Вғ sГ„Вғ pГ„ВғcГ„ВғleascГ„Вғ cu propagandГ„Вғ mincinoasГ„Вғ, Moldova alege Europa, iar Europa ГғВ®ГҲВҷi respectГ„Вғ cuvГғВўntul dat.
Prin acest program de 2 miliarde de euro investim nu doar ГғВ®n infrastructurГ„Вғ, energie, ci ГҲВҷi ГғВ®n viitorul fiecГ„Вғrui copil, ГғВ®n siguranГҲВӣa fiecГ„Вғrei familii, ГғВ®n puterea fiecГ„Вғrui antreprenor care crede ГғВ®ntr-o MoldovГ„Вғ europeanГ„Вғ.
ГҲВҳtim cГ„Вғ provocГ„Вғrile sunt mari, dar ГҲВҷtim ГҲВҷi cГ„Вғ cetГ„ВғГҲВӣenii Republicii Moldova au demonstrat iarГ„ВғГҲВҷi ГҲВҷi iarГ„ВғГҲВҷi cГ„Вғ au curajul ГҲВҷi hotГ„ВғrГғВўrea de a merge ГғВ®nainte.
AstГ„Вғzi, Uniunea EuropeanГ„Вғ nu doar sprijinГ„Вғ, ci crede ГғВ®n Moldova. Faptele probeazГ„Вғ asta. Viitorul este ГғВ®n mГғВўinile voastre, dragi cetГ„ВғГҲВӣeni ai Republicii Moldova, noi suntem aproape.</del:text>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T20:46:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:38:06</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_110"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_142"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_143"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_122">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_122</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:text>I give the floor to the rapporteur for two minutes.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T20:14:27</del:timestamp>
