  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_253">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_253</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Si je comprends bien votre prГғВ©sentation, Monsieur le Commissaire, la reconnaissance mutuelle des retours ne serait que volontaire, et non obligatoire. CГўВҖВҷest bien dommage de se priver dГўВҖВҷun outil commun, alors que les ГғВүtats membres ne font que se plaindre de dГғВ©cisions de retours dissonantes.
Au sujet des hubs de retour, quel sens cela a-t-il de renvoyer les migrants dans un pays intermГғВ©diaire avec lequel ils nГўВҖВҷont aucun lien? Comment pourrons-nous nous assurer du bon respect des droits fondamentaux des migrants en dehors de lГўВҖВҷEurope?
Pour amГғВ©liorer les retours, mon groupe, Renew, demande la nГғВ©gociation dГўВҖВҷaccords avec les pays dГўВҖВҷorigine, des pays souverains, pour quГўВҖВҷils reprennent leurs ressortissants. Monsieur le Commissaire, chers collГғВЁgues, donnons enfin une chance au pacte sur la migration et lГўВҖВҷasile. Assurons-nous de sa bonne mise en application avant de rechercher des solutions simplistes et populistes.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:19:55</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_187"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_252"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_253"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_61">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_61</del:identifier>
    <del:name>JГғВ¶rgen Warborn</del:name>
    <del:name>Javier Moreno SГғВЎnchez</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_25">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_25</del:identifier>
    <del:text>(Parliament rejected the request)
So the agenda remains unchanged.
The final request is from the Greens/EFA Group. For Wednesday, it has requested that a Commission statement on 'Secessionist threats in Bosnia and Herzegovina and the recent escalation' be added as the last point in the afternoon. As a consequence, the sitting would be extended to 11 p.m.
I give the floor to MsГӮВ Strick to move this request on behalf of the Green Group.</del:text>
    <del:text>We can make Russia pay. Let's seize 200ГӮВ billion of frozen Russian assets and direct them to Ukraine. MadamГӮВ President, the European Commission must make a decision on this right now.
Dear colleagues, the numbers don't lie. We are 450ГӮВ million Europeans. Russia has just 140ГӮВ million people. Our economy is 12 times larger. We have everything we need to defend ourselves and others. The only step left: removing the chains we have placed on ourselves.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:23:08</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:13:44</del:timestamp>
