  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_174">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_174</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Dan-Г…Вһtefan Motreanu</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_342">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_342</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Now, we must not only change our thinking and policies, but also defend Europe and our fellow Europeans. We must ensure European security, which is measured by the weakest link in its defence. Therefore, we must act together, not selectively. We must act now, not tomorrow.
Standardisation of weapons and military equipment, mobilisation of financial resources for their innovation, and speedy production and further development of military mobility and capabilities ГўВҖВ“ these are the most important things now.
For the European defence community should involve our partners from the very beginning, especially candidate countries like Ukraine. Close cooperation in this area will undoubtedly benefit all participant countries and, most importantly, our citizens.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:32:10</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_246"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_341"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_342"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_232">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_232</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ce nГўВҖВҷest pas tellement la faute des Indiens ou des Chinois, non: cГўВҖВҷest la faute des EuropГғВ©ens. Pourquoi? Parce que nous sommes dГғВ©pendants en premier lieu des choix que font les grandes multinationales pharmaceutiques. Ce sont elles qui dГғВ©cident quoi produire, oГғВ№ produire, combien produire et ГғВ  quel prix vendre,ГӮВ mГғВӘme lorsquГўВҖВҷelles ont reГғВ§u des subventions publiques ГғВ  la recherche ou ГғВ  la production.
Ce quГўВҖВҷil faut casser aujourdГўВҖВҷhui, cГўВҖВҷest le monopole quГўВҖВҷont ces entreprises, et pour ce faire les ONG, les associations et mГғВӘme les syndicats nous ont dГғВ©jГғВ  donnГғВ© la marche ГғВ  suivre: il sГўВҖВҷagit de crГғВ©er une infrastructure publique pour la recherche et le dГғВ©veloppement en Europe. CГўВҖВҷest possible. Vous trouvez 800ГӮВ milliards pour les armes; vous allez bien trouver quelques milliards pour la santГғВ©. QuГўВҖВҷest-ce que vous attendez?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:36:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_22"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_231"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_232"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_316">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_316</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Eszter Lakos</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_3">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_3</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Are there any comments? If not, the minutes will be deemed approved.</del:text>
    <del:text>The spring European Council meeting is traditionally focused on economic issues. However, in view of the rapidly evolving international context, leaders will also follow up on the special meeting of 6ГӮВ March. We are all aware of what is at stake, and the leaders will build on the important progress made at their meeting last week.
Allow me to add my voice here in stressing that only a comprehensive, just and lasting peace for Ukraine can put an end to the Russian war of aggression. A peace that is negotiated by Ukraine and its legitimated authorities led by President Volodymyr Zelenskyy. A peace that involves Europeans, whose security it will affect without a doubt. A peace based on strong security guarantees.
The European Council is also expected to revert to the situation in the Middle East, which has evolved substantially since the leaders last addressed the topic in December.
Let me now turn to competitiveness, which is a centrepiece of the agenda of the next European Council. 2024 was a year of assessment and reflection, with the Letta and Draghi reports the strategic agenda for the next five years. 2025 is the year for action and delivery.
Three priority areas have been identified for the leaders' debate on competitiveness: simplification, energy and the Saving and Investments Union. For the EU to remain competitive, we need to cut red tape and simplify EU rules for businesses, especially SMEs. Reducing administrative burdens and creating a simple and clear legislative framework remain a matter of urgency.
Europeans also require access to clean, secure and affordable energy, and we have to take steps to address the saving and investments mismatch in the EU in order to better meet Europe's investment needs, in particular those of young and innovative companies. This will also be important to ensure private financing to develop our defence industry for years ahead.
Leaders will also address the topics of the single market, industrial policy and skills, paying special attention to those sectors that are heavily impacted by the sustained rise in energy prices.
Finally, under this point, the European Council will also turn to its customary point on the European Semester. For a more long-term perspective, leaders will have a first exchange of views of views on the next multiannual financial framework and the new own resources, following the publication of the Commission Communication of 11ГӮВ February and ahead of the proposal expected in summer 2025.
Migration also remains high on the European Council agenda. Leaders will take stock of progress made in the implementation of previous conclusions and ensure a steady pace of work on returns.
Finally, other foreign policy issues will be addressed, notably multilateralism and oceans, which are expected to be on the table during the working lunch leaders will have with UN Secretary-General AntГғВіnio Guterres on Thursday. Depending on developments, Member States may also want to address issues in specific third countries or regions.
A Euro Summit is also scheduled to take place in the margins of the European Council, and will include the usual discussion on the economic situation with the President of the Eurogroup and the European Central Bank.
To conclude, we expect a substantial European Council meeting following up on the decision taken at last week's special European Council and advancing on essential work to ensure we are well prepared to meet the many challenges ahead. We are at a crucial juncture. We must rise to the occasion.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:05:33</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T09:04:05</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_2"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_2"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_3"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_20">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_20</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Enough with the violence. He said it was a metaphor. Well, a metaphor is what Shakespeare said, that the world is a stage. A metaphor is not when you say 'skinning people alive', when you put women down, when you put minorities down, when you go against the constitutional base of the country, when you say that ethnicities are less than people.
So enough with the hate. Let's not export the hate. Romanians deserve a European, modern, democratic life.</del:text>
    <del:text>A hГғВЎborГғВәpГғВЎrtiak rГғВЎadГғВЎsul mГғВ©g fordГғВӯtva is ГғВјlnek a dГғВ¶glГғВ¶tt lovon. Donald Trump vilГғВЎgosan megmondta, Amerika kiszГғВЎll a hГғВЎborГғВәbГғВіl, ГғВ©s bГғВ©kГғВ©t fog teremteni, pont. TehГғВЎt, amikor mГғВЎr az amerikaiaknak sem kell a proxy hГғВЎborГғВәjuk, akkor ezt a levetett amerikai hГғВЎborГғВәs hacikГғВЎt akarjГғВЎk a hГғВЎborГғВәpГғВЎrti vezetГ…В‘k EurГғВіpГғВЎra kГғВ©nyszerГғВӯteni. Az eddig elkГғВ¶ltГғВ¶tt eurГғВіmilliГғВЎrdok utГғВЎn, immГғВЎr bГғВЎrmennyi pГғВ©nzzel finanszГғВӯrozni akarjГғВЎk az ukrajnai ГғВ¶ldГғВ¶klГғВ©st. Amerika helyett is, sГ…В‘t az amerikai bГғВ©ketГғВ¶rekvГғВ©seket megakadГғВЎlyozandГғВі is. BrГғВјsszel vezetГ…В‘i rГғВЎadГғВЎsul nГғВ¶velik a bajt, megfejelik ezt azzal, hogy mГғВЎr Ukrajna gyorsГғВӯtott uniГғВіs csatlakozГғВЎsГғВЎt mantrГғВЎzzГғВЎk, ami egyenesen ГғВ¶sszedГғВ¶ntenГғВ© az eurГғВіpai gazdasГғВЎgot. Ezt a hГғВЎborГғВәt le kell zГғВЎrni, ГғВ©s lezГғВЎrni csak tГғВЎrgyalГғВЎsokkal lehet.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:19:04</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:05:13</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_10"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_17"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_19"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_20"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_487">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_487</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Clean Industrial Deal je prezentovanГғВҪ ako veГ„ВҫkolepГғВҪ plГғВЎn na zГғВЎchranu planГғВ©ty a posilnenie eurГғВіpskeho priemyslu. No v skutoГ„ВҚnosti? Je to Г„ВҸalГ…ВЎГғВӯ drahГғВҪ vГғВҪstrel do tmy od bruselskej elity, ktorГғВЎ ignoruje realitu naГ…ВЎich nГғВЎrodov.

Tento deal sГ„Вҫubuje zelenГғВә budГғВәcnosГ…ВҘ, ale za akГғВә cenu? PrГғВӯsne regulГғВЎcie a miliardovГғВ© dotГғВЎcie do vetra ГўВҖВ“ doslova ГўВҖВ“ zvyГ…ВЎujГғВә nГғВЎklady pre naГ…ВЎe firmy, ktorГғВ© uГ…Вҫ teraz bojujГғВә s konkurenciou z Г„ВҢГғВӯny a Ameriky. Tam si emisie nerieГ…ВЎia, vyrГғВЎbajГғВә lacno a efektГғВӯvne, kГғВҪm my tu topГғВӯme peniaze daГ…ВҲovГғВҪch poplatnГғВӯkov v byrokracii, solГғВЎrnych paneloch a vrtuliach. VГғВҪsledok? StratГғВӯme pracovnГғВ© miesta, presunieme vГғВҪrobu mimo EГғВҡ a globГғВЎlne emisie sa nezmenia ГўВҖВ“ len sa presГ…ВҘahujГғВә inde.

PГғВҪtam sa vГғВЎs: KoГ„Вҫko eГ…ВЎte zaplatГғВӯme za zelenГғВ© ilГғВәzie? KoГ„Вҫko fabrГғВӯk sa musГғВӯ zatvoriГ…ВҘ, koГ„Вҫko Г„ВҫudГғВӯ prГғВӯsГ…ВҘ o prГғВЎcu, kГғВҪm si priznГғВЎme, Г…Вҫe tento deal nie je rieГ…ВЎenГғВӯm, ale problГғВ©mom? My nepotrebujeme Г„ВҸalГ…ВЎie ideologickГғВ© experimenty ГўВҖВ“ my potrebujeme pragmatizmus, konkurencieschopnosГ…ВҘ a slobodu rozhodovaГ…ВҘ o vlastnej budГғВәcnosti.

Г„ВҺakujem</del:text>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_67"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_101">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_101</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Il conviendrait ГғВ©galement de mettre en place une avance sur recettes garantie par lГўВҖВҷUnion europГғВ©enne. Cet outil permettrait aux entreprises locales de mieux accГғВ©der aux financements et ГғВ©viterait que des projets importants pour le dГғВ©veloppement de nos outre-mer ne se retrouvent mort-nГғВ©s pour des questions de dГғВ©lais de financement.
Il est temps de simplifier les dГғВ©marches et dГўВҖВҷadapter les rГғВ©glementations aux rГғВ©alitГғВ©s ultramarines. LГўВҖВҷUnion europГғВ©enne a choisi dГўВҖВҷintГғВ©grer les rГғВ©gions ultramarines depuisГӮВ 1992, en crГғВ©ant les rГғВ©gions ultrapГғВ©riphГғВ©riques. Elle ne doit pas ГғВӘtre un frein, mais un vГғВ©ritable soutien ГғВ  leur dГғВ©veloppement.</del:text>
    <del:text>Most, hogy az EgyesГғВјlt ГғВҒllamok is visszavett a hГғВЎborГғВә tГғВЎmogatГғВЎsГғВЎbГғВіl, EurГғВіpГғВЎban is vissza kellene tГғВ©rni a jГғВіzan ГғВ©sz talajГғВЎra, vГғВЎltozГғВЎsra van szГғВјksГғВ©g az EU hГғВЎborГғВәval kapcsolatos stratГғВ©giГғВЎjГғВЎban.

A megvГғВЎltozott vilГғВЎgpolitikai helyzetben ugyanakkor kulcsfontossГғВЎgГғВә, hogy EurГғВіpa meg tudja vГғВ©deni magГғВЎt ГғВ©s tГғВ¶bbet tegyen sajГғВЎt bГғВ©kГғВ©jГғВ©nek ГғВ©s biztonsГғВЎgГғВЎnak garantГғВЎlГғВЎsГғВЎГғВ©rt. De az UniГғВі vГғВ©delmi kГғВ©pessГғВ©gei megerГ…В‘sГғВӯtГғВ©sГғВ©nek kГғВ©rdГғВ©se nem kГғВ¶thetГ…В‘ az UkrajnГғВЎnak nyГғВәjtott tovГғВЎbbi katonai segГғВӯtsГғВ©ghez. Ezeknek kГғВјlГғВ¶nГғВЎllГғВі kГғВ©rdГғВ©seknek kell maradniuk.

A vГғВ©delem terГғВјletГғВ©n tГғВЎmogatjuk azt az elkГғВ©pzelГғВ©st, hogy EurГғВіpГғВЎnak kГғВ©pesnek kell lennie arra, hogy megvГғВ©dje magГғВЎt. De a dГғВ¶ntГғВ©shozatalnak tagГғВЎllami hatГғВЎskГғВ¶rben kell maradnia. MikГғВ¶zben tГғВЎmogatjuk a tagГғВЎllamok kГғВ¶zГғВ¶tti ipari egyГғВјttmГ…ВұkГғВ¶dГғВ©st ГғВ©s a kГғВ¶zГғВ¶s programokat, ellenzГғВјnk minden olyan fГғВ¶deralista tГғВәlkapГғВЎst, tГғВәlterjeszkedГғВ©st a BizottsГғВЎg rГғВ©szГғВ©rГ…В‘l, amely alГғВЎГғВЎssa a nemzeti szuverenitГғВЎst.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:34:09</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_72"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_85"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_100"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_101"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_112">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_112</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ik roep de Commissie dan ook op om de komende tijd meer ambitie te tonen. Dit is een heel goed voorstel, maar het gaat nog niet ver genoeg. U bevindt zich op een betere weg. Zoals we in Nederland zeggen: "Beter ten halve gekeerd dan ten hele gedwaald". Ik wens u daarbij heel veel succes.</del:text>
    <del:text>Yesterday evening, on Russian TV, Vladimir Solovyov, the main propagandist of Putin's regime, attacked, insulted, threatened one of us: Pina Picierno, Vice-President of this House, has been assaulted with terrific violence on Russian TV.
And then you had campaigns of trolls and bots inside our own territory. So today it's time for us to show solidarity in front of fascist propagandists ...
(The President cut off the speaker)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:51:32</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T12:54:32</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_82"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_68"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_111"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_112"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_473">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_473</del:identifier>
    <del:text>O Clean Industrial Deal nГғВЈo ГғВ© apenas uma oportunidade, ГғВ© um compromisso com o crescimento e com a inovaГғВ§ГғВЈo, um compromisso de construir uma Europa que lidera na transiГғВ§ГғВЈo energГғВ©tica, que gera riqueza e cria empregos de qualidade. Uma Europa que inspira e se destaca no contexto global.
A indГғВәstria europeia foi sempre o motor do nosso progresso ГўВҖВ” agora temos a responsabilidade de descarbonizar para crescer. Este ГғВ© o momento de agir, de avanГғВ§ar mais rГғВЎpido, com mais determinaГғВ§ГғВЈo, ГғВ© o momento de garantir que a aposta em tecnologias limpas impulsiona a economia, reforГғВ§a a independГғВӘncia energГғВ©tica e cria novas oportunidades de emprego.
A Europa do futuro comeГғВ§a hoje com inovaГғВ§ГғВЈo, com visГғВЈo, com ambiГғВ§ГғВЈo, e comeГғВ§a connosco, com todos nГғВіs.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:17:43</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_340"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_472"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_473"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_350">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_350</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Ingeborg Ter Laak,</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_394">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_394</del:identifier>
    <del:text>For too long, Ireland has overlooked security and defence. While we remain committed to military neutrality, it does not equate to vulnerability. Securing our territorial waters and airspace is crucial, and the Government is prioritising the much-needed investment in our defence forces.
That is why I support Ireland's increased ambition in terms of urgent investment in primary radar, naval expansion and air defence. These are not luxuries: they are fundamental to our national security.
At the same time, Ireland's commitment to neutrality remains steadfast. But neutrality must be fit for purpose for the 21st century. That means contributing meaningfully to European security and contributing in areas in which we have a considerable degree of experience and expertise ГўВҖВ“ like peacekeeping, for example.
It's time to get off the fence and get on with defence.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:38:19</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_282"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_393"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_394"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_16">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_16</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:text>Ideje lenne szembenГғВ©zniГғВјk a valГғВіsГғВЎggal. MagyarorszГғВЎgot ГғВ©vek ГғВіta szГғВ©gyenpadra ГғВјltetik jogГғВЎllamisГғВЎgi problГғВ©mГғВЎk ГғВ©s a transzparencia hiГғВЎnya miatt. Ukrajna kapcsГғВЎn ez miГғВ©rt nem zavarja ГғВ–nГғВ¶ket? DemokrГғВЎciГғВЎrГғВіl nem beszГғВ©lhetГғВјnk, illegitim az elnГғВ¶ke, mindennaposak az emberi jogokat sГғВ©rtГ…В‘, erГ…В‘szakos kГғВ©nyszersorozГғВЎsok, a kisebbsГғВ©gi jogok tiprГғВЎsa lassan nГғВ©pirtГғВЎsba fordul, mГғВ©gsem hallok jogГғВЎllamisГғВЎgi aggodalmakat.
Ahelyett, hogy ГғВәjabb csillagГғВЎszati ГғВ¶sszegeket szavaznak meg a hГғВЎborГғВәra, ki kellene vizsgГғВЎlni a transzparencia jegyГғВ©ben, hogy az eddig UkrajnГғВЎba kГғВјldГғВ¶tt eurГғВіmilliГғВЎrdokbГғВіl mennyi kerГғВјlt oligarchГғВЎk kezГғВ©be. TisztГғВЎzni kell, hogy az oda ГғВ©rkezГ…В‘ fegyverek egy rГғВ©sze valГғВіban olyan terrorszervezeteknГғВ©l kГғВ¶tГғВ¶tt-e ki, mint a Hamasz vagy az ISIS, esetleg a mexikГғВіi drogkartell is profitГғВЎlt-e belГ…В‘le? LГғВ©pjenek ki elmГғВ©jГғВјk zГғВЎrt rendszerГғВ©bГ…В‘l, ГғВ©s mГғВ©rjГғВ©k fel a realitГғВЎsokat, mielГ…В‘tt Ukrajna EU-s ГғВ©s NATO tagsГғВЎgГғВЎrГғВіl fantГғВЎziГғВЎlnak, mert EurГғВіpa vГғВ©gzetes elgyengГғВјlГғВ©sГғВ©vel ГғВ©s a harmadik vilГғВЎghГғВЎborГғВәval jГғВЎtszanak!</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:16:12</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T09:59:09</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_13"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_15"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_16"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_333">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_333</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The war in Ukraine has highlighted the consequences of inaction and overreliance on external partners for European defence. Beyond Ukraine, Europe has increasingly become the target of hybrid attacks and disinformation campaigns, directly threatening our political and economic stability.
But, despite all possible efforts, NATO remains the cornerstone of our security. If Europe needs to step up, any European-led initiatives must complement, not duplicate, NATO's role.
In its current form, the joint resolution is concerning. Instead of strengthening Europe's security, it promotes an alternative to NATO, undermines the autonomy of Member States in defence matters and risks deepening confrontation with the United States ГўВҖВ“ our most important ally.
Instead, Europe must focus on real security: replenishing stockpiles, strengthening transatlantic ties and investing in credible deterrence.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:21:06</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_58"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_332"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_333"/>
  </rdf:Description>
