  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_412">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_412</del:identifier>
    <del:text>KaГ…Вјda inicjatywa wzmacniajГ„В…ca obronnoГ…ВӣГ„ВҮ Europy powinna uzupeГ…ВӮniaГ„ВҮ, a nie dublowaГ„ВҮ rolГ„Вҷ NATO. Obecny projekt rezolucji budzi niepokГғВіj, poniewaГ…Вј promuje alternatywГ„Вҷ dla Sojuszu i podwaГ…Вјa autonomiГ„Вҷ paГ…В„stw czГ…ВӮonkowskich w kwestiach obronnych. Co wiГ„Вҷcej, moГ…Вјe prowadziГ„ВҮ do niepotrzebnych napiГ„ВҷГ„ВҮ w relacjach z USA ГўВҖВ“ naszym kluczowym sojusznikiem.
Europa musi inwestowaГ„ВҮ w realne bezpieczeГ…В„stwo: odbudowГ„Вҷ zdolnoГ…Вӣci produkcyjnych, uzupeГ…ВӮnianie zapasГғВіw oraz wzmacnianie transatlantyckich wiГ„Вҷzi. Kluczowe jest takГ…Вјe, aby wszystkie paГ…В„stwa czГ…ВӮonkowskie wypeГ…ВӮniaГ…ВӮy swoje zobowiГ„В…zania obronne, wzorem Polski, ktГғВіra juГ…Вј dziГ…Вӣ wydaje 5% PKB na ten cel. Tylko w ten sposГғВіb zapewnimy stabilnoГ…ВӣГ„ВҮ i odstraszanie.</del:text>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_30"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem14">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Topic"/>
    <del:identifier>creitem14</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Request for the defence of immunity</del:name>
    <del:name>Assessment of the implementation of Horizon Europe in view of its interim evaluation and recommendations for the 10th Research Framework Programme (A10-0021/2025 - Christian Ehler) (vote)</del:name>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_335">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_335</del:identifier>
    <del:text>This is not a theoretical discussion about where Europe shall head. This is a very serious discussion about how we can protect the international rules-based order, the national sovereignty of countries, and the right of countries to determine their own fate. Russia and Putin do not believe in that. They want their empire, they want their sphere of influence, and they are building a war economy that is threatening Europe, but also countries outside of the EU.
By this paper ГўВҖВ“ and I urge you, Commissioner, to be very strong and ambitious ГўВҖВ“ we show that Europe is united, that we can invest in defence, we can create military capabilities where Europe is united and can also act alone without the support of the United States. And that is something that negates the threat of Russia and protects democracy and peace in Europe ГўВҖВ“ that is what we must achieve.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:23:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_241"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_334"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_335"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_386">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_386</del:identifier>
    <del:text>It is astonishing to find ourselves discussing the impact of both Putin and a US President in the same breath, but a fact is a fact. For the sake of future generations, we must invest in our industries, in our defence, in infrastructure and cybersecurity capacity, ensuring our societies are robust and resilient.
Moreover, we must broaden our alliance beyond the traditional transatlantic relations. While the partnership with the US is still important, Europe should also strengthen ties with states like the UK, Canada, Brazil, Mexico, India, Japan and countries across Africa. The future of global security, of course, depends on our strength, but it also depends on our cooperation with states with shared values and interests.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:28:54</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_275"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_385"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_386"/>
  </rdf:Description>
