  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_519">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_519</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Only a few words on the latest outbreak of violence. So we welcome, as I already said, the announcement by the interim authorities to support the investigative commission which is being established. Everything must be done to prevent any such crimes from happening again. This is why I said at the beginning that they had to translate their commitment into action.
On the Brussels conference, once again we think that it is a very important one, and a little bit different than earlier. For the first time, the Syrian interim authorities have been invited together with the United Nations, alongside Syria's neighbouring countries and other regional partners. There will be two different panels and two different pledges. One will be to address the immediate needs of the Syrian people, with the focus on socioГўВҖВ‘economic recovery. At the same time, it will be addressing the serious humanitarian needs which still exist.
On the different groups, some of you mentioned the Christians and the protection of Christian minorities or communities. You all know that the new authorities in Damascus have a major responsibility to ensure the protection of all components of society and to refrain from acts of vengeance. We are sure that this their task, but let's see what the future will bring. Of course, we have to protect all Syrians in their diversity, based on the equal rights of citizens.ГӮВ Once again, a very important issue is to support the inclusive transition in Syria, because it is critical for the regional security.
On returns ГўВҖВ“ returns cannot and should not be rushed. In the context of a very fragile transition, something which we want to see is whether and at what moment Syria will be proclaimed a safe third country. So let's see how this will go.
On sanctions, we have already suspended sectoral sanctions, but now let's see how to proceed with financial sanctions. We know that American sanctions are already there. So let's see.
All that we have been doing in January and February at the Foreign Affairs Council has been in a gradual and irreversible manner. I want to thank you for the support you have shown this evening. Syria's reconstruction will need the backing of all of us ГўВҖВ“ of the Commission, of the Member States and of Parliament ГўВҖВ“ in a Team Europe spirit. Parliamentary diplomacy, outreach and expertise in stateГўВҖВ‘building are of the essence at this critical juncture for Syria. What is important is that we here in Europe remain united and committed, and Syria's future depends on our collective action today. So we are looking forward to the resolution, which I hope will be voted tomorrow.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:26:10</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_349"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_518"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_519"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_488">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_488</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Reindustrializar Europa con un modelo sostenible y competitivo solo serГғВЎ posible si garantizamos energГғВӯa asequible para nuestras industrias y ciudadanos. Necesitamos mГғВЎs renovables e interconexiones para una UniГғВіn de la EnergГғВӯa real y mercados e instrumentos que reflejen esta asequibilidad para la industria.

AdemГғВЎs, la financiaciГғВіn es una condiciГғВіn imprescindible. Es una buena noticia que este plan venga acompaГғВұado de recursos, pero debemos asegurarnos de que el prГғВіximo Marco Financiero Plurianual continГғВәe en esa direcciГғВіn. Necesitamos apostar por campeones europeos capaces de competir a nivel global. Este pacto es tambiГғВ©n una oportunidad para fomentar el sector de las tecnologГғВӯas limpias para modernizar nuestra base industrial y mejorar nuestras condiciones de vida.</del:text>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_239"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_188">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_188</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Vous voulez donc commencer cela cette annГғВ©e, alors que la situation financiГғВЁre de lГўВҖВҷUnion est dГғВ©jГғВ  catastrophique et que, trГғВЁs souvent, vos projets immobiliers aboutissent ГғВ  des dГғВ©rapages scandaleux. Je citerai le projet Berlaymont, de la Commission, qui a coГғВ»tГғВ© plus de cinq fois le prix estimГғВ© au dГғВ©part, le projet Europa, ou encore ceux de la Cour de justice et de lГўВҖВҷEMA. Quelles garanties ГғВ©viteront cette fois un fiasco? OГғВ№ est la ventilation dГғВ©taillГғВ©e de ce budget? Un audit par la Cour des comptes sur cet ГғВ©chec ne devrait-il pas ГғВӘtre un prГғВ©alable?
Alors que le siГғВЁge officiel de notre Parlement est ici ГғВ  Strasbourg, vos doublons de siГғВЁges, aberration logistique, coГғВ»tent 114ГӮВ millions dГўВҖВҷeuros par an. Sont-ils compatibles avec les objectifs du pacte vert, que vous dГғВ©fendez? Quels critГғВЁres environnementaux chiffrГғВ©s imposez-vous pour justifier ces travaux? Maintenir deux sites, avec leurs dГғВ©placements incessants, ne ridiculise-t-il pas notre exemplaritГғВ© ГғВ©cologique?
Au lieu de dГғВ©penser 455ГӮВ millions, pourquoi ne vendez-vous pas Bruxelles? CГўВҖВҷest le moment: cela vous permettrait de rediriger ces fonds vers les PME, lГўВҖВҷagriculture et dГўВҖВҷautres sujets utiles aux citoyens.</del:text>
    <del:text>87ГӮВ 000 women across the world will die because they're women. Over the course of a decade, that's the city of Amsterdam. 96ГӮВ % of AIГўВҖВ‘generated content known as deepfakes are pornographic in nature, sexualised content targeting women and young girls. We know this from reports that 99ГӮВ % of them are indeed women and young girls.
The foundation of gender equality is built on the rights to live free from all injustices. Yet, at the current pace of progress, gender equality will only be achieved by 2158. Yet I ask, what are we doing in here for the 229 million citizens that elected us and expect us to do better?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:50:31</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:36:42</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_101"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_138"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_187"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_188"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_33">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_33</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Comme pour Mayotte aprГғВЁs Chido, lГўВҖВҷГғВүtat franГғВ§ais doit demander la mobilisation du Fonds de solidaritГғВ© de lГўВҖВҷUnion europГғВ©enne pour aider La RГғВ©union ГғВ  reconstruire. Nous devons aussi activer des mesures Restore pour rГғВ©parer aujourdГўВҖВҷhui, mais surtout pour prГғВ©parer demain: indemniser les pertes agricoles et soutenir les filiГғВЁres dans leur reprise dГўВҖВҷactivitГғВ©, reconstruire en mieux pour protГғВ©ger davantage les populations, et permettre ГғВ  lГўВҖВҷГғВ®le dГўВҖВҷaccГғВ©lГғВ©rer son adaptation aux nouvelles rГғВ©alitГғВ©s climatiques.
Au-delГғВ  de lГўВҖВҷurgence immГғВ©diate, cette catastrophe nous rappelle une fois de plus quГўВҖВҷil est impГғВ©ratif de mettre en place une politique europГғВ©enne plus ambitieuse pour nos rГғВ©gions ultrapГғВ©riphГғВ©riques, qui sont en premiГғВЁre ligne face au dГғВ©rГғВЁglement climatique. Nous devons renforcer nos capacitГғВ©s dГўВҖВҷanticipation, dГўВҖВҷadaptation et de reconstruction en investissant durablement dans des infrastructures rГғВ©silientes, des dispositifs dГўВҖВҷalerte plus performants et des mГғВ©canismes de soutien plus rГғВ©actifs.
Face ГғВ  ce drame, la solidaritГғВ© europГғВ©enne ne doit pas ГғВӘtre un vГ…В“u pieux, mais une rГғВ©ponse concrГғВЁte. Aux RГғВ©unionnaises et aux RГғВ©unionnais nous ne devons pas offrir notre seule compassion, mais lГўВҖВҷassurance que lГўВҖВҷUnion ne laissera pas tomber ses rГғВ©gions ultrapГғВ©riphГғВ©riques, ГғВ  commencer par lГўВҖВҷГғВ®le de La RГғВ©union.</del:text>
    <del:text>This is why I decided to give every Member the opportunity to raise a blue card, but only once, because otherwise we cannot finish in time. We are limited in the end. If you do not agree, then please file a complaint to the President.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:38:52</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:25:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_17"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_32"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_33"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_103">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_103</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Eugen Tomac</del:name>
    <del:name>Mathilde AndrouГғВ«t</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Renew"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PfE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_509">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_509</del:identifier>
    <del:text>It is vital for the country to continue developing national unity. It's good to see that the government finalised an agreement with the Kurdish-led Syrian Democratic Forces, and they have to use the chance to integrate them into the national army and into the governing structure.
While these developments are promising, challenges, of course, persist. The recent violence in Latakia, where more than 1ГӮВ 500 people lost their lives, highlights the fragile security situation. And this needs our engagement. No Syrian should live in fear anymore. Therefore, it is positive that we discuss Syria and that we work for a good future for the Syrian people. They deserve it.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:12:58</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_360"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_508"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_509"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_213">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_213</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Depuis trop longtemps, nous avons laissГғВ© nos mГғВ©dicaments critiques devenir les otages des dГғВ©localisations et des tensions gГғВ©opolitiques. DГғВ©pendre de quelques usines ГғВ  lГўВҖВҷautre bout du monde, cГўВҖВҷest accepter lГўВҖВҷimpuissance face ГғВ  lГўВҖВҷurgence. LГўВҖВҷacte lГғВ©gislatif sur les mГғВ©dicaments critiques doit donc bГғВўtir une vГғВ©ritable souverainetГғВ© pharmaceutique europГғВ©enne. Cela passera par une lГғВ©gislation ambitieuse: relocalisation stratГғВ©gique des productions, ГғВ©tablissement de stocks de sГғВ©curitГғВ© et coordination renforcГғВ©e entre les ГғВүtats membres.
Il ne sГўВҖВҷagit pas seulement dГўВҖВҷun enjeu industriel; il sГўВҖВҷagit ГғВ©galement dГўВҖВҷun impГғВ©ratif de santГғВ© publique.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:10:36</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_157"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_212"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_213"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_135">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_135</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Maciej WГ„В…sik</del:name>
    <del:name>Marit Maij</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_85">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_85</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Presidente.</del:name>
    <del:name>Kinga GГғВЎl</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:hasRole rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/role_participant_85"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PfE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_11">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_11</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The right to be who you are, to love who you want and to live your life free from discrimination is a fundamental European right. That right is clearly under attack.
At this critical moment, the decision by the European Commission to announce the withdrawal of the horizontal anti-discrimination directive came as a shock. It also represents a betrayal of all the EU citizens who are currently lacking protection against discrimination.
It is time for the EU to show global leadership against discrimination, not to back down. As the European Parliament's rapporteur for this directive, I strongly condemn this decision and I urge the European Commission to immediately reconsider it.</del:text>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:12:01</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T09:44:57</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_5"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_10"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_11"/>
  </rdf:Description>
