  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_234">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_234</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Elena Donazzan</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_194">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_194</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:text>But itГўВҖВҷs important to remember that this celebration is not just for one day ГўВҖВ“ it is a commitment to equality every day. True equality goes beyond recognition; itГўВҖВҷs about ensuring equal opportunity for all. ItГўВҖВҷs about creating a world where no girl grows up believing she has to fight harder to be heard. We should dismantle barriers, challenge outdated mindsets and build an environment where talent, not gender, defines success.
From the boardroom to the classroom, from theГӮВ front lines to the voting booths, women are constantly redefining leadership. Yet too many still face discrimination, unequal opportunities and violence. These injustices must have no place in our societies.
Our words today should turn into actions tomorrow. The future we strive for ГўВҖВ“ a world where every woman and girl can dream without limits ГўВҖВ“ is not just an aspiration; it is a necessity. And as the European Parliament, we must work hard to make this future a reality for all.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:58:24</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_117"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_141"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_193"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_194"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_470">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_470</del:identifier>
    <del:text>En cualquier caso, me gustarГғВӯa hacer dos apuntes sobre el Pacto por una Industria Limpia, que creo que ГўВҖВ”como digoГўВҖВ” es correcto y oportuno. El primero de ellos es la necesidad de mejorar los mecanismos de financiaciГғВіn. Si vamos a hacer polГғВӯtica industrial en Europa no podemos hacerla de manera que la financiaciГғВіn sea descentralizada. Esto genera un grave riesgo para el mercado ГғВәnico. Yo creo que necesitamos pensar cГғВіmo financiarla. Y, en segundo lugar, y siendo de Asturias, esperamos el 19 de marzo ese Plan de AcciГғВіnГӮВ para el acero, tan necesario para territorios como el mГғВӯo.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:13:41</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_337"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_469"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_470"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_340">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_340</del:identifier>
    <del:text>L'Italia sostiene una difesa piГғВ№ forte e fondata su investimenti mirati, su un'industria competitiva nei settori strategici dello spazio, delle comunicazioni e dell'innovazione tecnologica. Investire nella sicurezza non significa alimentare una corsa al riarmo ma dare stabilitГғВ , autonomia strategica e crescita economica.
Ecco perchГғВ© il piano presentato dalla presidente von der Leyen, a mio avviso, deve essere rinominato come Defence Europe.
La sicurezza ГғВЁ la vera garanzia di pace ed ГғВЁ per questo che voglio stigmatizzare anche il comportamento di alcuni che si professano pacifisti solo per raccogliere pochi consensi senza pensare agli interessi nazionali.
Il Libro bianco deve essere l'occasione per costruire una difesa europea solida, rispettando le specificitГғВ  di ogni Stato membro, e rafforzare il ruolo dell'Europa nel mondo.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:30:37</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_245"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_339"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_340"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_78">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_78</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:text>Die Ukraine braucht Sicherheitsgarantien, die den Namen auch verdienen, und der britische Premierminister hat gesagt ГўВҖВһboots on the ground and planes in the airГўВҖВң. Ich glaube, das wГғВӨre nach Ende des Kriegszustandes eine gemeinsame Antwort auf die russische Bedrohung.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:02:31</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:27:33</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_52"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_66"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_77"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_78"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_218">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_218</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Sans rГғВ©industrialisation, pas de production. Elle passe par la prioritГғВ© donnГғВ©e ГғВ  nos entreprises dans les marchГғВ©s publics, par la relocalisation, chaque fois quГўВҖВҷelle est possible, de la production de mГғВ©dicaments et de principes actifs et par la protection de nos intГғВ©rГғВӘts stratГғВ©giques contre les pratiques commerciales dГғВ©loyales et la prГғВ©dation ГғВ©conomique. Nous voulons relancer la production en Europe et rГғВ©duire nos dГғВ©pendances. Comment garantir quГўВҖВҷune gestion centralisГғВ©e respectera la souverainetГғВ© des ГғВүtats? La Commission assumera-t-elle un virage protectionniste, quitte ГғВ  revenir sur certaines rГғВЁgles du commerce international? Le dГғВ©fi est de taille.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:17:51</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_161"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_217"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_218"/>
  </rdf:Description>
