  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_61">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_61</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Az omnibusz 1. ГғВ©s 2. tГғВәl kГғВ©sГ…В‘n jГғВ¶tt ГғВ©s kevГғВ©s. Annyi tГғВ¶rtГғВ©nik, hogy kozmetikГғВЎzni prГғВіbГғВЎljГғВЎk a korГғВЎbbi balfogГғВЎsokat. Mi, a jobboldalon, az ГғВјzleti ГғВ©rdekkГғВ©pviseletekkel kГғВ¶zГғВ¶sen szГғВіltunk, hogy rossz az irГғВЎny. ГғВ–nГғВ¶k ГғВЎrtottak EurГғВіpГғВЎnak, ГғВ–nГғВ¶k eurГғВіpaellenesek. HabГғВЎr a javaslat egyszerГ…ВұsГғВӯteni prГғВіbГғВЎl, az ambГғВӯciГғВіszint elmarad a szГғВјksГғВ©gestГ…В‘l. A szГғВ©pГғВ©szeti beavatkozГғВЎsoknГғВЎl tГғВ¶bbre van szГғВјksГғВ©g. Azt kellene megnГғВ©zni, melyek szabГғВЎlyozГғВЎsi oldalrГғВіl a fГ…В‘ problГғВ©mГғВЎk, tehГғВЎt mi akadГғВЎlyozza leginkГғВЎbb a cГғВ©geket abban, hogy forrГғВЎshoz jussanak, fejlesszenek ГғВ©s az alaptevГғВ©kenysГғВ©gГғВјkre koncentrГғВЎlhassanak jelentГғВ©sirkГғВЎlГғВЎs helyett.
Nem nyГғВәlnak elГғВ©ggГғВ© bГғВЎtran a taxonГғВіmiГғВЎhoz, tehГғВЎt tovГғВЎbbra is ideolГғВіgiai alapon diszkriminГғВЎlnak befektetГғВ©sek kГғВ¶zГғВ¶tt. Marad a zГғВ¶ld ideolГғВіgia, s ГғВәjra le fogja gyГ…В‘zni a versenykГғВ©pessГғВ©get. A forrГғВЎshoz jutГғВЎs persze azГғВЎltal is javulna, ha ГғВ–nГғВ¶k politikai okokbГғВіl nem tartanГғВЎk vissza az ГғВ©n hazГғВЎmtГғВіl is az uniГғВіs forrГғВЎsokat. Az UniГғВіban nem nevelni kell egymГғВЎst, hanem kГғВ¶zГғВ¶sen dolgozni a prosperitГғВЎsГғВ©rt. Sajnos ГғВ–nГғВ¶k ez ellen is tesznek. Az eurГғВіpai vГғВЎllalkozГғВЎsok ennГғВ©l tГғВ¶bbet ГғВ©rdemelnek. ValГғВіdi ГғВјzletbarГғВЎt fordulatra van szГғВјksГғВ©g, igazi tehercsГғВ¶kkentГғВ©ssel. Mi, patriГғВіtГғВЎk ezГғВ©rt fogunk dolgozni.</del:text>
    <del:text>SoustГ…ВҷeГ„ВҸme se na posilovГғВЎnГғВӯ aliance NATO. Investujme diplomatickГғВ© ГғВәsilГғВӯ i finanГ„ВҚnГғВӯ zdroje do tohoto projektu. Je potГ…Вҷeba se zastavit a o obrannГғВ© politice pГ…ВҷemГғВҪГ…ВЎlet s chladnou hlavou. NaГ…ВЎe vzГғВЎjemnГғВ© vztahy se SpojenГғВҪmi stГғВЎty americkГғВҪmi nynГғВӯ omezujeme pouze na otГғВЎzku Ukrajiny a nechГғВЎvГғВЎme je definovat tГғВӯmto konfliktem. PГ…Вҷitom je zde mnoho jinГғВҪch problГғВ©mГ…ВҜ, na kterГғВҪch potГ…Вҷebujeme spolupracovat. MГ„Вӣli bychom vyvinout maximГғВЎlnГғВӯ ГғВәsilГғВӯ na zajiГ…ВЎtГ„ВӣnГғВӯ mГғВӯru a vytvoГ…ВҷenГғВӯ fungujГғВӯcГғВӯch bezpeГ„ВҚnostnГғВӯch zГғВЎruk. ChytrГғВ© a zodpovГ„ВӣdnГғВ© Г…ВҷeГ…ВЎenГғВӯ je zajiГ…ВЎtГ„ВӣnГғВӯ konkurenceschopnosti naГ…ВЎeho hospodГғВЎГ…ВҷstvГғВӯ, udrГ…ВҫovГғВЎnГғВӯ pro Evropu vГғВҪhodnГғВҪch transatlantickГғВҪch vztahГ…ВҜ a vedenГғВӯ pragmatickГғВ© diplomatickГғВ© politiky.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:35:00</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:04:31</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_36"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_53"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_60"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_61"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_92">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_92</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Victor Negrescu,</del:name>
    <del:name>ГҺВ•ГҺВ»ГҺВөГҺВҝГҺВҪГҸВҺГҸВҒГҺВұ ГҺВңГҺВөГҺВ»ГҺВӯГҸВ„ГҺВ·,</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_459">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_459</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Eppure, nel vostro piano "Industria pulita" non riusciamo a ravvedere dei ravvedimenti sostanziali: confermate la folle corsa verso l'elettrico; sussurrate, appena, l'espressione "neutralitГғВ  tecnologica" e snobbate bellamente l'uso del nucleare per fini civili.
In piГғВ№, di fronte al tracollo dell'auto elettrica, anzichГғВ© fare retromarcia sul Green Deal in modo del tutto incoerente, decidete di investire 850 miliardi di euro per costruire carri armati. Ma da quando i carri armati sono green?
E lo fate, peraltro, senza alcun mandato parlamentare e chiedendo, ancora una volta, enormi sacrifici a quei cittadini che, a causa delle vostre politiche scellerate, non riescono ad arrivare alla fine del mese.
Il problema ГғВЁ che, mentre qui dentro si perde tempo a giocare a Risiko, lГғВ  fuori la Cina ogni giorno ci soffia quote di mercato e ogni minuto perso per salvare le nostre imprese ГғВЁ una pietra tombale sulla competitivitГғВ  europea.
(La Presidente toglie la parola all'oratrice)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:59:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_328"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_458"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_459"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_447">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_447</del:identifier>
    <del:text>En tres dГғВ©cadas, la producciГғВіn industrial europea ha caГғВӯdo del 36 al 15ГӮВ % del total mundial. ГӮВҝY por quГғВ©? Porque la UniГғВіn Europea, como ustedes saben, no ha parado de imponer mГғВЎs ideologГғВӯa, mГғВЎs regulaciГғВіn, mГғВЎs costes energГғВ©ticos y mГғВЎs barreras a la inversiГғВіn en su industria. Ahora dicen que necesitan 480ГӮВ 000 millones de euros para salvar lo que ustedes mismos han destruido, pero ningГғВәn fondo puede compensar su obsesiГғВіn con la hiperregulaciГғВіn y una polГғВӯtica energГғВ©tica suicida.
Y lo mГғВЎs cГғВӯnico, la verdad, es escuchar hoy aquГғВӯ a socialistas y populares ГўВҖВ”que han impuesto esta agenda verde radicalГўВҖВ” fingir una preocupaciГғВіn por las consecuencias de sus propias polГғВӯticas. La imposiciГғВіn forzada del coche elГғВ©ctrico y la prohibiciГғВіn del motor de combustiГғВіn son el mejor ejemplo de este suicidio industrial. Y, por otra parte, ГӮВҝquГғВ© sentido tiene, seГғВұor comisario, presumir de una reducciГғВіn de emisiones cuando lo que estamos haciendo realmente es exportarlas?
Si de verdad queremos reindustrializar Europa lo que necesitamos es energГғВӯa barata, acceso real a materias primas y libertad para innovar sin que los burГғВіcratas de Bruselas decidan quГғВ© sectores deben sobrevivir y cuГғВЎles no. De lo contrario, seГғВұor comisario, su BrГғВәjula sГғВіlo servirГғВЎ para seГғВұalar el camino de salida a las pocas industrias europeas.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:43:36</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_318"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_446"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_447"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_302">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_302</del:identifier>
    <del:text>But let me change and swap to the whole discussion maybe we were facing this this afternoon. I listened, of course, very carefully to the discussion. Thank you to all the speakers of this afternoon.
For me, the clearest message is that the European Union needs a migration and asylum policy that is 100ГӮВ % credible. That is important, and that's what we try to deliver.
The pact has laid down a strong foundation and, of course, that has to be implemented now. That's the basis we have. But as a lot of you said, there was this missing piece we are talking about today.
I think EU citizens expect us to complete the whole picture and have this comprehensive approach. Also, this whole picture has to be completed. They want to know that the system operates efficiently; that is, I think, very important, so that we are able to properly integrate all migrants who do have a right to stay.
For migrants with no right to stay, they want them to be treated fairly, yes, but firmly, as you rightly mentioned. They want to know that dangerous individuals with no right to be in the European Union will not pose a threat, at the end of the day, for all of us. They are not anti-immigration, but they want migration that is legal and targeted at our labour market's needs also.
At this stage they are no longer asking us, actually. They are demanding that we that we act. It's up to us to listen carefully, to assume our responsibilities and also to finish building the common European migration system we promise. One hundred percentГӮВ of it, actually. I'm looking very much forward to discussing all the topics in a constructive way in the next weeks to bring these rules into effect.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:24:32</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_175"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_301"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_302"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_483">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_483</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Le premier est de recrГғВ©er de nouvelles dГғВ©pendances ГғВ  dГўВҖВҷautres ГғВ©nergies ou ГғВ  dГўВҖВҷautres continents, ce qui pose un risque de fragilitГғВ© ГғВ©conomique et gГғВ©opolitique. Le deuxiГғВЁme est de considГғВ©rer quГўВҖВҷil faut tout nationaliser et tout planifier pour pouvoir faire descendre le prix de lГўВҖВҷГғВ©nergie. Il nous faut une feuille de route avec une analyse qui montre que nos entreprises pourront dГғВ©gager des marges et donc ГғВӘtre plus compГғВ©titives avec une ГғВ©nergie moins chГғВЁre. JusquГўВҖВҷГғВ  prГғВ©sent, je ne connais pas de systГғВЁme nationalisГғВ© qui permette une efficacitГғВ© ГғВ©conomique.
Le troisiГғВЁme ГўВҖВ“ГӮВ et, ГғВ©ventuellement, le quatriГғВЁmeГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ point que je voulais soulever, cГўВҖВҷГғВ©tait la question des enjeux internationaux. Je pense que, dans un moment qui est agitГғВ© dГўВҖВҷun point de vue international ГўВҖВ“ГӮВ lГўВҖВҷEurope est dans une situation complexe vis-ГғВ -vis des discussions et des menaces sur les droits de douane europГғВ©ensГӮВ ГўВҖВ“, la rГғВ©ponse devra ГғВӘtre globale. Elle est globale sur le volet compГғВ©titivitГғВ©, et nous avons tenu ГғВ  pouvoir aborder un certain nombre de sujets, tel le prix de lГўВҖВҷГғВ©nergie, qui sГўВҖВҷavГғВЁre ГғВӘtre un facteur de compГғВ©titivitГғВ© pour lГўВҖВҷensemble des industries europГғВ©ennes.
Dans ce cadre-lГғВ , je veux rebondir sur quelques interrogations qui ont ГғВ©tГғВ© faites sur le prix de lГўВҖВҷГғВ©nergie et notre capacitГғВ© ГғВ  le garantir dans le cadre des PPA. Oui, la Banque europГғВ©enne dГўВҖВҷinvestissement servira de garante pour les PPA, pour pouvoir sГғВ©curiser et rГғВ©duire les risques associГғВ©s ГғВ  ces PPA, qui se multiplient et qui sont une bonne chose, puisquГўВҖВҷils retirent la volatilitГғВ© du cours de lГўВҖВҷГғВ©nergie et permettent de sortir du cours du prix carbonГғВ© de notre ГғВ©lectricitГғВ© les contrats de ce genre qui sont passГғВ©s entre les producteurs dГўВҖВҷГғВ©nergie et les industriels. Cette question, en tout cas, sera au cГ…В“ur de nos prioritГғВ©s pour donner de la visibilitГғВ©, sГғВ©curiser lГўВҖВҷapprovisionnement et garantir des prix bas de lГўВҖВҷГғВ©nergie dans la pГғВ©riode. CГўВҖВҷest une mesure dГўВҖВҷurgence, mais que nous souhaitons pГғВ©renniser et ГғВ©largir dans les prochains mois et les prochaines annГғВ©es.
La rГғВ©ponse globale concerne le prix de lГўВҖВҷГғВ©nergie ГўВҖВ“ГӮВ je lГўВҖВҷai ГғВ©voquГғВ©ГӮВ ГўВҖВ“, mais ГғВ©galement la demande de produits dГғВ©carbonГғВ©s ГўВҖВ“ГӮВ je lГўВҖВҷai ГғВ©voquГғВ© ГғВ©galement sur la question des matiГғВЁres premiГғВЁres et de notre capacitГғВ© ГғВ  pouvoir produire de nouveau des matiГғВЁres premiГғВЁres en Europe. Oui, il faudra, ГғВ  un moment donnГғВ©, rouvrir des mines de matiГғВЁres rares, de terres rares et de matiГғВЁres premiГғВЁres en Europe, si nous ne voulons pas dГғВ©pendre de partenariats, et ГғВ©ventuellement de mines qui font travailler des salariГғВ©s dans des conditions que nous nГўВҖВҷacceptons pas nous-mГғВӘmes, EuropГғВ©ens. Ces partenariats ne seront pas conclus avec notamment des pays qui font travailler un certain nombre de travailleurs dans des conditions absolument dГғВ©sastreuses. Je pense notamment ГғВ  la RDC: vu les conditions gГғВ©opolitiques du pays, on avait, concernant diverses matiГғВЁres premiГғВЁres, plusieurs partenariats envisageables avec la RDC, et qui ne me le semblent plus aujourdГўВҖВҷhui.
La voie ГғВ  suivre pour lГўВҖВҷEurope doit ГғВӘtre la rГғВ©duction des risques associГғВ©s ГғВ  nos matiГғВЁres premiГғВЁres, y compris en produisant en Europe. CГўВҖВҷest comme lГўВҖВҷГғВ©nergie. Nous ne produisons pas de pГғВ©trole, nous ne produisons pas de gaz et nous avons un certain nombre dГўВҖВҷinstruments pour pouvoir ГғВӘtre autonomes dans notre capacitГғВ© ГғВ  produire de lГўВҖВҷГғВ©nergie, dans ce moment qui est crucial, y compris pour notre industrie: prix de lГўВҖВҷГғВ©nergie, financements, circularitГғВ© et, enfin, formation et compГғВ©tences, puisque ces plans sectoriels se font ГғВ©galement avec les syndicats et les forces professionnelles. Nous les avons reГғВ§us, nous avons construit les plans sectoriels avec eux, que ce soit sur lГўВҖВҷautomobile, lГўВҖВҷacier ou la chimie, et nous poursuivrons cette mГғВ©thode de concertation et de co-construction des rГғВ©ponses, qui doivent correspondre ГғВ  une rГғВ©alitГғВ© ГғВ©conomique. Vous lГўВҖВҷavez compris, notre objectif est dГўВҖВҷaccГғВ©lГғВ©rer la dГғВ©carbonation pour des questions stratГғВ©giques, pour des questions de compГғВ©titivitГғВ©, mais aussi pour rendre lГўВҖВҷEurope plus forte dans ce moment complexe et incertain au niveau international.
Je viendrai prochainement en audition au Parlement europГғВ©en dans les commissions ITRE, ECON, IMCO, JURI, ENVI et INTA, qui mГўВҖВҷont conviГғВ©. Nous aborderons tous ces sujets dans le dГғВ©tail, et je remercie ГғВ©galement les groupes politiques pour leur soutien.
ГғВүvitons de politiser le pacte vert. Il a probablement donnГғВ© un certain nombre de sueurs froides administratives ГғВ  nos entreprises, et nous essayons de rГғВ©gler cela. Mais, une fois encore, quand les sujets de notre stratГғВ©gie ГғВ©conomique et de nos objectifs climatiques se rejoignent, je crois que cela devrait rГғВ©unir une trГғВЁs grande partie de cet hГғВ©micycle.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:30:46</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_297"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_482"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_483"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_400">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_400</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:46:31</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_286"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_399"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_400"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_538">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_538</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Instead of supporting and upholding international justice, the EU continues business as usual with Israel. In the meantime, our credibility in the global south crumbles by the day with these double standards. As Israel's largest trading partner, we have a responsibility to force change and end the atrocities in Palestine ГўВҖВ“ stop arms trade, cease this association agreement and impose sanctions.
So tonight, here are my questions: when will we finally stop business as usual with the aggressor? When will we stop applying these double standards? And when will we start treating Palestinian lives as human lives?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:58:55</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_375"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_537"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_538"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_68">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_68</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Julien Leonardelli</del:name>
    <del:name>RaphaГғВ«l Glucksmann</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PfE"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_220">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_220</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Silvia Sardone</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PfE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_175">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_175</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Propun, ГғВ®n acest sens, introducerea unui paГҲВҷaport european pentru radioizotopi medicali, integrat ГғВ®n dosarul digital european de sГ„ВғnГ„Вғtate. Acest instrument digital ar permite identificarea rapidГ„Вғ ГҲВҷi discretГ„Вғ a pacienГҲВӣilor trataГҲВӣi recent cu radioizotopi, simplificГғВўnd controalele de securitate ГҲВҷi protejГғВўnd totodatГ„Вғ confidenГҲВӣialitatea datelor personale.</del:text>
    <del:text>DoamnГ„Вғ preГҲВҷedintГ„Вғ, dragi colegi, ГғВ®mi aduc aminte, doamnГ„Вғ comisarГ„Вғ, ГғВ®n momentul ГғВ®n care eram ministra familiei ГғВ®n RomГғВўnia ГҲВҷi dumneavoastrГ„Вғ ministra fondurilor europene, cГғВўte lucruri frumoase am realizat ГғВ®mpreunГ„Вғ pentru femeile din RomГғВўnia ГҲВҷi sunt absolut convinsГ„Вғ cГ„Вғ veГҲВӣi pune aceastГ„Вғ experienГҲВӣГ„Вғ pe care o aveГҲВӣi ГғВ®n slujba tuturor femeilor din Europa. Noi, femeile, suntem obiГҲВҷnuite ca ГғВ®n jurul datei de 8 martie sГ„Вғ primim foarte multe flori ГҲВҷi promisiuni, inclusiv sub forma unor proiecte frumoase care, din pГ„Вғcate, pot sГ„Вғ spun, rГ„ВғmГғВўn prГ„Вғfuite ГғВ®n anumite sertare pГғВўnГ„Вғ anul viitor.
TotuГҲВҷi, vreau sГ„Вғ vГ„Вғ asigur cГ„Вғ nu suntem blazate ГҲВҷi nici nu renunГҲВӣГ„Вғm, ci vom lupta ГғВ®mpreunГ„Вғ pentru dezideratele noastre ГҲВҷi ГғВ®n special pentru femeile care au mai puГҲВӣine oportunitГ„ВғГҲВӣi. Pare ireal, dar ГғВ®n 2025 trebuie ГғВ®ncГ„Вғ sГ„Вғ vorbim despre protecГҲВӣia drepturilor femeilor. Avem ГғВ®n continuare probleme de reprezentare: prea puГҲВӣine femei iau parte la decizii care le privesc direct. Avem nevoie sГ„Вғ impunem cote de gen pentru accesul femeilor ГғВ®n poziГҲВӣii de conducere politicГ„Вғ ГҲВҷi administrativГ„Вғ. ГғВҺmpreunГ„Вғ cu doamna comisarГ„Вғ europeanГ„Вғ, ca ministrГ„Вғ a familiei, am propus ГғВ®n RomГғВўnia o lege prin care ГғВ®n toate consiliile de administraГҲВӣie sГ„Вғ fie incluse ГҲВҷi femei, 30ГӮВ % femei. RГ„Вғspunsul a fost unul dezarmant. RГ„Вғspund sub formГ„Вғ de ГғВ®ntrebare, dar vom avea atГғВўt de multe femei (...)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:32:51</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:18:20</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_112"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_127"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_174"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_175"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_93">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_93</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The real obstacle remains massive climate regulation compared to our competitors. Let's face it, too strict policies are killing our competitiveness and putting jobs at risk. What Europe needs is not endless directives from Brussels, but policies that will give Europe the chance to win. It is time to break the chains of too strict climate regulation, let businesses thrive and restore Europe to the top of the global economy.</del:text>
    <del:text>Liebe Kolleginnen und Kollegen, an diejenigen, die hier immer die alten RГғВ¶mer zitieren, dass diejenigen, die den Frieden wollen, jetzt fГғВјr den Krieg rГғВјsten sollten. Ich mГғВ¶chte euch sagen: Dann geht doch ab an die Front, aber schreit nicht nach der BevГғВ¶lkerung! Unsere SГғВ¶hne, unsere Kinder kriegt ihr nicht.
Die BevГғВ¶lkerung in Europa sehnt sich nicht nach Krieg, sie sehnt sich nach Frieden.ГӮВ Und unsere Geschichte in Europa hat uns beigebracht, dass immer mehr Waffen nicht zu Frieden beitragen werden.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:22:27</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:44:59</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_64"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_80"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_92"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_93"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_507">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_507</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The EU needs to invest in the political economy of reconciliation as a matter of urgency. The Syria conference that takes place next Monday is the ninth one, but different from every other ГўВҖВ“ for some very obvious reasons and some less obvious reasons. The most obvious is the change in regime. The less obvious is the fact that international aid has collapsed in the last 12ГӮВ months.
My plea to you, Commissioner, is to concentrate on the agricultural industry, to concentrate on replanting, on irrigation, on bakeries, on the core of the regrowth of the Syrian economy and the pathway to that sustainable peace.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:10:20</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_358"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_506"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_507"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem17">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Topic"/>
    <del:identifier>creitem17</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Establishing the Reform and Growth Facility for the Republic of Moldova (debate)</del:name>
    <del:name>Roadmap for Women`s Rights (debate)</del:name>
    <skos:related rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem8"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_436">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_436</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Brussel beweert dat deze deal de Europese industrie moet versterken. Maar tegelijk worden bedrijven verplicht tot peperdure CO2-reducties, extra regelgeving en torenhoge energiekosten. De oplossing is niet nog een Europees plan, maar het afschaffen van de Green Deal. We moeten daarom inzetten op drie zaken: ten eerste betaalbare energie door kernenergie, ten tweede bescherming van onze industrie tegen oneerlijke concurrentie, en ten derde minder EU-bemoeienis en minder bureaucratie. Want enkel op die manier heeft de industrie weer toekomst in Europa.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:31:01</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_312"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_435"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_436"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_209">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_209</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Jaroslav BГ…Вҫoch</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PfE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_339">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_339</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Un tavolo, da cui ricordo, noi siamo stati espulsi senza neanche essere stati avvertiti, a meno che il ministro Lubilius non lo fosse stato. Questo ГғВЁ un vulnus incredibile, ГғВЁ il vero punto di queste trattative: tenere fuori l'Europa.
Allora, io vi domando: mentre prepariamo giustamente questo piano di difesa, non dobbiamo porci il problema e la prioritГғВ  di tornare a quel tavolo? Ministro, noi rischiamo oggi di fare un grande discorso militare ma di tenere fuori la politica a cominciare dal ruolo del Parlamento.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:29:31</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_244"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_338"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_339"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_380">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_380</del:identifier>
    <del:text>A UniГғВЈo Europeia jГғВЎ despende hoje trГғВӘs vezes e meia mais em gastos militares do que a RГғВәssia e 1,3 vezes mais do que a China. Qual ГғВ© o sinal que se dГғВЎ ao resto do mundo com esta corrida aos armamentos?
Como ГғВ© que desviar verbas dos fundos da coesГғВЈo para os gastos militares pode corresponder ГғВ s necessidades e expectativas dos povos? O senhor deputado nГғВЈo acha que se pГғВөe em risco nГғВЈo apenas aquilo que era prioritГғВЎrio para a vida dos povos, como, ainda por cima, se acentua a ameaГғВ§a e o risco de a confrontaГғВ§ГғВЈo e a guerra se tornarem mais globais?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:22:02</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_40"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_379"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_380"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_163">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_163</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Veronika CifrovГғВЎ OstrihoГ…ВҲovГғВЎ</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Renew"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_59">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_59</del:identifier>
    <del:text>And my question is ГўВҖВ“ to S&amp;D ГўВҖВ“ you ask to work with us, we are ready to work with everybody here. But the question is, what is S&amp;D actually ready to change in the current proposals? What is it?</del:text>
    <del:text>Europa lo tiene claro: frente a la sumisiГғВіn, liderazgo, acciГғВіn y firmeza. Y esta es la peor noticia para Putin. No renunciaremos a la libertad, no descansaremos hasta una paz justa y duradera. Nuestro apoyo a Ucrania ha sido claro y firme desde el primer minuto, algo que no todos pueden decir aquГғВӯ.
Mientras Estados miembros como Polonia y Alemania redoblan su inversiГғВіn en seguridad y defensa, EspaГғВұa tiene el Gobierno que menos invierte en defensa en Europa, solo un 1,2ГӮВ %. EspaГғВұa es uno de los paГғВӯses que mГғВЎs gas compra a Putin desde que comenzГғВі la guerra: 9ГӮВ 000 millonesГӮВ de euros. SГғВЎnchez es el equilibrista de una coaliciГғВіn de Gobierno sin presupuestos ni respaldo parlamentario que le exige la salida de la OTAN y blanquea a dictadores. Todo con un mismo objetivo: debilitar a EspaГғВұa y a Europa desde dentro.
Europa debe asegurarse de que cada euro europeo para defensa se dedique a ello y no se repita lo que ha hecho SГғВЎnchez con los fondos de Next Generation EU: usarlos como si fueran propiedad de ГғВ©l y de su Partido Socialista. El Partido Popular Europeo lo dice bien claro y bien fuerte: sГғВӯ a la UniГғВіn Europea de Defensa y sГғВӯ a una soberanГғВӯa estratГғВ©gica real. La historia ya nos ha enseГғВұado el precio de la inacciГғВіn y esta vez no podemos fallar.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:33:17</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:01:35</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_35"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_51"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_58"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_59"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_189">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_189</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Ana Catarina Mendes</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_257">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_257</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Esta ГғВ© uma proposta que aprofunda o Pacto em matГғВ©ria de MigraГғВ§ГғВЈo e Asilo da pior forma, violando e desrespeitando os direitos fundamentais dos migrantes. ГғВү ГғВіbvio que assume e reconhece medidas de detenГғВ§ГғВЈo, particularmente em relaГғВ§ГғВЈo aos menores, que atГғВ© hoje eram negadas, mas que aparecem no texto desta proposta de regulamento bem assumidas.
Mas, infelizmente, hГғВЎ um aspeto com o qual nГғВЈo posso concordar com a senhora deputada: ГғВ© que, infelizmente, em Portugal, nГғВіs jГғВЎ tГғВӯnhamos uma aproximaГғВ§ГғВЈo disto. Porque, quando o atual Governo portuguГғВӘs decidiu introduzir as alteraГғВ§ГғВөes legislativas que introduziu na polГғВӯtica de migraГғВ§ГғВөes, foi precisamente para impedir o reconhecimento da situaГғВ§ГғВЈo dos migrantes que estГғВЈo indocumentados, e essa proposta de regulamento, infelizmente, tambГғВ©m dГғВЎ cobertura a essas mГғВЎs prГғВЎticas do atual Governo em Portugal, que, se tudo correr bem, chegarГғВЎ hoje ao fim.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:25:06</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_40"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_256"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_257"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_254">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_254</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Dopo il fallito accordo tra Regno Unito e Ruanda, si ipotizza l'espulsione dagli Stati membri verso Stati terzi con cui si stipulano accordi che non contengono garanzie di diritti umani e che non tengono conto dei legami del migrante con il Paese terzo contraente. Non ГғВЁ neanche previsto, alla fine, il ritorno nel Paese d'origine: sembra evocare ancora un altro esempio fallimentare dopo quello Inghilterra-Ruanda.
Si finisce infatti con il dare legittimazione al recente protocollo fra Italia ed Albania, diventato un monumento di inefficienza e spreco di risorse, denunciato dall'opinione pubblica: ГғВЁ un monumento alla violazione dei diritti umani, condannato dai tribunali italiani.
Questo atteggiamento alla Ponzio Pilato non mi sembra degno dell'Unione europea nella quale crediamo. Voglio sperare che l'Unione europea alla fine contribuirГғВ  al rispetto di tutti gli esseri umani, perchГғВ© anche i migranti, signor Commissario, sono esseri umani.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:21:19</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_188"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_253"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_254"/>
  </rdf:Description>
