  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_549">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_549</del:identifier>
    <del:text>ГҺВ— ГҺВҙГҺВ№ГҺВөГҺВёГҺВҪГҺВ®ГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВҝГҺВ№ГҺВҪГҸВҢГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҺВҝГҸВҶГҺВөГҺВҜГҺВ»ГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВјГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВ®ГҸВғГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВәГҺВ»ГҺВөГҺВҜГҺВҪГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҺВұ ГҺВјГҺВ¬ГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВұ. ГҺВ— ГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВјГҸВүГҸВҒГҺВ·ГҸВғГҺВҜГҺВұ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҺВҷГҸВғГҸВҒГҺВұГҺВ®ГҺВ» ГҸВҖГҸВҒГҺВӯГҸВҖГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВјГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВ®ГҸВғГҺВөГҺВ№. ГҺВ‘ГҸВҖГҺВұГҺВ№ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВҚГҺВјГҺВө ГҺВ¬ГҺВјГҺВөГҸВғГҺВ· ГҺВәГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВ¬ГҸВҖГҺВұГҸВ…ГҸВғГҺВ· ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҸВҖГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҸВҢГҸВӮ, ГҺВ¬ГҸВҒГҸВғГҺВ· ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВҝГҺВәГҺВ»ГҺВөГҺВ№ГҸВғГҺВјГҺВҝГҸВҚ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВҙГҺВҜГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ГҺВ· ГҺВ»ГҸВҚГҸВғГҺВ· ГҺВіГҺВ№ГҺВұ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҺВҪ ГҸВҖГҺВұГҺВ»ГҺВұГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВҪГҺВ№ГҺВұГҺВәГҸВҢ ГҺВ»ГҺВұГҸВҢ. ГҺВҹ ГҸВҮГҸВҒГҸВҢГҺВҪГҺВҝГҸВӮ ГҺВіГҺВ№ГҺВұ ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВҙГҺВӯГҸВ„ГҺВөГҸВҒГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҺВҙГҺВ·ГҺВ»ГҸВҺГҸВғГҺВөГҺВ№ГҸВӮ ГҺВӯГҸВҮГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҺВөГҺВ»ГҺВөГҺВ№ГҸВҺГҸВғГҺВөГҺВ№. ГҺВү ГҺВөГҺВҜГҺВјГҺВұГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҺВјГҺВө ГҸВ„ГҺВ· ГҺВҙГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ГҺВҝГҸВғГҸВҚГҺВҪГҺВ· ГҺВ® ГҺВөГҺВҜГҺВјГҺВұГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҸВғГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҺВӯГҺВҪГҺВҝГҸВҮГҺВҝГҺВ№ ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВҝ ГҺВӯГҺВіГҺВәГҺВ»ГҺВ·ГҺВјГҺВұ. ГҺВ”ГҺВөГҺВҪ ГҸВ…ГҸВҖГҺВ¬ГҸВҒГҸВҮГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВәГҺВ¬ГҸВ„ГҺВ№ ГҺВөГҺВҪГҺВҙГҺВ№ГҺВ¬ГҺВјГҺВөГҸВғГҺВҝ. ГҺВ— ГҺВұГҺВҪГҺВёГҸВҒГҸВүГҸВҖГҺВ№ГҺВ¬ ГҺВјГҺВұГҸВӮ, ГҺВ»ГҺВҝГҺВ№ГҸВҖГҸВҢГҺВҪ, ГҺВҙГҺВҝГҺВәГҺВ№ГҺВјГҺВ¬ГҺВ¶ГҺВөГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВ№. ГҺВ‘ГҸВӮ ГҺВјГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҺВөГҸВҖГҺВ№ГҸВ„ГҸВҒГҺВӯГҸВҲГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВјГҺВө ГҺВ· ГҸВғГҺВ№ГҸВүГҸВҖГҺВ® ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВіГҺВҜГҺВҪГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҸВғГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҺВөГҺВҪГҺВҝГҸВҮГҺВ®.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T23:13:16</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_382"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_548"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_549"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_461">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_461</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Energiepolitik ist Sicherheitspolitik. Wir dГғВјrfen nicht lГғВӨnger abhГғВӨngig sein von Autokraten und auch nicht von denen, die es gerne wГғВӨren. Eine erfolgreiche Energiewende mit einem modernen, grenzГғВјbergreifenden Stromnetz sichert unsere Freiheit. Eine echte Energie-Union, wo das Baltikum von der Sonnenenergie Spaniens und Kroatien von der Windenergie aus der Nordsee profitiert: Das ist ein Schutzschild fГғВјr unsere Wirtschaft, fГғВјr unsere GesellschaftГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ nicht mehr und nicht weniger.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:02:38</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_329"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_460"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_461"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_256">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_256</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Pergunto-lhe se isto vai ou nГғВЈo vai no sentido de uma violaГғВ§ГғВЈo gritante daquilo que sГғВЈo os direitos humanos destas pessoas.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:24:20</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_189"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_255"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_256"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_486">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_486</del:identifier>
    <del:text>ElГ…В‘szГғВ¶r, a Budapesti Nyilatkozattal ГғВ¶sszhangban, az iparpolitika kГғВ¶zГғВ©ppontjГғВЎban a versenykГғВ©pessГғВ©gnek kell ГғВЎllnia. Ehelyett BrГғВјsszel, a tagГғВЎllamok dГғВ¶ntГғВ©sГғВ©t megkerГғВјlve, nem vГғВЎltoztat a ZГғВ¶ld MegГғВЎllapodГғВЎson, hanem ГғВәjabb klГғВӯmacГғВ©lokat prГғВіbГғВЎl az iparra ГғВ©s a vГғВЎllalkozГғВЎsokra kГғВ©nyszerГғВӯteni. Ez hibГғВЎs megkГғВ¶zelГғВӯtГғВ©s - a zГғВ¶ldГғВӯtГғВ©s nem mehet a versenykГғВ©pessГғВ©g rovГғВЎsГғВЎra.

MГғВЎsodszor, bГғВЎr az ipar szenved a magas energiaГғВЎraktГғВіl, a BizottsГғВЎg tovГғВЎbbra sem foglalkozik ezzel kellГ…В‘kГғВ©ppen. A Tisztaipar-megГғВЎllapodГғВЎsban javasolt intГғВ©zkedГғВ©sek elГғВ©gtelenek az energiaГғВЎrak szГғВјksГғВ©ges mГғВ©rtГғВ©kГ…Вұ letГғВ¶rГғВ©sГғВ©re. Ehhez leginkГғВЎbb a rossz szabГғВЎlyozГғВЎsok felГғВјlvizsgГғВЎlatГғВЎra ГғВ©s az energiaszankciГғВіk azonnali eltГғВ¶rlГғВ©sГғВ©re lenne szГғВјksГғВ©g.

Harmadszor, a versenykГғВ©pessГғВ©g elГ…В‘mozdГғВӯtГғВЎsГғВЎhoz a bГғВјrokrГғВЎciacsГғВ¶kkentГғВ©s mellett az energia- ГғВ©s kГғВјlГғВ¶nГғВ¶sen a villamosenergia-infrastruktГғВәra fejlesztГғВ©sГғВ©nek fokozГғВЎsa szГғВјksГғВ©ges. Fel kell gyorsГғВӯtani az ГғВЎramhГғВЎlГғВіzati ГғВ©s elektromos tГғВ¶ltГ…В‘infrastruktГғВәra-beruhГғВЎzГғВЎsokat, amihez az eddiginГғВ©l erГ…В‘sebb tГғВЎmogatГғВЎsra van szГғВјksГғВ©g BrГғВјsszeltГ…В‘l.

Ez ГғВӯgy nem elГғВ©gsГғВ©ges. A BizottsГғВЎgnak vissza kell tГғВ©rnie a Budapesti Nyilatkozathoz, ГғВ©s annak mentГғВ©n kell dolgoznia. Mi, PatriГғВіtГғВЎk ezt kГғВ¶veteljГғВјk.</del:text>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_346"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_536">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_536</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Los Acuerdos de Abraham de sus hermanos ГғВЎrabes vecinos debieron avisarles. Pero como Gaza, y no solo Gaza, se acostumbrГғВі a vivir de dinero ajeno y Europa, los Estados Unidos y otros han pagado a los gazatГғВӯes para ser refugiados eternos y odiar y querer asesinar judГғВӯos, han seguido abrazados al terrorismo, algo que se ha vuelto a ver en los canjes por rehenes: no parece que hayan aprendido.
Gaza tiene que ser limpiada de terroristas y se ha visto en estos meses que se estГғВЎ aГғВәn lejos de ello. ConvendrГғВӯa a todos que la poblaciГғВіn gazatГғВӯ colaborara, que soltaran a todos los rehenes y se entregaran los tГғВәneles, todas las armas y esos uniformes planchaditos que se han utilizado en esos desfiles de propaganda cuando han soltado ГўВҖВ”humillГғВЎndolosГўВҖВ” a los rehenes. Si no lo hacen, lo harГғВЎn las fuerzas israelГғВӯes.
Si los vecinos ГғВЎrabes ГўВҖВ”Jordania y EgiptoГўВҖВ” acogieran a los gazatГғВӯes, como los vecinos de Ucrania acogieron a los ucranianos, serГғВӯa mГғВЎs fГғВЎcil hacer todo este proceso, pero vamos a ver quГғВ© disposiciГғВіn hay. En todo caso, la base terrorista no puede subsistir.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:55:43</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_373"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_535"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_536"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_27">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_27</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Tobiasz BocheГ…В„ski,</del:name>
    <del:name>Anna BryГ…ВӮka</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_NI"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem19">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Topic"/>
    <del:identifier>creitem19</del:identifier>
    <del:name>One-minute speeches on matters of political importance</del:name>
    <del:name>Presentation of the proposal on a new common approach on returns (debate)</del:name>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_270">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_270</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Los inmigrantes ilegales y las organizaciones que los ayudan se las saben todas y alargan los procedimientos administrativos o judiciales sin fin. No lo podemos permitir. Toda deportaciГғВіn debe incluir el examen de la solicitud de asilo y producir efecto ejecutivo inmediato. Toda persona que entra o permanece sin permiso de residencia o visado en vigor debe ser detenida e internada ГўВҖВ”en un centro de detenciГғВіn o en un tercer paГғВӯs seguroГўВҖВ” por todo el tiempo que sea necesario para que vuelva a su paГғВӯs. Solo asГғВӯ pondremos fin al efecto llamada: cuando sepan que hay derechos que solo tenemos los europeos o los extranjeros residentes legales.
Para asegurar los retornos debemos incluir un mecanismo de garantГғВӯa por el cual la ayuda al desarrollo, los acuerdos comerciales y la emisiГғВіn de visados sean suspendidos automГғВЎticamente si el tercer paГғВӯs no coopera con los retornos, alegando la clГғВЎusula de orden pГғВәblico que ya tenemos en nuestros acuerdos internacionales, con lo cual no hay que firmar nada nuevo. Nada de esto estГғВЎ en la propuesta de la ComisiГғВіn, que nos mantiene en el fracaso y nos lanza al abismo. Vamos a intentar mejorar.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:42:18</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_200"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_269"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_270"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_405">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_405</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The special European Council last week gave a strong impetus to our work on European defence. The EU leaders had the first concrete discussion based on options tabled by the Commission. The President of the Commission presented them this morning. The EU leaders will continue their discussion on the European Council meetings next week and in June. As presidency of the Council, we stand ready to proactively take forward all initiatives that will reinforce European defence. I look forward to our continued exchange on this key topic and, of course, the forthcoming white paper on the future of European defence.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:54:47</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_2"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_404"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_405"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_450">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_450</del:identifier>
    <del:text>CГўВҖВҷest plus ou moins la question que je vous avais posГғВ©e lors de votre audition en octobre, Monsieur le Commissaire. Nous voici ГғВ  prГғВ©sent avec la proposition du pacte pour une industrie propre, qui, je lГўВҖВҷavoue, contient 36ГӮВ fois le mot circulaire ou circularitГғВ©.
But where are the concrete policies and financing to build a secondary raw material market? How can we ease transport and recycling materials across EU borders? Nothing concrete. And looking at one of the industries in dire need of transition, the textile industry, what are we missing to actually scale up fibre-to-fibre recycling?
You might answer that this will come as part of the circular economy act, but we will have to wait 21ГӮВ months for that, so no real action will be taken to boost the circular economy with this industrial policy. My fear is that this is more than a mismatch in timing. This is actually a real strategic mistake.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:48:10</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_321"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_449"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_450"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_367">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_367</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Wenn ich dann hier die Reden hГғВ¶re von der extremen Rechten und der extremen Linken, wie die uns unterstellen, dass wir als EuropГғВӨer Krieg wollen, dann wird mir wirklich schlecht. Wenn man sich das anschaut, wie historisch vergesslich diese Kollegen sind, von linker und rechter Seite, dann sollten diese Kollegen mal weniger TikTok schauen, damit ihr Wissen nicht begrenzt auf 30 oder 60ГӮВ Sekunden ist, sondern sollten einfach mal ein bisschen mehr in den GeschichtsbГғВјchern lesen.
Wladimir Putin hat unmittelbar nach seiner ersten Wahl zum PrГғВӨsidenten von Russland die Tschetschenen angegriffen, 1999. Dieser Mann tГғВ¶tet seit 1999, seit 25ГӮВ Jahren, Menschen auf diesem Kontinent und an den Grenzen seines Kontinents und auch indirekt in Afrika mit seiner WagnerГўВҖВ‘Gruppe und auch stellvertretend in Syrien und ГғВјberall woanders. Wir mГғВјssen verteidigungsfГғВӨhig werden, um diesen Mann endlich zu stoppen, damit er weiГғВҹ: So geht es nicht weiter! All seinen Nachfolgern, wenn er mal beim lieben Gott ist, mГғВјssen wir auch ein Zeichen setzen.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:03:28</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_265"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_366"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_367"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_284">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_284</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Radan Kanev</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_267">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_267</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Che cosa succederГғВ  poi alle persone quando sono nel Paese terzo? Nessuno lo sa. Per di piГғВ№, non vi sarebbe alcun obbligo di trasparenza di rendere pubblici questi accordi con i Paesi terzi. PerchГғВ©?
Ancora: chi viene trovato sul suolo europeo senza documenti validi potrГғВ  essere detenuto fino a due anni ГўВҖВ“ prima erano 18 mesi. I dati, per inciso, ci dicono che piГғВ№ si allunga il periodo di trattenimento, meno diventa probabile il rimpatrio. Ma questo ГғВЁ un altro discorso.
Per le famiglie con i bambini minori non accompagnati, la detenzione sarebbe l'ultima opzione, ma non dovrebbe proprio essere un'opzione. Davvero l'Unione europea pensa di poter mettere in gabbia per due anni dei ragazzini che non hanno commesso alcun reato? Ci sono molte cose inaccettabili in questa proposta, sulle quali vigileremo e lavoreremo.
Caro Commissario, sentiamo dire spesso che l'approccio europeo deve essere fermo e giusto e finora abbiamo visto molto bene la parte ferma: perГғВІ vogliamo vedere anche la parte giusta.
(L'oratrice accetta di rispondere a una domanda "cartellino blu")</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:39:11</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_198"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_266"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_267"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_113">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_113</del:identifier>
    <del:text>ГӮВҝPuede caminar en la buena direcciГғВіn la reforma del Reglamento InvestEU porque permite optimizar todos los instrumentos y fondos actualmente disponiblesГӮВ ГўВҖВ”hasta los heredadosГўВҖВ” para intentar incentivar la innovaciГғВіn, la investigaciГғВіn y la competitividad sin renunciar al compromiso con la sostenibilidad y el medio ambiente, al que se dedica prГғВЎcticamente la mitad de las inversiones del Reglamento? Puede, pero no camina en la buena direcciГғВіn la degradaciГғВіn de la diligencia debida, ni de los objetivos climГғВЎticos, ni del compromiso medioambiental.
Porque si la ComisiГғВіn hace eso al servicio de los grandes intereses econГғВіmicos que se quejan del exceso de regulaciГғВіn, tenemos derecho a sospechar que harГғВЎ lo mismo a la hora de degradar la Agenda Digital al servicio de las grandes corporaciones tecnolГғВіgicas, o el Pacto sobre MigraciГғВіn y Asilo para devolver a los Estados la competencia que hemos conseguido, por fin, que seaГӮВ de la UniГғВіn Europea. Y frente a eso decimos con toda claridad que encontrarГғВЎ un no rotundo en este Parlamento Europeo a cualquier retroceso.</del:text>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:52:42</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T12:55:13</del:timestamp>
