  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_527">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_527</del:identifier>
    <del:text>On 7 October 2023, Hamas, supported by other armed groups from the Gaza Strip, carried out a coordinated terrorist attack on Israel. Over 3ГӮВ 000 rockets were fired from Gaza and up to 3ГӮВ 000 terrorists infiltrated Israeli territory. Around 1ГӮВ 200 people were killed and approximately 250 others were kidnapped. In response, Israel officially declared that it was a state of war, launched air strikes on the Gaza Strip, and after about two weeks began ground operations.
The recent ceasefire between Israel and Hamas began on 19 January, following extensive diplomatic efforts by Egypt, Qatar, and the United States. It marked a significant deГўВҖВ‘escalation after 15 months of conflict, with both parties committing to halt hostilities and engage in negotiations.
High humanitarian costs in Gaza are unacceptable. We recognise the right of states to defend themselves, but at the same time Europe has a great role to play in promoting stability. We stand for peace, security and for the right of all people to live without fear.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:41:36</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_365"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_526"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_527"/>
  </rdf:Description>
