  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_94">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_94</del:identifier>
    <del:text>ГҺВ ГҸВҺГҸВӮ ГҺВұГҺВ»ГҺВ»ГҺВ№ГҸВҺГҸВӮ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВөГҺВҫГҺВ·ГҺВіГҺВ®ГҸВғГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВәГҺВ¬ГҸВҖГҺВҝГҺВ№ГҺВҝГҸВӮ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝ ГҺВіГҺВөГҺВіГҺВҝГҺВҪГҸВҢГҸВӮ ГҸВҢГҸВ„ГҺВ№ ГҺВ· ГҸВҖГҺВөГҸВҒГҺВҜГҸВҶГҺВ·ГҺВјГҺВ· ГҺВұГҸВ…ГҸВ„ГҺВ® ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВ»ГҺВҝГҸВҚГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВөГҸВ…ГҸВғГҺВ· ГҺВҫГҺВөГҺВәГҺВ№ГҺВҪГҺВ¬ГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҸВҢ ГҸВ„ГҺВ· ГҺВІГҺВ№ГҸВүГҸВғГҺВ№ГҺВјГҸВҢГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВ„ГҺВұ; ГҺВҘГҸВҖГҺВ¬ГҸВҒГҸВҮГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВҪ ГҸВ„ГҸВҢГҸВғГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҺВҙГҺВөГҺВәГҺВ¬ГҺВҙГҺВөГҸВӮ, ГҺВөГҺВәГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВ¬ГҺВҙГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҺВҙГҺВ№ГҺВұГҺВҙГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВұГҸВғГҺВҜГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҺВёГҺВұ ГҺВјГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВҒГҺВҝГҸВҚГҸВғГҺВұГҺВҪ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВ»ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВөГҸВ…ГҺВёГҺВҝГҸВҚГҺВҪ. ГҺВ“ГҺВ№ГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВҜ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВҫГҺВөГҺВәГҺВ№ГҺВҪГҺВ®ГҸВғГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВјГҺВө ГҺВұГҸВҖГҸВҢ ГҸВ„ГҺВ· ГҺВІГҺВ№ГҸВүГҸВғГҺВ№ГҺВјГҸВҢГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВ„ГҺВұ, ГҺВәГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҺВҜГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВәГҸВҚГҸВҒГҺВ№ГҺВҝГҺВ№ ГҸВғГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҺВ¬ГҺВҙГҺВөГҺВ»ГҸВҶГҺВҝГҺВ№; ГҺВҳГҺВөГҸВүГҸВҒГҸВҺ ГҸВҢГҸВ„ГҺВ№ ГҸВҖГҸВҒГҺВӯГҸВҖГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҸВ„ГҺВҝ ГҺВұГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВҒГҸВҒГҺВҜГҸВҲГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВјГҺВө ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВјГҺВөГҺВҜГҺВҪГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВјГҺВө ГҺВөГҺВәГҺВөГҺВҜ ГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҸВғГҸВ…ГҺВјГҸВҶГҸВүГҺВҪГҺВ®ГҸВғГҺВұГҺВјГҺВө. ГҺВЈГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҺВөГҸВ…ГҸВҮГҺВұГҸВҒГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҸВҺ.</del:text>
    <del:text>Die EuropГғВӨische Union ist ein Friedensprojekt, aber solange die UN ein zahnloser Tiger ist, muss man Frieden leider verteidigen. Und dafГғВјr brauchen wir langfristig eine europГғВӨische Armee, denn wohl kaum werden die Spanier die Portugiesen angreifen, die Polen die Tschechen oderГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ Gott behГғВјteГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ die Luxemburger uns Deutsche.
Mittelfristig muss die Beistandspflicht aus ArtikelГӮВ 42 NummerГӮВ 7ГӮВ des Vertrags ГғВјber die EuropГғВӨische Union dem ArtikelГӮВ 5 des NATO-Vertrags mindestens gleichkommen, aber kurzfristig wird der Kampf um unsere Freiheit in der Ukraine gefГғВјhrt. Und dementsprechend muss es unsere grГғВ¶ГғВҹte PrioritГғВӨt bei unserer eigenen Verteidigung sein, die weitere und nun mit dem Wegfall der USA noch stГғВӨrkere AufrГғВјstung der Ukraine voranzutreiben. Denn der Feind stehtГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ leider genauso wie bei unseren ГғВңbungen damals auf dem TruppenГғВјbungsplatzГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ im Osten.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:23:37</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:46:17</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_65"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_81"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_93"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_94"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_237">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_237</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Written Statements (Rule 178)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:45:57</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_236"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_237"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_262">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_262</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Em segundo lugar, a minha casa ГғВ© um lugar regido pela lei, e essa lei chama-se Acordos de Schengen. NГғВЈo tem visto, nГғВЈo entra. E quem entra sem visto, quem entra sem a minha vontade, tem de voltar para casa.
E este, Senhor ComissГғВЎrio, ГғВ© um primeiro passo. Tem falhas, com certeza, mas ГғВ© um primeiro passo positivo para o retorno daqueles que nГғВЈo devem estar em nossa casa, porque a soberania nacional e a seguranГғВ§a sГғВЈo afetados por esta migraГғВ§ГғВЈo ilegal.
O meu paГғВӯs era um paГғВӯs seguro atГғВ© hГғВЎ dois anos e meio, agora nГғВЈo ГғВ© um paГғВӯs seguro.
E o que ГғВ© que se passa em termos de direitos humanos? Os portugueses ГўВҖВ” os europeus ГўВҖВ” tambГғВ©m tГғВӘm direitos humanos. SГғВЈo eles o principal objeto dos direitos humanos. Porque ГғВ© que nГғВіs caГғВ§amos os direitos humanos dos cidadГғВЈos da Europa, dos cidadГғВЈos dos nossos paГғВӯses, dos cidadГғВЈos de Portugal, para elevarmos os direitos humanos de outros que entram em nossa casa ГғВ  forГғВ§a e sem convite?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:31:47</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_194"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_261"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_262"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem13">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Topic"/>
    <del:identifier>creitem13</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Requests for the waiver of immunity</del:name>
    <del:name>European Social Fund Plus post-2027 (A10-0014/2025 - Marit Maij) (vote)</del:name>
    <skos:related rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem18"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_346">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_346</del:identifier>
    <del:name>AndrГғВЎs GyГғВјrk</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PfE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_524">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_524</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The EU has been clear on the utmost importance of maintaining the ceasefire. For the moment, the ceasefire holds, but it remains very fragile. We now need to move towards negotiations on phase two of the ceasefire and a hostage release agreement.
The first aspect is to improve the humanitarian situation, which is again deteriorating. The UN tells us that food prices in Gaza have spiked and aid food parcels could soon run out. There is an urgent need to resume a consistent flow of supplies, and the EU continues to play its part.
The EU has also made an active contribution to the ceasefire through its CSDP mission, EUBAM Rafah, which is operational at the Rafah crossing point. More than 3ГӮВ 000 people have crossed the border since it reopened on 1ГӮВ February. In addition, the EU is carrying out medical evacuations.
The second aspect is our continued support for the Palestinian Authority in its reforms and its gradual return to Gaza. We believe that the Palestinian Authority is best placed to govern Gaza. It needs to be strengthened and supported financially. There is no place for Hamas in Gaza.
On concrete support to the Palestinians, the EU is ready to work with the entire international community, our partners and the United Nations. The EU position is clear: we support UN Security Council Resolution 2735. This means rejecting any attempts at demographic and territorial changes in the Gaza Strip and stressing the importance of unifying the Gaza Strip with the West Bank under the Palestinian Authority. We therefore welcomed the initiative by the Arab countries to draw up a plan which covers interim measures, reconstruction and governance, and does not foresee any displacement of Gaza's population.
The third aspect is the two-state solution. It is the only way to ensure sustainable peace and security for Israel, the Palestinians and the entire region. The EU will continue to work to review the political process, in particular as part of the Global Alliance for the Implementation of the Two-State Solution. We are also opening a new chapter of strengthened engagement through the recent EU-Israel Association Council, and the first ever EU-Palestine high-level dialogue with Prime Minister Mustafa, which will take place in April on the margins of the Foreign Affairs Council.
To conclude, the EU is committed to play its role in contributing to a more stable situation in Gaza and supporting the Palestinian Authority. The ceasefire must be maintained and the negotiations for its second phase must start as soon as possible.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:31:40</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_2"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_523"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_524"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_108">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_108</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Virginie Joron</del:name>
    <del:name>Christine Anderson</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PfE"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ESN"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_381">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_381</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Aquilo que nГғВіs dizemos ГғВ© ГӮВ«nГғВЈoГӮВ», nГғВіs queremos ter capacidade mГғВӯnima de dissuasГғВЈo para defender o povo europeu dos 27 EstadosГўВҖВ‘Membros.
NГғВіs nГғВЈo queremos fazer um armamento atГғВ© aos dentes, como se diz em bom portuguГғВӘs, nГғВіs queremos ter uma capacidade de dissuasГғВЈo mГғВӯnima para nГғВЈo sermos invadidos, como foi a UcrГғВўnia, injustamente, por Putin.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:22:46</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_82"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_380"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_381"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_501">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_501</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Una vez mГғВЎs, la historia se repite y grupos yihadistas se hacen con el control de paГғВӯses ante la complacencia de las grandes potencias. PasГғВі con AfganistГғВЎn, pasГғВі con Libia y ahora se ha fomentado deliberadamente que pase en Siria.
No podemos aceptar que el nuevo Gobierno sirio reprima a las distintas comunidades nacionales o religiosas del paГғВӯs y menos que acabe con su vida, como acabamos de ver en el caso de los alauitas. Es fundamental apostar por un nuevo futuro para Siria que garantice la pluralidad del paГғВӯs, que cuente particularmente con los kurdos para organizar su futuro y que respete la administraciГғВіn autГғВіnoma de Rojava como fundamental para ese objetivo.
Quiero aprovechar para saludar la disoluciГғВіn del PKK que, sin duda, traerГғВЎ estabilidad a la zona, al menos por la parte kurda. Es una buena noticia que debe ser correspondida por TurquГғВӯa con la liberaciГғВіn inmediata de ГғВ–calan y la aceptaciГғВіn del hecho nacional diferencial kurdo.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:02:20</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_353"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_500"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_501"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem20">
