    <del:identifier>creitem20</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Agenda of the next sitting</del:name>
    <del:name>White paper on the future of European defence (debate)</del:name>
    <skos:narrower rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem26"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_168">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_168</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Elena Nevado del Campo</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_141">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_141</del:identifier>
    <del:name>ГҺВ”ГҺВ·ГҺВјГҺВ®ГҸВ„ГҸВҒГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВӨГҸВғГҺВ№ГҸВҢГҺВҙГҸВҒГҺВұГҸВӮ</del:name>
    <del:name>Loucas Fourlas</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_14">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_14</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:text>However, this also means that the Council should act on this asset of Putin within the Council. Doing conclusions with only 26 is a first step, triggering Article 7 is really, really time to act on it.
Secondly, Madam President, I want to thank you for your ReArm proposal. And the Greens are fully on board and supporting you for a truly European defence and security Union. However, in your plan, we do have some questions and concerns.
First of all, triggering an escape clause. To be very honest, if you are triggering an escape clause in your fiscal rules continuously, maybe at a certain moment you need to wonder whether maybe the fiscal rules are not fit for purpose and you need a proper review instead of every time triggering an escape rule.
Secondly, and here I have to agree with Mr Weber, the European approach is not strong enough in your approach. Of the 800 billion, only 150 billion are European, the rest is national. Without any clear indication it will be a European approach. And even with the 150, only by doing it through a joint procurement, I'm not sure this will really have a proper European approach. We don't need more tanks on the Greek-Turkish border.
That brings me to the third point. Defence and security is much broader than arms and ammunition. This is about infrastructure. European infrastructure needs to be improved also to transport all the materials throughout Europe. This is about real infrastructure as well. This is about cyber security but this is also about energy independence. And Mr Procaccini, you said it already, looking at how much money we as Europe are spending on fossil dependency, EUR 400 billion each year, and we moved it from Russia to the United States. It's not helping anything. So the green transition is in the same agenda as the security agenda and should not be treated separately.
And that is why we are concerned that investments in green and social transition are being at the cost of investments in security, and therefore we need to increase both and we need to increase spending on both.
That brings me to the last point. The situation in Ukraine is very dire and very sincere, and we cannot not act and we cannot lack on action and have complacency. The next Council needs to act faster. We need to stand by Ukraine. We need peace in Europe. We need peace in Ukraine. We need peace on our own terms.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:15:15</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T09:52:22</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_11"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_13"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_14"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_49">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_49</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Because of that reckless attitude, we, the Europeans are in huge danger. EU is losing the international race. China and US are growing faster, more stable and more innovative. Many nations are mocking the EU with such excessive bureaucracy. Our continent has become a sick man of the world.
We urgently need to deregulate our economy, we have to break the chains that hinder our growth. The Commission is proposing the Omnibus package. It is a step in the right direction, but it's a very small step. It's not enough. The Omnibus initiative is shallow. You are trying to avoid making ГўВҖВ“ Madam is absent, of course ГўВҖВ“ you are trying to avoid making hard decisions.
We need new deregulations with which we shout: cut, cut, cut and, once again, cut. We have to throw a lot of directives into trash where they belong. There is a lot of work ahead of us to get rid of the unnecessary burdens from our economy. The Omnibus proposal needs to be amended and extended.</del:text>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T18:09:06</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:46:57</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_27"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_41"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_48"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_49"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_166">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_166</del:identifier>
    <del:text>ГғВҺn ultimii ani, prin activitatea mea din Parlamentul European, am salvat miliarde de euro din fondurile neutilizate, modificГғВўnd regulamentele europene pentru a faza proiectele europene. Am contribuit la simplificarea regulilor privind accesarea programelor europene ГҲВҷi am amendat bugetul Uniunii Europene pentru ca aceste resurse sГ„Вғ ajungГ„Вғ ГғВ®n regiunea noastrГ„Вғ.
Dar aceste fonduri nu sunt doar cifre pe hГғВўrtie. Trebuie sГ„Вғ privim ГғВ®nainte: avem nevoie de o absorbГҲВӣie mai bunГ„Вғ, mai eficientГ„Вғ, mai multГ„Вғ flexibilitate ГҲВҷi o strategie pentru viitor.
100 de miliarde de euro sunt un succes, dar ГҲВҷi o responsabilitate. Extremismul cautГ„Вғ sГ„Вғ distrugГ„Вғ aceasta oportunitate pentru RomГғВўnia.
Voi continua sГ„Вғ lupt pentru ca fiecare euro sГ„Вғ fie folosit acolo unde este cel mai necesar pentru romГғВўni ГҲВҷi europeni.</del:text>
    <del:text>Te vГғВӨititte juuri ГғВӨsken, ettГғВӨ tГғВӨГғВӨllГғВӨ puhutaan puppua ja alistetaan miehiГғВӨ. MillГғВӨ tavalla naisten oikeuksien esiin tuominen alistaa miehiГғВӨ? Ei millГғВӨГғВӨn tavalla. Vastatkaa, mihin perustatte vГғВӨitteenne?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:20:48</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:06:04</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_71"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_119"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_165"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_166"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_503">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_503</del:identifier>
    <del:text>LГўВҖВҷUnion ne doit pas avoir de difficultГғВ© ГғВ  nommer le mal quГўВҖВҷest le totalitarisme islamique. CГўВҖВҷest lui qui a frappГғВ© la cГғВҙte syrienne, cГўВҖВҷest lui qui a dГғВ©versГғВ© le sang de nos peuples sur le sol europГғВ©en, cГўВҖВҷest lui lГўВҖВҷennemi. Nous devons conditionner la levГғВ©e des sanctions et le versement des millions dГўВҖВҷeuros dГўВҖВҷaide ГғВ  la preuve de la non-implication du gouvernement transitoire et ГғВ  son engagement total ГғВ  rГғВ©tablir lГўВҖВҷordre, alors quГўВҖВҷil est aujourdГўВҖВҷhui incapable de retenir des chiens de guerre face ГғВ  des civils.
Exigeons des garanties de sГғВ©curitГғВ© pour les minoritГғВ©s de Syrie! Ne reproduisons pas les mГғВӘmes erreurs quГўВҖВҷen Iraq et quГўВҖВҷen Libye!</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:05:08</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_355"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_502"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_503"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_221">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_221</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Mariusz KamiГ…В„ski</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_243">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_243</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Wie hier illegaal aanwezig is, moet per direct vertrekken. Dat is niet radicaal, dat is gewoon gezond verstand. Het migratiepact wordt gebracht als een soort wondermiddel om de asielellende op te lossen. Maar we kunnen hier nog tien migratiepacten aannemen ГўВҖВ” als de terugkeercijfers niet fors omhooggaan, blijft het dweilen met de kraan open. Daarom hebben we een robuust terugkeerbeleid nodig. Eerlijk tegenover migranten, maar vooral eerlijk tegenover onze eigen burgers. Ik wil automatische sancties voor landen die hun onderdanen niet terugnemen. Geen terugname betekent geen ontwikkelingshulp, geen visumregelingen en geen andere privileges. Want Europa is te lang de gekke Henkie van de wereld geweest. We moeten ook onze interne procedures versimpelen. Wie is afgewezen, moet vertrekken en mag niet eindeloos doorprocederen. We moeten ervoor zorgen dat afgewezen asielzoekers ook naar andere landen en zogenaamde "return hubs" buiten de EU gestuurd kunnen worden.
Als schaduwrapporteur voor de PfEГўВҖВ‘Fractie ben ik vastberaden om constructief samen te werken met de andere fracties. Zonder de PfEГўВҖВ‘Fractie is er geen meerderheid voor een streng terugkeerbeleid en wordt het linkse wanbeleid voortgezet en gaat het van kwaad tot erger. Laten we werken aan wetgeving die effectief is en de veiligheid van onze burgers op ГғВ©ГғВ©n zet.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:02:21</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_178"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_242"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_243"/>
