  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_435">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_435</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ich finde es deswegen gut, dass der Vorschlag der EuropГғВӨischen Kommission zum Clean Industrial Deal das groГғВҹe Ganze im Blick behГғВӨlt und ГғВјber die Sektoren hinweg tatsГғВӨchlich auch an Schwachstellen des Green Deals ansetzt. Wir haben zum Beispiel bisher ein absolutes Nachfrageproblem. Deswegen ist es richtig, LeitmГғВӨrkte zu schaffen, deswegen ist es wichtig, zum Beispiel die Kreislaufwirtschaft anzukurbeln.
Aber man muss auch sagen, am Ende des Tages sind dort viele leere Versprechungen in Ihrem Vorschlag, insbesondere bei der fundamentalen Frage, wo eigentlich das Geld herkommen soll. Ohne die Investitionssicherheit werden wir es nicht schaffen, den Wandel hinzubekommen, deswegen vielen Dank fГғВјr den Vorschlag, aber es liegt noch viel gemeinsame Arbeit vor uns.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:29:38</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_153"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_434"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_435"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_228">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_228</del:identifier>
    <del:text>De geopolitieke instabiliteit, gecombineerd met onze afhankelijkheid van China en India op het vlak van geneesmiddelen, maakt ons kwetsbaar. Zeker in tijden van hybride oorlogsvoering. Want ГғВ©ГғВ©n geopolitiek evenement, ГғВ©ГғВ©n zotte beslissing van een bepaalde beleidsmaker of ГғВ©ГғВ©n probleem in een fabriek hier ver vandaan kan ons in een ongeziene gezondheidscrisis storten. Dat is een groot probleem. Geneesmiddelentekorten kunnen mensenlevens kosten. Reden te meer om dit in Europa samen aan te pakken met de volle impact van onze interne markt.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:31:56</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_170"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_227"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_228"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_164">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_164</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Oliver Schenk</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_17">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_17</del:identifier>
    <del:text>In accordance with Rule 9(9), the following report is added to the final draft agenda for a vote on Tuesday: report by Dainius Г…ВҪalimasГӮВ on the request for waiver of the immunity of Adam Bielan.
With the agreement of the political groups, I also wish to put to the House the following proposal for changes to the final draft agenda for Tuesday. The order of debates in the afternoon will change as follows.
The debate on the presentation of the proposal for a Critical Medicines Act will be taken as the second point, and the debate on the presentation of the proposal on a new common approach on returns will be taken as the third point.
If there are no objections to this, then the change will be approved.
We now move to changes requested by the political groups, starting with Wednesday.
The ECR Group has requested that Council and Commission statements on 'Recent events in Romania: the ongoing investigation into the presidential candidate' be added as the fifth point in the afternoon, before the debate on frozen Russian assets. As a consequence, the sitting would be extended to 11ГӮВ p.m.
I give the floor to Gheorghe Piperea to move the request on behalf of the ECR.</del:text>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T17:16:22</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:00:56</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_14"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_16"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_17"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_181">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_181</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:text>The Finnish police recently published statistics on sex crime rates by nationality. The results are revealing. Compared to Finnish nationals, the rates of sexual offences committed are six times higher for Somalis; ten times higher for Iraqis; 12 times higher for Afghans and Congolese; and as much as 15 times higher for Syrians. Absolutely shocking numbers.
Colleagues, let us stand up for our daughters, sisters and wives. Let us make our streets safe again ГўВҖВ“ let's protect our borders from the type of immigration that is harmful.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:41:03</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:27:32</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_132"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_180"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_181"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_490">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_490</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Reindustrializar Europa con un modelo sostenible y competitivo solo serГғВЎ posible si garantizamos energГғВӯa asequible para nuestras industrias y ciudadanos. Necesitamos mГғВЎs renovables e interconexiones para una UniГғВіn de la EnergГғВӯa real y mercados e instrumentos que reflejen esta asequibilidad para la industria.

AdemГғВЎs, la financiaciГғВіn es una condiciГғВіn imprescindible. Es una buena noticia que este plan venga acompaГғВұado de recursos, pero debemos asegurarnos de que el prГғВіximo Marco Financiero Plurianual continГғВәe en esa direcciГғВіn. Necesitamos apostar por campeones europeos capaces de competir a nivel global. Este pacto es tambiГғВ©n una oportunidad para fomentar el sector de las tecnologГғВӯas limpias para modernizar nuestra base industrial y mejorar nuestras condiciones de vida.</del:text>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_348"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_265">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_265</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ces derniГғВЁres semaines, les responsables europГғВ©ens brandissent ГғВ  lГўВҖВҷenvi les valeurs europГғВ©ennes face ГғВ  un Trump qui, lui, les piГғВ©tinerait. Mais de quelles valeurs europГғВ©ennes parlons-nous? De la violation des droits fondamentaux des plus vulnГғВ©rables? De la dГғВ©tention des chercheurs de refuge, y compris de jeunes enfants? De lГўВҖВҷexpulsion forcГғВ©e des personnes fuyant la guerre ou la misГғВЁre dans des centres de retour? De la sous-traitance de nos obligations humaines et juridiques ГғВ  des pays tiers, que lГўВҖВҷon qualifiera de ГӮВ«sГғВ»rsГӮВ» au grГғВ© de nos propres intГғВ©rГғВӘts?
Qui finalement les piГғВ©tine, ces valeurs europГғВ©ennes, Monsieur le Commissaire? De Dublin ГғВ  cette proposition de retour, en passant par le pacte sur la migration et lГўВҖВҷasile, la politique europГғВ©enne en matiГғВЁre dГўВҖВҷasile nГўВҖВҷa vraiment rien ГғВ  envier aux dГғВ©lires dГўВҖВҷexpulsion massive de DonaldГӮВ Trump.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:36:03</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_197"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_264"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_265"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem26">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Topic"/>
    <del:identifier>creitem26</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Agenda of the next sitting</del:name>
    <skos:broader rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem20"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_370">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_370</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Mounir Satouri,</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_526">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_526</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The first priority for Gaza currently is to resume full access to humanitarian aid. Let us recall that there are 3.1ГӮВ million people who are affected by 15 months of conflict ahead of the January ceasefire. The local population should not again suffer from the hostilities from all sides.
The European Union and its Member States are among the biggest financial supporters of the Palestinians, and currently the largest donors to the Palestinian Authority and to UNRWA. It has already mobilised an additional amount of EURГӮВ 120ГӮВ million for humanitarian assistance. Since the onset of the Gaza crisis, this brings our total contribution to EURГӮВ 450ГӮВ million.
TheГӮВ package of essential services includes food, clean water, healthcare and shelter. So far, 4ГӮВ 500 tonnes of humanitarian cargo have been transferred via humanitarian air bridge flights to Gaza. The European Union has also expanded its civil protection mechanism for medical evacuations in Gaza. A blockage of the delivery of humanitarian assistance and interruption of services such as electricity would have devastating consequences for the population on the ground.
Second, the extension of the ceasefire or a move to the second stage of the ceasefire and release of all hostages are the only ways to permanently end the hostilities, and it would allow us to start the early recovery and reconstruction of Gaza.
While European Union efforts are currently focusing on scaling up humanitarian support, we are also preparing for a long recovery and reconstruction phase. On 18ГӮВ February, the European Union released its Gaza Rapid Disaster Needs Assessment, together with the United Nations and the World Bank. This assessment looks at the damages, losses and needs. It estimates that EURГӮВ 49ГӮВ billion are required over the next decade. The Egyptian-led reconstruction plan came to similar conclusions.
Housing requires the largest share of recovery needs ГўВҖВ“ about 30ГӮВ % ГўВҖВ“ followed by the health sector, commerce and industry, and agriculture and food. Given the magnitude of needs, the European Union cannot act alone. The international community must take collective and coordinated efforts to support Gaza's recovery and reconstruction. This is why we are working closely with our Arab partners. We welcome the Arab Recovery and Reconstruction Plan that was endorsed at the emergency summit of the League of Arab States in Cairo on 4ГӮВ March. We are studying the technical details of the plan in order to identify and create possible synergies, and we look forward to the upcoming international conference on Gaza that Egypt will host soon.
Large-scale recovery and reconstruction can only start when there is stability on the ground. This includes arrangements on the governance and security of Gaza. We firmly reject any attempt of relocation of the population or of territorial change in Gaza and the West Bank. Discussions on the recovery and reconstruction of Gaza must involve the Palestinians. The Palestinian Authority is their legitimate body.
When it comes to Gaza governance, we see the Palestinian Authority as the only viable partner. This is why we are committed to supporting a reformed Palestinian Authority and avoid its fiscal collapse. Last year, the Commission disbursed almost EURГӮВ 400ГӮВ million in emergency funding to address the most urgent needs.
We are now preparing a multi-year, comprehensive programme for the Palestinian recovery and resilience. It is based on the reform agenda of the Palestinian Authority, and we are encouraging Israel to support it by releasing withheld tax revenues.ГӮВ We hope that other regional stakeholders, including in the Gulf, will also support this approach.
Finally, I want to highlight the essential role that UNRWA has played. It has delivered more than half of the entire emergency response in Gaza over the last 15 months. As a provider of many essential services to Palestinians, also beyond Gaza, UNRWA has an important role. They are a humanitarian and development actor. As European Commission, we will continue our support to the Palestinian refugees and to the UN agency.
Let me finish by saying that I am looking forward to high-level political dialogue with the Palestinian Authority in April. It will take place on 13 or 14ГӮВ April and will be a good occasion to take stock of the reform achievements.
We must not forget the central role of the Palestinian Authority and the role which it will have in the day after in Gaza. Thank you and I am looking forward to your debate.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:35:48</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_349"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_525"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_526"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_90">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_90</del:identifier>
    <del:text>But I also see ГўВҖВ“ and this is important for the Greens as well to see ГўВҖВ“ that we have a problem with the competitiveness. That is why it's so important to open up these files. That's so good that the Commission comes up with the first Omnibus package to change this.
This is not enough, though. We have to continue. We have to cut red tape even more than in these proposals. And for all the political groups that would like to do that, I am sure that EPP will work together with you to cut the red tape, to increase the growth, to come back to competitiveness. That is what we can do. And then we get the resources also to focus on the green issues.</del:text>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:18:54</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:41:28</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_61"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_77"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_89"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_90"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_463">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_463</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Den hГғВӨr fГғВ¶rГғВӨndringen gГғВ¶r vi inte fГғВ¶r att vara snГғВӨlla mot nГғВҘgon annan, utan fГғВ¶r vГғВҘr egen skull: fГғВ¶r jobben, industrisamhГғВӨllena och de hГғВ¶gst verkliga mГғВӨnniskorna. Ska vi vara en producerande kontinent i framtiden, med bra villkor fГғВ¶r arbetare, kan man inte klamra sig fast vid teknik som blir fГғВ¶rГғВҘldrad. Trots detta hГғВ¶r vi extremhГғВ¶gern lova att pausa tiden eller helst spola tillbaka den.
Det ГғВӨr absurt och ett svek mot de som arbetar pГғВҘ bruken, pГғВҘ industrierna, de vars arbeten kommer att fГғВ¶rsvinna om EU-lГғВӨnderna fГғВ¶rsГғВ¶ker frysa tiden. ExtremhГғВ¶gern sviker dem nГғВӨr de ljuger och sГғВӨger att allt kan bli som det alltid har varit. Men det har aldrig varit som det alltid har varit. Fattar de inte det?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:05:24</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_331"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_462"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_463"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_279">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_279</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Niemcy Г…ВӣciГ„В…gnГ„ВҷГ…ВӮy na siebie problem, a teraz usiГ…ВӮujГ„В… siГ„Вҷ nim podzieliГ„ВҮ z innymi narodami, co obniГ…Вјa poziom wspГғВіГ…ВӮpracy i zaufania, a takГ…Вјe rozbija strefГ„Вҷ Schengen. Czas na zdecydowane dziaГ…ВӮania na rzecz powstrzymania imigracji. Czas na deportowanie kryminalistГғВіw z naszego kontynentu. Czas na peГ…ВӮne wdroГ…Вјenie zaГ…ВӮoГ…ВјeГ…В„ deklaracji budapesztaГ…В„skiej PatriotГғВіw. Tylko w ten sposГғВіb moГ…Вјemy uratowaГ„ВҮ EuropГ„Вҷ.
(MГғВіwczyni nie zgodziГ…ВӮa siГ„Вҷ na pytanie zasygnalizowane przez podniesienie niebieskiej kartki przez Lukas Sieper)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:55:01</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_27"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_278"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_279"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_328">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_328</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Attention, toutefois, ne remplacez pas une dГғВ©pendance par une autre. Ce nГўВҖВҷest pas la Commission europГғВ©enne qui vous dГғВ©fendra. La dГғВ©fense dГўВҖВҷune nation, cГўВҖВҷest sa survie, et la survie ne se nГғВ©gocie pas entre bureaucrates, ГғВ  la majoritГғВ© qualifiГғВ©e. Ne donnez pas ГғВ  MmeГӮВ vonГӮВ derГӮВ Leyen le pouvoir dГўВҖВҷenvoyer vos fils sur le champ de bataille. Il faut nous rГғВ©armer, et on ne rГғВ©arme pas une nation avec des comptes publics en faillite. Une ГғВ©conomie de guerre, ce nГўВҖВҷest pas une machine ГғВ  jeter notre argent par les fenГғВӘtres au profit de pays du monde entier. Si nous voulons gagner la prochaine guerre, il nous faut dГўВҖВҷabord gagner tout de suite la guerre contre le gaspillage, les gabegies et le dГғВ©sordre budgГғВ©taire.
Notre rГғВ©armement doit bГғВ©nГғВ©ficier exclusivement ГғВ  notre industrie militaire. Si vous achetez amГғВ©ricain, vous restez sous tutelle amГғВ©ricaine ГўВҖВ“ГӮВ cГўВҖВҷest aussi simple que cela. La France, seule puissance nuclГғВ©aire du continent, dotГғВ©e dГўВҖВҷune armГғВ©e exceptionnelle, a un rГғВҙle historique ГғВ  jouer. Pour les nations qui voudraient se placer sous notre protection, il faudra contribuer et donner ГғВ  la France les moyens nГғВ©cessaires, car la puissance exige des moyens. En revanche, notre dissuasion nuclГғВ©aire ne sera jamais ГғВ  partager avec quiconque, car la puissance ne se partage pas, la puissance ne se dГғВ©lГғВЁgue pas, et la sГғВ©curitГғВ© ne se sous-traite pas. CГўВҖВҷest ГғВ  nous dГўВҖВҷassumer lГўВҖВҷeffort, ou ГғВ  nous de nous prГғВ©parer ГғВ  en payer le prix.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:13:13</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_237"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_327"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_328"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_327">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_327</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Wenn Sie uns heute erzГғВӨhlen, dass Abschreckung mit AufrГғВјstung erreicht wird, dann sage ich Ihnen, auch im Kalten Krieg war es die Diplomatie, die uns davor beschГғВјtzt hat, einen schlimmeren Krieg zu erleben als die AufrГғВјstung selber. Deshalb, wirklich, wenn Sie keinen Krieg wollen, Herr Sieper, dann plГғВӨdieren Sie bitte fГғВјr einen anderen Kurs in der EU als fГғВјr die AufrГғВјstung!</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:12:19</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_80"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_326"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_327"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_281">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_281</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Onde nГғВЈo existe a capacidade de retorno efetivo, vigorarГғВЎ o condicionamento da entrada de migrantes. A melhor forma de favorecer uma polГғВӯtica migratГғВіria positiva ГғВ©, pois, com uma verdadeira estratГғВ©gia de retornos.
Precisamos de uma resposta que seja europeia, rГғВЎpida, uniforme e clara em matГғВ©ria de retornos, que assegure o legado de Schengen, pelo que defendemos a implementaГғВ§ГғВЈo de um regulamento, enquanto ato legislativo, para os retornos.
O regulamento a criar deve assentar em duas medidas essenciais: em primeiro lugar, o acompanhamento efetivo do migrante, desde a sua entrada atГғВ© ГғВ  verificaГғВ§ГғВЈo das condiГғВ§ГғВөes para a sua permanГғВӘncia. Por outro lado, devemos assegurar que esse processo de anГғВЎlise seja breve, se cumpra dentro da jurisdiГғВ§ГғВЈo da UniГғВЈo Europeia e obedeГғВ§a a regras que assegurem tratamento condigno dos migrantes, sempre no escrupuloso respeito dos seus direitos fundamentais.
Sejamos claros: precisamos de medidas que permitam os retornos, mas ГғВ© nosso dever fundamental garantir que estas medidas sГғВЈo humanas e proporcionais.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:58:00</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_206"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_280"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_281"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_319">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_319</del:identifier>
    <del:text>After numerous wake-up calls we have discussed here, Europe's moment of truth has finally arrived. We're not starting from scratch. In MarchГӮВ 2022, the 27ГӮВ heads of state or government adopted the Strategic Compass. A year later, the Commission published the European Defence Industrial Strategy, and we also adopted ASAP and EDIRPA and agreed on the capability development priorities.
All these initiatives are slowly but surely pushing Member States to step outside their national corridors in pursuit of a genuine European Defence Union. But now we really have to make a great leap.
Therefore, dear Commissioner Kubilius, the white paper must build on these achievements, and propose regulatory and programmatic initiatives at European level, rather than confining itself to a description of threats and shared needs.
You, dear Commissioner, and the HR/VP have a chance to significantly steer this debate. I look forward to discussing the white paper thoroughly at committee level.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:59:17</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_233"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_318"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_319"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_411">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_411</del:identifier>
    <del:text>ГғВҺn acest sens, RomГғВўnia are un potenГҲВӣial semnificativ de a deveni un actor important ГғВ®n industria de apГ„Вғrare europeanГ„Вғ, ГғВ®nsГ„Вғ pentru aceasta trebuie sГ„Вғ acГҲВӣionГ„Вғm rapid ГҲВҷi strategic. Este necesar sГ„Вғ simplificГ„Вғm procedurile administrative, sГ„Вғ implicГ„Вғm mediul de afaceri, sГ„Вғ creГ„Вғm parteneriate strategice cu statele membre ГҲВҷi sГ„Вғ dezvoltГ„Вғm proiecte concrete, care sГ„Вғ contribuie direct la ГғВ®ntГ„Вғrirea capacitГ„ВғГҲВӣilor de apГ„Вғrare. ГғВҺn acelaГҲВҷi timp, trebuie sГ„Вғ elaborГ„Вғm ГҲВҷi sГ„Вғ implementГ„Вғm un plan naГҲВӣional de dezvoltare a industriei de apГ„Вғrare, care sГ„Вғ alinieze RomГғВўnia la standardele ГҲВҷi obiectivele europene.

Avem nevoie de o viziune europeanГ„Вғ de apГ„Вғrare care sГ„Вғ rГ„ВғspundГ„Вғ eficient provocГ„Вғrilor externe, dar ГҲВҷi sГ„Вғ ofere o perspectivГ„Вғ strategicГ„Вғ pe termen lung. Doar printr-o abordare colectivГ„Вғ ГҲВҷi unitarГ„Вғ putem construi o EuropГ„Вғ capabilГ„Вғ sГ„Вғ facГ„Вғ faГҲВӣГ„Вғ ameninГҲВӣГ„Вғrilor actuale ГҲВҷi viitoare.</del:text>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_295"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_121">
