  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_356">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_356</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Mums ir jГ„ВҒizmanto tГ„ВҒs priekГ…ВЎrocГ„В«bas, ko sniedz Ukrainas aizsardzГ„В«bas industrija ГўВҖВ” Ukrainas attГ„В«stГ„В«tГ„ВҒs militГ„ВҒrГ„ВҒs tehnoloГ„ВЈijas jau ir pierГ„ВҒdГ„В«juГ…ВЎas sevi kaujas laukГ„ВҒ. IepГ„В“rkot bruГ…ВҶojumu no Ukrainas, mГ„В“s palГ„В«dzam ne tikai tГ„ВҒs ekonomikai, bet arГ„В« investГ„В“jam savГ„ВҒ droГ…ВЎГ„В«bГ„ВҒ.
Aizdevuma plГ„ВҒns ir iezГ„В«mГ„В“ts Г„ВҚetriem gadiem. Sagaidu, ka paredzГ„В“tie un papildu finanГ…ВЎu avoti bГ…В«s dalГ„В«bvalstГ„В«m pieejami tГ…В«lГ„В«tГ„В“ji, nevis kaut kad gada beigГ„ВҒs.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:51:04</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_257"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_355"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_356"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_365">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_365</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Today, almost everyone supports it, and we recently reached European conclusions with reference to the defence of all EU borders, from the northeast down to the south and eastern Mediterranean.
But these EU borders are violated by the neo-Ottoman Turkey that occupies part of Cyprus. Currently, neo-Ottoman Turkey occupies also part of Syria and Iraq, it has a military presence in Libya and beyond. This neo-Ottoman Turkey has illegally intervened in the eastern Mediterranean, violating the United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea against two EU Member States.
Paradoxically, though, the neo-Ottoman Turkey is considered an ally more than a threat. In fact, the Presidents of the Council and of the Commission had a teleconference the day after the conclusions to brief our partners, including ErdoГ„Вҹan, about European defence.
Mr Commissioner, this is hypocrisy in action. It divides us, and I strongly believe that it will not fool this House, neither the EU citizens.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:00:15</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_263"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_364"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_365"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_557">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_557</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T23:18:27</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_14"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_242">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_242</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Se hГғВЎ medidas apresentadas que sГғВЈo positivas, hГғВЎ trГғВӘs que eu gostava de sublinhar como sendo negativas e que, do meu ponto de vista, do ponto de vista do S&amp;D, violam os direitos fundamentais.
Em primeiro lugar, a ideia de dar aos Estados-Membros a liberdade de escolher com que paГғВӯs terceiro negociar para o retorno dos seus cidadГғВЈos. Eu julgo que esta liberdade ГғВ© um perigo, porque nГғВЈo vai ao encontro do que o senhor comissГғВЎrio aqui disse, que ГғВ© necessГғВЎrio haver uma polГғВӯtica comum de retorno.
Em segundo lugar, a possibilidade de as pessoas serem enviadas para paГғВӯses terceiros que nГғВЈo ratificaram nenhum instrumento de direito internacional ou que cooperam com entidades nГғВЈo reconhecidas, incluindo as que controlam partes dos paГғВӯses que nГғВЈo sГғВЈo reconhecidos do ponto de vista diplomГғВЎtico (termino) ГғВ© um perigo e julgo que devia ser revista.
E, por ГғВәltimo, Senhor ComissГғВЎrio, (estou mesmo a terminar) os menores nГғВЈo acompanhados poderem ser enviados para paГғВӯses terceiros ГғВ© um perigo e viola as liberdades mais bГғВЎsicas ГўВҖВ” e peГғВ§o ao senhor comissГғВЎrio que regresse atrГғВЎs nesse ponto.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:00:46</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_177"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_241"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_242"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_91">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_91</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Das Omnibuspaket der Kommission ist ein Synonym fГғВјr Verantwortungsflucht. Es ist ein Kniefall der KommissionsprГғВӨsidentin vor einigen wenigen groГғВҹen Konzernen, auf deren Druck hin beschlossene Gesetze wieder aufgemacht werden. Was bedeutet das: Unternehmen haften nicht mehr. Es wird nahezu unmГғВ¶glich, die Mutterfirma zur Verantwortung zu ziehen, wenn bei einer Tochterfirma Probleme identifiziert wurden. Strafzahlungen werden gestrichen.
Unser Wettbewerbsvorteil in der EuropГғВӨischen Union ist, dass die EuropГғВӨische Union fГғВјr QualitГғВӨt steht, dass Investorinnen und Investoren, dass Konsumentinnen und Konsumenten, dass Unternehmen und Staaten weltweit darauf zГғВӨhlen kГғВ¶nnen, dass bei uns hohe Standards eingehalten werdenГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ und das dГғВјrfen wir nicht aufgeben.</del:text>
    <del:text>Ik heb de heren Merz en Macron gehoord. Frankrijk en Duitsland doen mee en als zij meedoen, dan zullen andere landen sowieso mee instappen. Doe dit gewoon. Neem ook de Noren en de Britten mee aan tafel. We weten allemaal waarom. Laat ons niet gewoon meer van hetzelfde doen, alleen maar een "coalition of the willing" vormen. Er is nog ГғВ©ГғВ©n grote stap die u samen met de Commissie moet zetten ГўВҖВ“ en ik heb dit vandaag maar een paar keer gehoord ГўВҖВ“ГӮВ nl. de stap naar een Europees leger. Dat is wat we nodig hebben.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T19:19:48</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:42:34</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_62"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_78"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_90"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_91"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PfE">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Organization"/>
    <del:name>PfE</del:name>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_86">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_86</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Siegfried MureГ…Вҹan,</del:name>
    <del:name>Sviatlana Tsikhanouskaya,</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_550">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_550</del:identifier>
    <del:text>In my introductory statement, I already said a lot. So, against all odds, there are also opportunities with the dire situation in Gaza.
As a short-term measure, we need to focus on the resumption of full access to humanitarian aid. After all, it is about the most pressing needs of the population on the ground, as I already said: food, clean water and health services and, of course, electricity.
The longer-term path to recovery and reconstruction will be complex and challenging. I already explained that there is a plan, but let's see, which was endorsed by Arab countries. We are looking into it, and let's see, but there are some preconditions, meaning a ceasefire which should hold and last.
We want to go this path together with our partners in the region and with the Palestinian people. The relocation of the population or the questioning of the territorial integrity cannot have a place in a sustainable solution in Gaza.
There were some diverging views here, but I am grateful for the vast support you have shown this evening. I think that parliamentary diplomacy is also very important. Your outreach, your expertise in state-building could be essential for the future of Gaza.
Gaza's reconstruction needs the backing of all of us. So, once again, the Commission, Member States and Parliament in a team Europe spirit.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T23:14:49</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_349"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_549"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_550"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_497">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_497</del:identifier>
    <del:text>En Syrie, cГўВҖВҷest lГўВҖВҷinverse. La grille de lecture manichГғВ©enne de certains leur a fait croire quГўВҖВҷГғВ  un bourreau ne pouvait succГғВ©der quГўВҖВҷun hГғВ©ros. Les ministres et les fonctionnaires, et malheureusement parmi eux, le ministre franГғВ§ais des affaires ГғВ©trangГғВЁres, se sont envolГғВ©s au plus vite vers la Syrie compliquГғВ©e avec des idГғВ©es simplistes. On apprend pourtant aux enfants quГўВҖВҷun train peut en cacher un autre. Faut-il rappeler ГғВ  la diplomatie europГғВ©enne quГўВҖВҷun rГғВ©gime dictatorial ГўВҖВ“ГӮВ celui dГўВҖВҷel-AssadГӮВ ГўВҖВ“ peut cacher la barbarie islamiste ГўВҖВ“ГӮВ celle du nouveau pouvoir et de ses factions armГғВ©es?
La prudence nГўВҖВҷaurait pas permis dГўВҖВҷГғВ©viter le terrible massacre des Alaouites, mais elle aurait ГғВ©vitГғВ© le dГғВ©shonneur. Honte ГғВ  ceux qui ont tendu la main aux nouveaux maГғВ®tres de la Syrie alors quГўВҖВҷelle ГғВ©tait sale des atrocitГғВ©s dГўВҖВҷhier et quГўВҖВҷelle est pleine des crimes de demain!</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:56:38</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_227"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_496"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_497"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_351">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_351</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Mariusz KamiГ…В„ski,</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_345">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_345</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Lina GГғВЎlvez</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_203">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_203</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Stefano Cavedagna</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_347">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_347</del:identifier>
    <del:text>I am a committed transatlanticist, and I still refuse to believe that this is the end. I still have faith that America will be back, but I also know that Europe cannot wait for that. This is why it is good that European leaders are finally waking up. It is good to invest EURГӮВ 800ГӮВ billion in defence. It is good that countries like Germany are finally breaking free from self-imposed fiscal straitjackets.
But funds alone are not enough: we must anchor this investment in a broader security strategy, one that recognises that, in an era of hybrid warfare, social cohesion and resilience are just as vital for our security as tanks and drones. This white book offers the opportunity for us to do just that, to be a blueprint for a whole-of-society approach to defence. One that defends Europe, regardless of who is sitting in the White House.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:39:47</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_251"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_346"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_347"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_234">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_234</del:identifier>
    <del:text>GГ„В§andna wkoll dimensjoni interna u esterna ta' din l-issue. Wara kollox gГ„В§aГ„ВӢ-Г„ВӢittadin qed nitkellmu fuq disponibilitГғВ . Internament, gГ„В§andna l-pakkett tal-farmaГ„ВӢewtiГ„ВӢi li gГ„В§adu jqassam is-suq f'market authorisations gГ„В§al kull pajjiГ…Вј. Dan qed jippenalizza bil-kbir gГ…Вјejjer bГ„В§al Malta. Dan suppost suq wieГ„В§ed. Г„ВҰbieb tiegГ„В§i, jekk tiГ„ВЎu Malta tisimgГ„В§u Г„В§afna l-kelma out of stock, fl-isptar, fl-ispiГ…Вјeriji, out of stock. Ejja naГ„В§dmu flimkien biex ikollna Suq Ewropew gГ„В§all-MediГ„ВӢini gГ„В§all-Ewropej kollha.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:39:24</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_172"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_233"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_234"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_195">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_195</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Nicolas Bay</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_221">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_221</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Aber LieferengpГғВӨsse sind vermeidbar. Sie sind das Ergebnis von politischen Rahmenbedingungen, die die nationale und europГғВӨische Politik setzen. Wir kГғВ¶nnen diese Rahmenbedingungen ГғВӨndern; der CMA wird dazu einen Beitrag leisten. Wir kГғВ¶nnen die AbhГғВӨngigkeiten reduzieren und stabile Lieferketten schaffen, wenn wir sie fГғВјr uns fГғВјr eine starke, nachhaltige und international wettbewerbsfГғВӨhige Pharmaindustrie in Europa einsetzen. Die aktuellen EngpГғВӨsse sind ein wakeГўВҖВ‘up call. Europa braucht eine starke Pharmaindustrie. Dazu mГғВјssen wir IndustrieГўВҖВ‘, ForschungsГўВҖВ‘ und Gesundheitspolitik zusammen denken, die gesamte WertschГғВ¶pfungskette in den Blick nehmen und die richtigen Signale an die Unternehmen aussenden.
Wir mГғВјssen bei kritischen Wirkstoffen und Antibiotika, von denen heute zwei Drittel in Asien produziert werden, Anreize fГғВјr eine eigene Produktion in Europa schaffen. DafГғВјr brauchen wir finanzielle Anreize, und wir brauchen schnellere Genehmigungsverfahren, die unternehmerisches Engagement honorieren. Meine Erwartung an den CMA ist deshalb ganz klar: Er muss einen Beitrag zur besseren VerfГғВјgbarkeit von Arzneimitteln durch Anreize fГғВјr mehr Produktion, stabilere Lieferketten und mehr SolidaritГғВӨt untereinander liefern.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:22:09</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_164"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_220"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_221"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_79">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_79</del:identifier>
    <del:name>DГғВіra DГғВЎvid</del:name>
    <del:name>Ana Miranda Paz</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Verts_ALE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_236">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_236</del:identifier>
    <del:text>One should not forget about the other proposal, which is the reform of the EU pharmaceutical legislation. This House has already managed to come to an agreement. I hope that we will have very quickly an agreement also in the Council, so that these two pieces of legislation can go hand in hand and help us to create the security of supply across the board and in every Member State, because it is very clear also from this debate, the immense risk the shortages of critical medicines can create. And we have seen this already in the COVID crisis.
Now, maybe to respond to one of the key issues that was mentioned here by Mr Sokol. And then there was an exchange between him and Mr WГғВ¶lken about the stock planning. Just to make it very clear. We have clear provisions now so that when Member States are setting their own rules, when it comes to the security of supply, they will be required by this law to come forward with programmes and to communicate this to the Commission, but also to other Member states. And when they do that, they have to be mindful when defining the scope of which products are covered, but also in terms of the timings or the time periods necessary, that it has to be proportionate. It has to be done in a transparent and in a solid way so that they are not putting risks on other Member States. I think this is a topic which we have all seen during the COVID crisis, but it is a reoccurring one, and this is why we have included this in the proposal itself.
Now, one of you also mentioned the issue of orphan drugs. I would also add the need for new antibiotics. This is why we have enlarged the scope of the act to cover all potential products, where we will have a critical need emerging so that we will be much faster to react to any problems on the market. And we will be able to deliver these products much faster.
And finally, on the points raised by many about transparency. I think it is very clear that this Commission aims for full transparency when it comes to the implementation of this act. This is why joint procurement is the key tool through which we are going from where the conditions and costs are going to be public, as it is the case in any procurement. Same goes for the facilities created through the possibility of providing State aid for re-attracting manufacturing capacities in the EU. I think the State aid rules already have a very high level of transparency in the European Union.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:42:08</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_144"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_235"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_236"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_453">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_453</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Algunos estГғВЎn promocionando aquГғВӯ la vuelta a los combustibles fГғВіsiles, al gas, que fue verdaderamente el problema que lastrГғВі nuestra competitividad en los ГғВәltimos aГғВұos aumentando los precios de la energГғВӯa. Por eso, cuando estos grupos hablan de promover de nuevo los fГғВіsiles, realmente quienes se frotan las manos son Putin y Trump. Por lo tanto, nosotros debemos continuar apostando por una energГғВӯa limpia ГўВҖВ”preferiblemente renovableГўВҖВ” y apostar por las interconexiones. AdemГғВЎs, la financiaciГғВіn es una condiciГғВіn imprescindible para lograrlo. Damos la bienvenida a los 100ГӮВ 000 millones de euros, pero creemos que esto debe continuar en el nuevo marco financiero plurianual.
Miren, vivimos en un mundo hostil, pero no debemos hacer caso a la propaganda antieuropea. Valoremos nuestra posiciГғВіn favorable y lo que hemos construido. Nuestras condiciones de vida tambiГғВ©n forman parte de nuestra competitividad.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:51:54</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_160"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_452"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_453"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_445">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_445</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Az infrastrukturГғВЎlis fejlesztГғВ©sek hiГғВЎnya mГғВЎshol is ГғВ©rezteti a hatГғВЎsГғВЎt. PГғВ©ldГғВЎul 2029 elГ…В‘tt nem vГғВЎrhatГғВіak ГғВәj szГғВ©lerГ…В‘mГ…Вұ- kapacitГғВЎsok, a hГғВЎlГғВіzati csatlakozГғВЎsok szГ…ВұkГғВ¶ssГғВ©ge miatt. A magyar ipar kiszolgГғВЎltatottsГғВЎgГғВЎt tovГғВЎbbГғВЎ nГғВ¶veli az is, hogy bГғВЎr a kormГғВЎny elhanyagolta az energiaberuhГғВЎzГғВЎsokat, most adГғВіfizetГ…В‘i pГғВ©nzbГ…В‘l csГғВЎbГғВӯtja be a gigГғВЎszi energiaГғВ©hsГғВ©gГ…Вұ kГғВӯnai akkumulГғВЎtorgyГғВЎrakat ГғВ©s autГғВіgyГғВЎrakat. ГғВҚgy pedig tovГғВЎbb emelkednek az ГғВЎramГғВЎrak, amelyek kГғВ¶zvetlenГғВјl a magyar vГғВЎllalkozГғВЎsok versenykГғВ©pessГғВ©gГғВ©t is veszГғВ©lyeztetik.
A magyar helyzet megmutatja, milyen kГғВЎrokat tud okozni a megfizethetГ…В‘ energiakГғВӯnГғВЎlat hiГғВЎnya a versenykГғВ©pessГғВ©gnek. Ezzel szemben a tiszta ipari megГғВЎllapodГғВЎsban kijelГғВ¶lt stratГғВ©gia kivГғВЎlГғВі alapot ad a fenntarthatГғВі eurГғВіpai iparfejlesztГғВ©snek.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:40:42</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_316"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_444"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_445"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_170">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_170</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Es una amenaza comercial muy grave, porque esta guerra arancelaria tampoco tiene en Europa quiГғВ©n la defienda, seГғВұora comisaria. ГӮВҝQuГғВ© estГғВЎ haciendo la UniГғВіn Europea para potenciar sus propios astilleros y la industria auxiliar local? Nada.
Desde el BNG hemos defendido durante muchos aГғВұos que se potenciara y apoyara la industria europea con ayudas pГғВәblicas. En el caso de la industria galega, hemos defendido que da trabajo a muchos miles de trabajadores y esta industria ha sufrido recortes, reconversiones, limitaciones de producciГғВіn y competencia desleal. Y, el ГғВәltimo clavo que faltaba, la imposiciГғВіn de aranceles a una industria que es exportadora. ГӮВҝQuГғВ© va a hacer la UniГғВіn Europea para defender al sector del metal?</del:text>
    <del:text>En mi paГғВӯs, EspaГғВұa, se han tapado episodios de acoso sexual por parte de dirigentes de la izquierda al mismo tiempo que se pedГғВӯa a la poblaciГғВіn que no guardara silencio. ГӮВҝCГғВіmo se puede guardar silencio ante los mГғВәltiples escГғВЎndalos relacionados con prostituciГғВіn por parte de dirigentes socialistas del Gobierno de EspaГғВұa ГўВҖВ”al parecer, pagados con dinero pГғВәblicoГўВҖВ” y seguir defendiendo, al mismo tiempo, que su objetivo es acabar con la prostituciГғВіn? Flaco servicio a la igualdad y los derechos de las mujeres. No deberГғВӯamos proclamar en pГғВәblico lo que luego no hacemos en privado.
Tenemos derecho a una educaciГғВіn de calidad y romper con los estereotipos: contar con las mujeres con discapacidad en todos los sectores de nuestras vidas; derecho a la igualdad salarial y a tener oportunidades en el mercado de trabajo con condiciones dignas, derecho a una salud de calidad y derecho tambiГғВ©n a la conciliaciГғВіn. Sin conciliaciГғВіn ni corresponsabilidad las mujeres siempre hacen las renuncias.
Hago un llamamiento desde aquГғВӯ al Gobierno de EspaГғВұa para que traspase ya el permiso parental remunerado; si no, hay muchas mujeres que en estos momentos no se lo cogen por esa falta de transposiciГғВіn que ha llevado a la ComisiГғВіn a abrir un proceso de infracciГғВіn. EstГғВЎ el tema en el Tribunal de Justicia de la UniГғВіn Europea con una sanciГғВіn que puede llegar a los siete millones.
Nos desmarcamos del negacionismo de unos y de la hipocresГғВӯa demagГғВіgica de otros.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:26:32</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:10:46</del:timestamp>
