  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_196">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_196</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:text>On tГғВӨrkeГғВӨГғВӨ, ettГғВӨ komission uudessa naisten oikeuksien tiekartassa mainitaan digivГғВӨkivalta, joka kohdistuu erityisesti naisiin ja tyttГғВ¶ihin, rajoittaen heidГғВӨn ilmaisunvapauttaan, osallistumistaan yhteiskunnalliseen keskusteluun ja turvallisuuttaan verkossa. TГғВӨmГғВӨ on jatkumoa laajemmalle sukupuolittuneelle, rakenteelliselle vГғВӨkivallalle, joka yllГғВӨpitГғВӨГғВӨ eriarvoisuutta ja pelon ilmapiiriГғВӨ. Pekingin julistuksessa tunnistettu rakenteellinen vГғВӨkivalta tarkoittaa yhteiskunnallisia rakenteita ja kГғВӨytГғВӨntГғВ¶jГғВӨ, jotka jГғВӨttГғВӨvГғВӨt naiset marginaaliin, esimerkiksi rajoittamalla heidГғВӨn vaikutusmahdollisuuksiaan pГғВӨГғВӨtГғВ¶ksenteossa, sekГғВӨ yllГғВӨpitГғВӨmГғВӨllГғВӨ palkkaeroja ja kasautuvia hoivavastuita.

Ilman mГғВӨГғВӨrГғВӨtietoisia toimia nГғВӨmГғВӨ rakenteet jatkavat sukupuolten epГғВӨtasa-arvon syventГғВӨmistГғВӨ. Siksi EU:n on rakennettava parempi tulevaisuus jokaiselle tytГғВ¶lle ja naiselle vahvistamalla perusoikeusnГғВӨkГғВ¶kulmaa kaikessa lainsГғВӨГғВӨdГғВӨnnГғВ¶ssГғВӨ.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T21:58:46</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_117"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_143"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_195"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_196"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_80">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_80</del:identifier>
    <del:name>SunГ„ВҚana Glavak</del:name>
    <del:name>ГғВ–zlem Demirel</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_The_Left"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_554">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_554</del:identifier>
    <del:text>What were Israel's options? Do nothing? Accept any demand made by the terrorists while the hostages were still being held? No country in the world would tolerate this! The EU did not negotiate with ISIS, nor did the US negotiate with Al-Qaeda!
Just as the EU sees peace negotiations between Russia and Ukraine as dangerous and invalid without security guarantees for Ukraine, it should analyse the situation between Israel and Gaza in the same manner, as long as the hostages are not released. If not, let us admit that we are applying double standards in EU institutions.
If we truly want peace, we should start by standing with those fighting against terrorism, not by legitimizing those who practice it - including here, in Europe, in Brussels, Strasbourg, Paris, and many other places.
Which of our children will be the terroristsГўВҖВҷ next victim?</del:text>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_384"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_505">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_505</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Au vu des ГғВ©vГғВ©nements rГғВ©cents, il devient vital dГўВҖВҷempГғВӘcher quГўВҖВҷun deuxiГғВЁme Afghanistan advienne ГғВ  nos portes. Ce serait un drame humain et une menace inГғВ©dite pour lГўВҖВҷEurope.
Enfin, lГўВҖВҷUnion europГғВ©enne veut parler de transition juste avec des islamistes qui ont ГғВ©tГғВ© les principaux acteurs dГўВҖВҷattentats terroristes internationaux, ГғВ  lГўВҖВҷidГғВ©ologie totalitaire et rГғВ©trograde. Cela montre le caractГғВЁre candide de la politique europГғВ©enne, complГғВЁtement inadaptГғВ©e aux bouleversements mondiaux qui sГўВҖВҷopГғВЁrent en ce moment.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:07:40</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_357"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_504"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_505"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_200">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_200</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Jorge BuxadГғВ© Villalba</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PfE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_344">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_344</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Donnons-nous donc les moyens de cette autonomie, en changeant radicalement nos politiques industrielles et commerciales, en prГғВҙnant moins de libre-ГғВ©change et plus de protectionnisme, et en achetant europГғВ©en.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:35:14</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_248"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_343"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_344"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_222">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_222</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Piotr MГғВјller</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_297">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_297</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Dovete perГғВІ fare un enorme mea culpa. Mentre in Italia il ministro Salvini bloccava gli sbarchi, faceva crollare gli arrivi e quindi diminuiva le tragedie in mare, voi lo criticavate! Quando noi chiedevamo la redistribuzione dei migranti e la rotazione dei porti, voi dormivate.
ГғВҲ da sei anni che bloccate la riforma dei rimpatri, schiavi dei ricatti della sinistra. Ora la sbloccate ma non affrontate un problema importantissimo: non ГғВЁ prevista infatti alcuna sanzione verso gli Stati terzi che non si vogliono riprendere i loro connazionali presenti illegalmente nei nostri Paesi.
Contro l'immigrazione illegale serve un lavoro piГғВ№ coordinato e piГғВ№ fermo, sennГғВІ ci troveremo di fronte all'ennesimo vostro fallimento: disperati nei nostri territori che non hanno alcun diritto a rimanervi e che vivono delinquendo. Basta!</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:19:12</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_220"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_296"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_297"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_277">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_277</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Vasile DГғВ®ncu</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_381">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_381</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Hanna Gedin</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_The_Left"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_516">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_516</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Lo avevamo detto dopo la caduta di Assad, che non c'era da esultare per coloro che avevano preso il potere. Lo avevamo detto. Eppure, qui c'era qualcuno che aveva reagito festante per l'avvento del regime di coloro, che anche noi qui ritenevamo terroristi e, che da un momento all'altro, si sono dimostrati, invece, per questo Parlamento, moderati.
Dobbiamo, invece, difendere da costoro la nostra civiltГғВ , rappresentata dai cristiani che soffrono in tutto il mondo e, in questo momento, stanno soffrendo in Siria. Ed ГғВЁ questo che dobbiamo fare. Agiamo ora, prima che sia troppo tardi, prima che vengano sterminati o cacciati dalla propria terra.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:22:11</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_363"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_515"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_516"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_137">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_137</del:identifier>
    <del:text>In the quickly changing world order, we need to start backing words with deeds. And this growth plan shows that we will invest to lift people out of poverty, build solar panels, schools and hospitals. This growth plan shows strong reforms will make Moldova ready to join the EU. And this growth plan shows Europe chose Moldova.
And it tells it tells those that want to join our Union, if you walk the path to Europe, Europe will walk with you. We did this in four months, which for the EU is as fast as travelling at the speed of light. And the Moldovans are not wasting time either. Last week they joined the Single Euro Payments Area.
So let's vote in favour of this growth plan and show the people in Moldova, you'll never walk alone.</del:text>
    <del:text>My question to you is: would you agree with me that access to contraception and sexual and reproductive rights ГўВҖВ“ including abortion and abortion pills ГўВҖВ“ for women in rural areas is something that we should all work on?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-10T20:38:43</del:timestamp>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:32:50</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_104"/>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_101"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_136"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_137"/>
  </rdf:Description>
