  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_197">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_197</del:identifier>
    <del:text>ГҺВ‘ГҺВәГҸВҢГҺВјГҺВұ ГҸВҖГҺВ№ГҺВҝ ГҸВғГҺВҝГҺВәГҺВұГҸВҒГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ® ГҺВөГҺВҜГҺВҪГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВ· ГҺВұГҺВҙГҺВ№ГҺВ¬ГҺВәГҺВҝГҸВҖГҺВ· ГҺВјГҺВ¬ГҸВҮГҺВ· ГҺВөГҺВҪГҺВ¬ГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВұ ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҺВӯГҺВјГҸВҶГҸВ…ГҺВ»ГҺВ· ГҺВІГҺВҜГҺВұ. ГҺВҹГҺВ№ ГҺВіГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҺВұГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВҝГҺВәГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҺВҪГҺВҜГҺВөГҸВӮ, ГҺВҝГҺВ№ ГҺВІГҺВ№ГҺВұГҸВғГҺВјГҺВҝГҺВҜ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВ· ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВәГҺВҝГҸВҖГҺВҝГҺВҜГҺВ·ГҸВғГҺВ· ГҺВҙГҺВөГҺВҪ ГҺВөГҺВҜГҺВҪГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВјГҺВөГҺВјГҺВҝГҺВҪГҸВүГҺВјГҺВӯГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҸВҖГҺВөГҸВҒГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ¬ГӮВ· ГҺВөГҺВҜГҺВҪГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВҙГҺВҝГҺВјГҺВ№ГҺВәГҸВҢ ГҸВҖГҸВҒГҸВҢГҺВІГҺВ»ГҺВ·ГҺВјГҺВұ ГҺВјГҺВ№ГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВҝГҺВ№ГҺВҪГҸВүГҺВҪГҺВҜГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҺВұГҺВҪГҺВӯГҸВҮГҺВөГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҺВ· ГҺВІГҺВҜГҺВұ. ГҺВҡГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВҢГҺВјГҸВүГҸВӮ, ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҺВ•ГҺВ»ГҺВ»ГҺВ¬ГҺВҙГҺВұ ГҺВҙГҺВөГҺВҪ ГҸВ…ГҸВҖГҺВ¬ГҸВҒГҸВҮГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВҪ ГҺВҪГҺВҝГҺВјГҺВҝГҺВёГҺВөГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҸВҢ ГҸВҖГҺВ»ГҺВұГҺВҜГҸВғГҺВ№ГҺВҝ ГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВ… ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВұГҺВҪГҺВұГҺВіГҺВҪГҸВүГҸВҒГҺВҜГҺВ¶ГҺВөГҺВ№ ГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҸВӮ ГҺВіГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҺВұГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВҝГҺВәГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҺВҪГҺВҜГҺВөГҸВӮ, ГҺВҙГҺВөГҺВҪ ГҸВ…ГҸВҖГҺВ¬ГҸВҒГҸВҮГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВҪ ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВғГҺВ№ГҺВұГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ¬ ГҺВјГҺВӯГҸВ„ГҸВҒГҺВұ ГҸВҖГҸВҒГҸВҢГҺВ»ГҺВ·ГҸВҲГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҸВҖГҸВҒГҺВҝГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВұГҸВғГҺВҜГҺВұГҸВӮ ГҸВ„ГҸВүГҺВҪ ГҺВёГҸВ…ГҺВјГҺВ¬ГҸВ„ГҸВүГҺВҪ. ГҺВҹГҺВ№ ГҺВҙГҸВҒГҺВ¬ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҺВјГҺВӯГҺВҪГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВҪ ГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВјГҸВҺГҸВҒГҺВ·ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҺВ№, ГҺВөГҺВҪГҸВҺ ГҺВҝГҺВ№ ГҺВіГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҺВұГҺВҜГҺВәГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҸВғГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҺВөГҸВҮГҺВҜГҺВ¶ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВҪ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВ¶ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВҪ ГҺВјГҺВө ГҸВ„ГҺВҝГҺВҪ ГҸВҶГҸВҢГҺВІГҺВҝ.
ГҺВ— ГҺВ•ГҺВ»ГҺВ»ГҺВ¬ГҺВҙГҺВұ ГҺВҙГҺВөГҺВҪ ГҺВјГҸВҖГҺВҝГҸВҒГҺВөГҺВҜ ГҺВҪГҺВұ ГҺВөГҺВҜГҺВҪГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҸВҒГҺВұГҺВіГҸВҢГҸВӮ ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҺВҪ ГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВҢГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВ„ГҺВұ. ГҺВ§ГҸВҒГҺВөГҺВ№ГҺВұГҺВ¶ГҸВҢГҺВјГҺВұГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВө ГҺВ¬ГҺВјГҺВөГҸВғГҺВөГҸВӮ, ГҺВұГҸВ…ГҸВғГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВҒГҺВӯГҸВӮ ГҸВҖГҺВҝГҺВ»ГҺВ№ГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВӯГҸВӮ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВҙГҺВөГҸВғГҺВјГҺВөГҸВҚГҸВғГҺВөГҺВ№ГҸВӮ ГҺВјГҺВө ГҸВҖГҸВҒГҺВұГҺВіГҺВјГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҸВҢ ГҺВұГҺВҪГҸВ„ГҺВҜГҺВәГҸВ„ГҸВ…ГҸВҖГҺВҝ. ГҺВ“ГҺВ№ГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВҜ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВјГҺВҜГҺВұ ГҺВәГҺВҝГҺВ№ГҺВҪГҸВүГҺВҪГҺВҜГҺВұ ГҺВҙГҺВөГҺВҪ ГҺВөГҺВҜГҺВҪГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВҙГҺВ·ГҺВјГҺВҝГҺВәГҸВҒГҺВұГҸВ„ГҺВ№ГҺВәГҺВ® ГҸВҢГҸВ„ГҺВұГҺВҪ ГҺВҝГҺВ№ ГҺВіГҸВ…ГҺВҪГҺВұГҺВҜГҺВәГҺВөГҸВӮ ГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВӮ ГҺВ¶ГҺВҝГҸВ…ГҺВҪ ГҺВјГҺВө ГҸВҶГҸВҢГҺВІГҺВҝ ГҺВәГҺВұГҺВ№ ГҺВұГҺВҪГҺВ№ГҸВғГҸВҢГҸВ„ГҺВ·ГҸВ„ГҺВұ.</del:text>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_34"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_500">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_500</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Those working for peaceful transition are asking us, the EU, for support, not to steer the wheel, but to be the wind in their backs; to support decisively, but not naively ГўВҖВ“ decisively, because hesitation means losing this window of opportunity. We must ease sectoral sanctions that are crushing ordinary citizens. We need to support reconstruction, back democratic reforms and transitional justice, and ensure that the Syrian diaspora can contribute.
If we don't, others will fill the void, dear colleagues. But we must not support naively, because support must come with conditions: no new dictatorship, no new violence, no carving up the country like warlords, no exclusion of women opposition voices.
And to the foreign powers still meddling in Syria ГўВҖВ“ Turkey, Israel, Iran, Russia ГўВҖВ“ this is not your chessboard. Let Syrians finally reclaim their own future.
None of this is easy. None of this is quick. Fighting erupted again over the weekend, fuelled yet again by external interference and foreign fighters. This is exactly the vicious circle that Syrians want to break and that this new government must break. That's why we need to step up our support ГўВҖВ“ so that Syrians can rebuild their homes, heal their wounds and turn their country into a country for everyone.
(The President cut off the speaker)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:00:23</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_352"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_499"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_500"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_379">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_379</del:identifier>
    <del:text>O Livro Branco sobre o futuro da defesa europeia ГғВ© um bom ГўВҖВ” ГғВ© um excelente ГўВҖВ” alicerce, sobre o qual construiremos uma verdadeira UniГғВЈo Europeia da Defesa.ГӮВ As nossas prioridades sГғВЈo claras: uma abordagem abrangente ГғВ  seguranГғВ§a europeia, aumentar significativamente o investimento em defesa e desenvolver uma indГғВәstria de defesa credГғВӯvel, autГғВіnoma e soberana.
A ComissГғВЈo apresentou o plano ReArm Europe para mobilizar, inicialmente, 800 mil milhГғВөes de euros. Apoiamos estas medidas, mas exigimos compromissos vinculativos e imediatos com responsabilidades atribuГғВӯdas a todos os EstadosГўВҖВ‘Membros.
A diplomacia sem capacidade de dissuasГғВЈo ГғВ© um pleno exercГғВӯcio de fraqueza. ГғВү tempo de honrar a responsabilidade histГғВіrica que nos foi confiada, e a HistГғВіria serГғВЎ escrita em funГғВ§ГғВЈo da nossa aГғВ§ГғВЈo ou da nossa inaГғВ§ГғВЈo.
(O orador aceita responder a uma pergunta ГӮВ«cartГғВЈo azulГӮВ»)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:20:35</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_82"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_378"/>
    <del:follows rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_379"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_102">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_102</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Mariusz KamiГ…В„ski</del:name>
    <del:name>Joanna Scheuring-Wielgus</del:name>
    <del:platform>EU Parliament</del:platform>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
